  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 51ee3e37f5ded7941ab6216610f6fc67, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '  These are the words of Jeremiah son of Hilkiah, one of the priests
        from the town of Anathoth in the land of Benjamin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> first gave messages to Jeremiah during
        the thirteenth year of the reign of Josiah son of Amon, king of Judah.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:2 '
        content: "The thirteenth year of Josiah\u2019s reign was 627 <span class=\"ChapterContent_sc__Hg9da\">b.c.</span>"
    - name: "3: Jeremiah\u2019s Call and First Visions"
      title: "Jeremiah\u2019s Call and First Visions"
      number: 3
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s messages continued throughout
        the reign of King Jehoiakim, Josiah\u2019s son, until the eleventh year of
        the reign of King Zedekiah, another of Josiah\u2019s sons. In August[[COMMENT(0)]]
        of that eleventh year the people of Jerusalem were taken away as captives.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:3 '
        content: "Hebrew <b>In the fifth month, </b>of the ancient Hebrew lunar calendar.
          A number of events in Jeremiah can be cross-checked with dates in surviving
          Babylonian records and related accurately to our modern calendar. The fifth
          month in the eleventh year of Zedekiah\u2019s reign occurred within the
          months of August and September 586 <span class=\"ChapterContent_sc__Hg9da\">b.c.</span>
          Also see 52:12 and the note there."
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave me this message:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CI knew you before I formed you in your mother\u2019s womb.Before
        you were born I set you apartand appointed you as my prophet to the nations.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CO Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,\u201D I said, \u201CI
        can\u2019t speak for you! I\u2019m too young!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> replied, \u201CDon\u2019t say, \u2018I\u2019m
        too young,\u2019 for you must go wherever I send you and say whatever I tell
        you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And don\u2019t be afraid of the people, for I will be with you and
        will protect you. I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, have spoken!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> reached out and touched my mouth
        and said,\u201CLook, I have put my words in your mouth!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Today I appoint you to stand upagainst nations and kingdoms.Some
        you must uproot and tear down,destroy and overthrow.Others you must build
        upand plant.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me, \u201CLook, Jeremiah!
        What do you see?\u201DAnd I replied, \u201CI see a branch from an almond
        tree.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said, \u201CThat\u2019s right,
        and it means that I am watching,[[COMMENT(0)]] and I will certainly carry
        out all my plans.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:12 '
        content: "The Hebrew word for \u201Cwatching\u201D <b>(shoqed) </b>sounds
          like the word for \u201Calmond tree\u201D <b>(shaqed).</b>"
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> spoke to me again and asked,
        \u201CWhat do you see now?\u201DAnd I replied, \u201CI see a pot of boiling
        water, spilling from the north.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CYes,\u201D the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said, \u201Cfor
        terror from the north will boil out on the people of this land. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Listen! I am calling the armies of the kingdoms of the north to come
        to Jerusalem. I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, have spoken!\u201CThey
        will set their thronesat the gates of the city.They will attack its wallsand
        all the other towns of Judah.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "I will pronounce judgmenton my people for all their evil\u2014for
        deserting me and burning incense to other gods.Yes, they worship idols made
        with their own hands!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CGet up and prepare for action.Go out and tell them everything
        I tell you to say.Do not be afraid of them,or I will make you look foolish
        in front of them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "For see, today I have made you stronglike a fortified city that cannot
        be captured,like an iron pillar or a bronze wall.You will stand against the
        whole land\u2014the kings, officials, priests, and people of Judah.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "They will fight you, but they will fail.For I am with you, and I
        will take care of you.I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, have spoken!\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: The \u2019s Case against His People"
      title: "The \u2019s Case against His People"
      number: 1
      content: '<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave
        me another message. He said, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CGo and shout this message to Jerusalem. This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        says:\u201CI remember how eager you were to please meas a young bride long
        ago,how you loved me and followed meeven through the barren wilderness.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "In those days Israel was holy to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,the
        first of his children.[[COMMENT(0)]]All who harmed his people were declared
        guilty,and disaster fell on them.I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, have
        spoken!\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:3 '
        content: Hebrew <b>the firstfruits of his harvest.</b>
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Listen to the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, people of
        Jacob\u2014all you families of Israel! "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\u201CWhat did
        your ancestors find wrong with methat led them to stray so far from me?They
        worshiped worthless idols,only to become worthless themselves.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "They did not ask, \u2018Where is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>who
        brought us safely out of Egyptand led us through the barren wilderness\u2014a
        land of deserts and pits,a land of drought and death,where no one lives or
        even travels?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CAnd when I brought you into a fruitful landto enjoy its bounty
        and goodness,you defiled my landand corrupted the possession I had promised
        you.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "The priests did not ask,\u2018Where is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>?\u2019Those
        who taught my word ignored me,the rulers turned against me,and the prophets
        spoke in the name of Baal,wasting their time on worthless idols.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Therefore, I will bring my case against you,\u201Dsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201CI
        will even bring charges against your children\u2019s childrenin the years
        to come.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CGo west and look in the land of Cyprus[[COMMENT(0)]];go east
        and search through the land of Kedar.Has anyone ever heard of anythingas
        strange as this?  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:10 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Kittim.</b>
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Has any nation ever traded its gods for new ones,even though they
        are not gods at all?Yet my people have exchanged their glorious God[[COMMENT(0)]]for
        worthless idols!  '
      comments:
      - number: '2:11 '
        content: Hebrew <b>their glory.</b>
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "The heavens are shocked at such a thingand shrink back in horror
        and dismay,\u201Dsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: "13: The Results of Israel\u2019s Sin"
      title: "The Results of Israel\u2019s Sin"
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CFor my people have done two evil things:They have abandoned
        me\u2014the fountain of living water.And they have dug for themselves cracked
        cisternsthat can hold no water at all!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CWhy has Israel become a slave?Why has he been carried away
        as plunder?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Strong lions have roared against him,and the land has been destroyed.The
        towns are now in ruins,and no one lives in them anymore.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Egyptians, marching from their cities of Memphis[[COMMENT(0)]] and
        Tahpanhes,have destroyed Israel\u2019s glory and power.  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:16 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Noph.</b>
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And you have brought this upon yourselvesby rebelling against the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God,even though he was leading you on the
        way!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CWhat have you gained by your alliances with Egyptand your covenants
        with Assyria?What good to you are the streams of the Nile[[COMMENT(0)]]or
        the waters of the Euphrates River?[[COMMENT(1)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:18a '
        content: Hebrew <b>of Shihor, </b>a branch of the Nile River.
      - number: '2:18b '
        content: Hebrew <b>the river?</b>
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Your wickedness will bring its own punishment.Your turning from me
        will shame you.You will see what an evil, bitter thing it isto abandon the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God and not to fear him.I, the Lord, the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies, have spoken!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CLong ago I broke the yoke that oppressed youand tore away the
        chains of your slavery,but still you said,\u2018I will not serve you.\u2019On
        every hill and under every green tree,you have prostituted yourselves by
        bowing down to idols.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "But I was the one who planted you,choosing a vine of the purest stock\u2014the
        very best.How did you grow into this corrupt wild vine?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: Israel, an Unfaithful Wife'
      title: Israel, an Unfaithful Wife
      number: 22
      content: 'No amount of soap or lye can make you clean.I still see the stain
        of your guilt.I, the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, have spoken!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CYou say, \u2018That\u2019s not true!I haven\u2019t worshiped
        the images of Baal!\u2019But how can you say that?Go and look in any valley
        in the land!Face the awful sins you have done.You are like a restless female
        cameldesperately searching for a mate.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "You are like a wild donkey,sniffing the wind at mating time.Who can
        restrain her lust?Those who desire her don\u2019t need to search,for she
        goes running to them!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "When will you stop running?When will you stop panting after other
        gods?But you say, \u2018Save your breath.I\u2019m in love with these foreign
        gods,and I can\u2019t stop loving them now!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CIsrael is like a thiefwho feels shame only when he gets caught.They,
        their kings, officials, priests, and prophets\u2014all are alike in this.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "To an image carved from a piece of wood they say,\u2018You are my
        father.\u2019To an idol chiseled from a block of stone they say,\u2018You
        are my mother.\u2019They turn their backs on me,but in times of trouble they
        cry out to me,\u2018Come and save us!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'But why not call on these gods you have made?When trouble comes,
        let them save you if they can!For you have as many godsas there are towns
        in Judah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Why do you accuse me of doing wrong?You are the ones who have rebelled,\u201Dsays
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "\u201CI have punished your children,but they did not respond to my
        discipline.You yourselves have killed your prophetsas a lion kills its prey.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "\u201CO my people, listen to the words of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>!Have
        I been like a desert to Israel?Have I been to them a land of darkness?Why
        then do my people say, \u2018At last we are free from God!We don\u2019t need
        him anymore!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Does a young woman forget her jewelry,or a bride her wedding dress?Yet
        for years on endmy people have forgotten me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "\u201CHow you plot and scheme to win your lovers.Even an experienced
        prostitute could learn from you!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Your clothing is stained with the blood of the innocent and the poor,though
        you didn\u2019t catch them breaking into your houses!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "And yet you say,\u2018I have done nothing wrong.Surely God isn\u2019t
        angry with me!\u2019But now I will punish you severelybecause you claim you
        have not sinned.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "First here, then there\u2014you flit from one ally to another asking
        for help.But your new friends in Egypt will let you down,just as Assyria
        did before.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: In despair, you will be led into exilewith your hands on your heads,for
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has rejected the nations you trust.They will
        not help you at all.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CIf a man divorces a womanand she goes and marries someone
        else,he will not take her back again,for that would surely corrupt the land.But
        you have prostituted yourself with many lovers,so why are you trying to come
        back to me?\u201Dsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CLook at the shrines on every hilltop.Is there any place you
        have not been defiledby your adultery with other gods?You sit like a prostitute
        beside the road waiting for a customer.You sit alone like a nomad in the
        desert.You have polluted the land with your prostitutionand your wickedness.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "That\u2019s why even the spring rains have failed.For you are a brazen
        prostitute and completely shameless.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Yet you say to me,\u2018Father, you have been my guide since my youth.  "
      comments: []
    - name: "5: Judah Follows Israel\u2019s Example"
      title: "Judah Follows Israel\u2019s Example"
      number: 5
      content: "Surely you won\u2019t be angry forever!Surely you can forget about
        it!\u2019So you talk,but you keep on doing all the evil you can.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "During the reign of King Josiah, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        said to me, \u201CHave you seen what fickle Israel has done? Like a wife
        who commits adultery, Israel has worshiped other gods on every hill and under
        every green tree. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "I thought, \u2018After she has done all this, she will return to
        me.\u2019 But she did not return, and her faithless sister Judah saw this. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'She saw[[COMMENT(0)]] that I divorced faithless Israel because of
        her adultery. But that treacherous sister Judah had no fear, and now she,
        too, has left me and given herself to prostitution. '
      comments:
      - number: '3:8 '
        content: As in Dead Sea Scrolls, one Greek manuscript, and Syriac version;
          Masoretic Text reads <b>I saw.</b>
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Israel treated it all so lightly\u2014she thought nothing of committing
        adultery by worshiping idols made of wood and stone. So now the land has
        been polluted. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Hope for Wayward Israel'
      title: Hope for Wayward Israel
      number: 10
      content: "But despite all this, her faithless sister Judah has never sincerely
        returned to me. She has only pretended to be sorry. I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        have spoken!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me, \u201CEven faithless
        Israel is less guilty than treacherous Judah! "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Therefore, go and give this message to Israel.[[COMMENT(0)]] This
        is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\u201CO Israel, my faithless
        people,come home to me again,for I am merciful.I will not be angry with you
        forever.  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:12 '
        content: Hebrew <b>toward the north.</b>
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Only acknowledge your guilt.Admit that you rebelled against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your Godand committed adultery against himby worshiping idols under every
        green tree.Confess that you refused to listen to my voice.I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        have spoken!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CReturn home, you wayward children,\u201Dsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,\u201Cfor
        I am your master.I will bring you back to the land of Israel[[COMMENT(0)]]\u2014one
        from this town and two from that family\u2014from wherever you are scattered.  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:14 '
        content: Hebrew <b>to Zion.</b>
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And I will give you shepherds after my own heart,who will guide you
        with knowledge and understanding.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CAnd when your land is once more filled with people,\u201D says
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, \u201Cyou will no longer wish for \u2018the
        good old days\u2019 when you possessed the Ark of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        Covenant. You will not miss those days or even remember them, and there will
        be no need to rebuild the Ark. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "In that day Jerusalem will be known as \u2018The Throne of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u2019
        All nations will come there to honor the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. They
        will no longer stubbornly follow their own evil desires. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'In those days the people of Judah and Israel will return together
        from exile in the north. They will return to the land I gave your ancestors
        as an inheritance forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CI thought to myself,\u2018I would love to treat you as my own
        children!\u2019I wanted nothing more than to give you this beautiful land\u2014the
        finest possession in the world.I looked forward to your calling me \u2018Father,\u2019and
        I wanted you never to turn from me.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "But you have been unfaithful to me, you people of Israel!You have
        been like a faithless wife who leaves her husband.I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        have spoken.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Voices are heard high on the windswept mountains,the weeping and
        pleading of Israel\u2019s people.For they have chosen crooked pathsand have
        forgotten the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> their God.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CMy wayward children,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,\u201Ccome
        back to me, and I will heal your wayward hearts.\u201D\u201CYes, we\u2019re
        coming,\u201D the people reply,\u201Cfor you are the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        our God.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Our worship of idols on the hillsand our religious orgies on the
        mountainsare a delusion.Only in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our Godwill
        Israel ever find salvation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "From childhood we have watchedas everything our ancestors worked
        for\u2014their flocks and herds, their sons and daughters\u2014was squandered
        on a delusion.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Let us now lie down in shameand cover ourselves with dishonor,for
        we and our ancestors have sinnedagainst the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our
        God.From our childhood to this daywe have never obeyed him.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CO Israel,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,\u201Cif
        you wanted to return to me, you could.You could throw away your detestable
        idolsand stray away no more.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: Coming Judgment against Judah'
      title: Coming Judgment against Judah
      number: 2
      content: "Then when you swear by my name, saying,\u2018As surely as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        lives,\u2019you could do sowith truth, justice, and righteousness.Then you
        would be a blessing to the nations of the world,and all people would come
        and praise my name.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says to the people of
        Judah and Jerusalem:\u201CPlow up the hard ground of your hearts!Do not waste
        your good seed among thorns.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'O people of Judah and Jerusalem,surrender your pride and power.Change
        your hearts before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,[[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps>or
        my anger will burn like an unquenchable fire</smallcaps>because of all your
        sins.  '
      comments:
      - number: '4:4 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Circumcise yourselves to the <span class="ChapterContent_nd__ECPAf">Lord</span>,
          and take away the foreskins of your heart.</b>
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CShout to Judah, and broadcast to Jerusalem!Tell them to sound
        the alarm throughout the land:\u2018Run for your lives!Flee to the fortified
        cities!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Raise a signal flag as a warning for Jerusalem[[COMMENT(0)]]:\u2018Flee
        now! Do not delay!\u2019For I am bringing terrible destruction upon youfrom
        the north.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:6 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Zion.</b>
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "A lion stalks from its den,a destroyer of nations.It has left its
        lair and is headed your way.It\u2019s going to devastate your land!Your towns
        will lie in ruins,with no one living in them anymore.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So put on clothes of mourningand weep with broken hearts,for the
        fierce anger of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>is still upon us.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CIn that day,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,\u201Cthe
        king and the officials will tremble in fear.The priests will be struck with
        horror,and the prophets will be appalled.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then I said, \u201CO Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,the people
        have been deceived by what you said,for you promised peace for Jerusalem.But
        the sword is held at their throats!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "The time is coming when the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will sayto
        the people of Jerusalem,\u201CMy dear people, a burning wind is blowing in
        from the desert,and it\u2019s not a gentle breeze useful for winnowing grain.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "It is a roaring blast sent by me!Now I will pronounce your destruction!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Our enemy rushes down on us like storm clouds!His chariots are like
        whirlwinds.His horses are swifter than eagles.How terrible it will be, for
        we are doomed!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'O Jerusalem, cleanse your heartthat you may be saved.How long will
        you harboryour evil thoughts?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Your destruction has been announcedfrom Dan and the hill country
        of Ephraim.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CWarn the surrounding nationsand announce this to Jerusalem:The
        enemy is coming from a distant land,raising a battle cry against the towns
        of Judah.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "They surround Jerusalem like watchmen around a field,for my people
        have rebelled against me,\u201Dsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: Jeremiah Weeps for His People'
      title: Jeremiah Weeps for His People
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CYour own actions have brought this upon you.This punishment
        is bitter, piercing you to the heart!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "My heart, my heart\u2014I writhe in pain!My heart pounds within me!
        I cannot be still.For I have heard the blast of enemy trumpetsand the roar
        of their battle cries.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Waves of destruction roll over the land,until it lies in complete
        desolation.Suddenly my tents are destroyed;in a moment my shelters are crushed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'How long must I see the battle flagsand hear the trumpets of war?  '
      comments: []
    - name: "22: Jeremiah\u2019s Vision of Coming Disaster"
      title: "Jeremiah\u2019s Vision of Coming Disaster"
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CMy people are foolishand do not know me,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201CThey
        are stupid childrenwho have no understanding.They are clever enough at doing
        wrong,but they have no idea how to do right!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'I looked at the earth, and it was empty and formless.I looked at
        the heavens, and there was no light.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'I looked at the mountains and hills,and they trembled and shook.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'I looked, and all the people were gone.All the birds of the sky had
        flown away.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "I looked, and the fertile fields had become a wilderness.The towns
        lay in ruins,crushed by the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s fierce anger.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\u201CThe whole
        land will be ruined,but I will not destroy it completely.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "The earth will mournand the heavens will be draped in blackbecause
        of my decree against my people.I have made up my mind and will not change
        it.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "At the noise of charioteers and archers,the people flee in terror.They
        hide in the bushesand run for the mountains.All the towns have been abandoned\u2014not
        a person remains!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'What are you doing,you who have been plundered?Why do you dress up
        in beautiful clothingand put on gold jewelry?Why do you brighten your eyes
        with mascara?Your primping will do you no good!The allies who were your loversdespise
        you and seek to kill you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "I hear a cry, like that of a woman in labor,the groans of a woman
        giving birth to her first child.It is beautiful Jerusalem[[COMMENT(0)]]gasping
        for breath and crying out,\u201CHelp! I\u2019m being murdered!\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: '4:31 '
        content: Hebrew <b>the daughter of Zion.</b>
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Sins of Judah'
      title: The Sins of Judah
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CRun up and down every street in Jerusalem,\u201D says the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201CLook high and low; search throughout the
        city!If you can find even one just and honest person,I will not destroy the
        city.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "But even when they are under oath,saying, \u2018As surely as the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> lives,\u2019they are still telling lies!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '  <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, you are searching for honesty.You
        struck your people,but they paid no attention.You crushed them,but they refused
        to be corrected.They are determined, with faces set like stone;they have
        refused to repent.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then I said, \u201CBut what can we expect from the poor?They are
        ignorant.They don\u2019t know the ways of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.They
        don\u2019t understand God\u2019s laws.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "So I will go and speak to their leaders.Surely they know the ways
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>and understand God\u2019s laws.\u201DBut
        the leaders, too, as one man,had thrown off God\u2019s yokeand broken his
        chains.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So now a lion from the forest will attack them;a wolf from the desert
        will pounce on them.A leopard will lurk near their towns,tearing apart any
        who dare to venture out.For their rebellion is great,and their sins are many.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CHow can I pardon you?For even your children have turned from
        me.They have sworn by gods that are not gods at all!I fed my people until
        they were full.But they thanked me by committing adulteryand lining up at
        the brothels.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "They are well-fed, lusty stallions,each neighing for his neighbor\u2019s
        wife.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Should I not punish them for this?\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201CShould
        I not avenge myself against such a nation?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CGo down the rows of the vineyards and destroy the grapevines,leaving
        a scattered few alive.Strip the branches from the vines,for these people
        do not belong to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "The people of Israel and Judahare full of treachery against me,\u201Dsays
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CThey have lied about the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>and said,
        \u2018He won\u2019t bother us!No disasters will come upon us.There will be
        no war or famine.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "God\u2019s prophets are all windbagswho don\u2019t really speak for
        him.Let their predictions of disaster fall on themselves!\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Therefore, this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> God of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies says:\u201CBecause the people are talking like this,my messages will
        flame out of your mouthand burn the people like kindling wood.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "O Israel, I will bring a distant nation against you,\u201Dsays the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201CIt is a mighty nation,an ancient nation,a
        people whose language you do not know,whose speech you cannot understand.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Their weapons are deadly;their warriors are mighty.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'They will devour the food of your harvest;they will devour your sons
        and daughters.They will devour your flocks and herds;they will devour your
        grapes and figs.And they will destroy your fortified towns,which you think
        are so safe.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CYet even in those days I will not blot you out completely,\u201D
        says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. "
      comments: []
    - name: "19: A Warning for God\u2019s People"
      title: "A Warning for God\u2019s People"
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CAnd when your people ask, \u2018Why did the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        our God do all this to us?\u2019 you must reply, \u2018You rejected him and
        gave yourselves to foreign gods in your own land. Now you will serve foreigners
        in a land that is not your own.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CMake this announcement to Israel,[[COMMENT(0)]]and say this
        to Judah:  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:20 '
        content: "Hebrew <b>to the house of Jacob. </b>The names \u201CJacob\u201D
          and \u201CIsrael\u201D are often interchanged throughout the Old Testament,
          referring sometimes to the individual patriarch and sometimes to the nation."
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Listen, you foolish and senseless people,with eyes that do not seeand
        ears that do not hear.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Have you no respect for me?Why don\u2019t you tremble in my presence?I,
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, define the ocean\u2019s sandy shorelineas
        an everlasting boundary that the waters cannot cross.The waves may toss and
        roar,but they can never pass the boundaries I set.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'But my people have stubborn and rebellious hearts.They have turned
        away and abandoned me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "They do not say from the heart,\u2018Let us live in awe of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        our God,for he gives us rain each spring and fall,assuring us of a harvest
        when the time is right.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Your wickedness has deprived you of these wonderful blessings.Your
        sin has robbed you of all these good things.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CAmong my people are wicked menwho lie in wait for victims like
        a hunter hiding in a blind.They continually set trapsto catch people.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Like a cage filled with birds,their homes are filled with evil plots.And
        now they are great and rich.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'They are fat and sleek,and there is no limit to their wicked deeds.They
        refuse to provide justice to orphansand deny the rights of the poor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Should I not punish them for this?\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201CShould
        I not avenge myself against such a nation?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "A horrible and shocking thinghas happened in this land\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: the prophets give false prophecies,and the priests rule with an iron
        hand.Worse yet, my people like it that way!But what will you do when the
        end comes?
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Jerusalem\u2019s Last Warning"
      title: "Jerusalem\u2019s Last Warning"
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CRun for your lives, you people of Benjamin!Get out of Jerusalem!Sound
        the alarm in Tekoa!Send up a signal at Beth-hakkerem!A powerful army is coming
        from the north,coming with disaster and destruction.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "O Jerusalem,[[COMMENT(0)]] you are my beautiful and delicate daughter\u2014but
        I will destroy you!  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:2 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Daughter of Zion.</b>
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Enemies will surround you, like shepherds camped around the city.Each
        chooses a place for his troops to devour.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "They shout, \u2018Prepare for battle!Attack at noon!\u2019\u2018No,
        it\u2019s too late; the day is fading,and the evening shadows are falling.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u2018Well then, let\u2019s attack at nightand destroy her palaces!\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies
        says:\u201CCut down the trees for battering rams.Build siege ramps against
        the walls of Jerusalem.This is the city to be punished,for she is wicked
        through and through.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'She spouts evil like a fountain.Her streets echo with the sounds
        of violence and destruction.I always see her sickness and sores.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Listen to this warning, Jerusalem,or I will turn from you in disgust.Listen,
        or I will turn you into a heap of ruins,a land where no one lives.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: "9: Judah\u2019s Constant Rebellion"
      title: "Judah\u2019s Constant Rebellion"
      number: 9
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies
        says:\u201CEven the few who remain in Israelwill be picked over again,as
        when a harvester checks each vine a second timeto pick the grapes that were
        missed.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "To whom can I give warning?Who will listen when I speak?Their ears
        are closed,and they cannot hear.They scorn the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.They
        don\u2019t want to listen at all.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So now I am filled with the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s fury.Yes,
        I am tired of holding it in!\u201CI will pour out my fury on children playing
        in the streetsand on gatherings of young men,on husbands and wivesand on
        those who are old and gray.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Their homes will be turned over to their enemies,as will their fields
        and their wives.For I will raise my powerful fistagainst the people of this
        land,\u201Dsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CFrom the least to the greatest,their lives are ruled by greed.From
        prophets to priests,they are all frauds.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "They offer superficial treatmentsfor my people\u2019s mortal wound.They
        give assurances of peacewhen there is no peace.  "
      comments: []
    - name: "15: Judah Rejects the \u2019s Way"
      title: "Judah Rejects the \u2019s Way"
      number: 15
      content: "Are they ashamed of their disgusting actions?Not at all\u2014they
        don\u2019t even know how to blush!Therefore, they will lie among the slaughtered.They
        will be brought down when I punish them,\u201Dsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\u201CStop at the
        crossroads and look around.Ask for the old, godly way, and walk in it.Travel
        its path, and you will find rest for your souls.But you reply, \u2018No,
        that\u2019s not the road we want!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "I posted watchmen over you who said,\u2018Listen for the sound of
        the alarm.\u2019But you replied,\u2018No! We won\u2019t pay attention!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CTherefore, listen to this, all you nations.Take note of my
        people\u2019s situation.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Listen, all the earth!I will bring disaster on my people.It is the
        fruit of their own schemes,because they refuse to listen to me.They have
        rejected my word.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "There\u2019s no use offering me sweet frankincense from Sheba.Keep
        your fragrant calamus imported from distant lands!I will not accept your
        burnt offerings.Your sacrifices have no pleasing aroma for me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: An Invasion from the North'
      title: An Invasion from the North
      number: 21
      content: "Therefore, this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\u201CI
        will put obstacles in my people\u2019s path.Fathers and sons will both fall
        over them.Neighbors and friends will die together.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\u201CLook! A great
        army coming from the north!A great nation is rising against you from far-off
        lands.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "They are armed with bows and spears.They are cruel and show no mercy.They
        sound like a roaring seaas they ride forward on horses.They are coming in
        battle formation,planning to destroy you, beautiful Jerusalem.[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:23 '
        content: Hebrew <b>daughter of Zion.</b>
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'We have heard reports about the enemy,and we wring our hands in fright.Pangs
        of anguish have gripped us,like those of a woman in labor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Don\u2019t go out to the fields!Don\u2019t travel on the roads!The
        enemy\u2019s sword is everywhereand terrorizes us at every turn!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Oh, my people, dress yourselves in burlapand sit among the ashes.Mourn
        and weep bitterly, as for the loss of an only son.For suddenly the destroying
        armies will be upon you!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CJeremiah, I have made you a tester of metals,[[COMMENT(0)]]that
        you may determine the quality of my people.  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:27 '
        content: As in Greek version; Hebrew reads <b>a tester of my people a fortress.</b>
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'They are the worst kind of rebel,full of slander.They are as hard
        as bronze and iron,and they lead others into corruption.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'The bellows fiercely fan the flamesto burn out the corruption.But
        it does not purify them,for the wickedness remains.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "I will label them \u2018Rejected Silver,\u2019for I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        am discarding them.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jeremiah Speaks at the Temple'
      title: Jeremiah Speaks at the Temple
      number: 1
      content: '  The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave another message to Jeremiah.
        He said, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CGo to the entrance of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        Temple, and give this message to the people: \u2018O Judah, listen to this
        message from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>! Listen to it, all of you who
        worship here! "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies,
        the God of Israel, says:\u201C\u2018Even now, if you quit your evil ways,
        I will let you stay in your own land. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "But don\u2019t be fooled by those who promise you safety simply because
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s Temple is here. They chant, \u201CThe
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s Temple is here! The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        Temple is here!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But I will be merciful only if you stop your evil thoughts and deeds
        and start treating each other with justice; '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'only if you stop exploiting foreigners, orphans, and widows; only
        if you stop your murdering; and only if you stop harming yourselves by worshiping
        idols. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then I will let you stay in this land that I gave to your ancestors
        to keep forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201C\u2018Don\u2019t be fooled into thinking that you will never
        suffer because the Temple is here. It\u2019s a lie! "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Do you really think you can steal, murder, commit adultery, lie,
        and burn incense to Baal and all those other new gods of yours, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "and then come here and stand before me in my Temple and chant, \u201CWe
        are safe!\u201D\u2014only to go right back to all those evils again? "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Don\u2019t you yourselves admit that this Temple, which bears my
        name, has become a den of thieves? Surely I see all the evil going on there.
        I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, have spoken!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201C\u2018Go now to the place at Shiloh where I once put the Tabernacle
        that bore my name. See what I did there because of all the wickedness of
        my people, the Israelites. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'While you were doing these wicked things, says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        I spoke to you about it repeatedly, but you would not listen. I called out
        to you, but you refused to answer. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So just as I destroyed Shiloh, I will now destroy this Temple that
        bears my name, this Temple that you trust in for help, this place that I
        gave to you and your ancestors. '
      comments: []
    - name: "15: Judah\u2019s Persistent Idolatry"
      title: "Judah\u2019s Persistent Idolatry"
      number: 15
      content: "And I will send you out of my sight into exile, just as I did your
        relatives, the people of Israel.[[COMMENT(0)]]\u2019  "
      comments:
      - number: '7:15 '
        content: Hebrew <b>of Ephraim, </b>referring to the northern kingdom of Israel.
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CPray no more for these people, Jeremiah. Do not weep or pray
        for them, and don\u2019t beg me to help them, for I will not listen to you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Don\u2019t you see what they are doing throughout the towns of Judah
        and in the streets of Jerusalem? "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'No wonder I am so angry! Watch how the children gather wood and the
        fathers build sacrificial fires. See how the women knead dough and make cakes
        to offer to the Queen of Heaven. And they pour out liquid offerings to their
        other idol gods! '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Am I the one they are hurting?\u201D asks the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        \u201CMost of all, they hurt themselves, to their own shame.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "So this is what the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: \u201CI
        will pour out my terrible fury on this place. Its people, animals, trees,
        and crops will be consumed by the unquenchable fire of my anger.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies,
        the God of Israel, says: \u201CTake your burnt offerings and your other sacrifices
        and eat them yourselves! "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'When I led your ancestors out of Egypt, it was not burnt offerings
        and sacrifices I wanted from them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "This is what I told them: \u2018Obey me, and I will be your God,
        and you will be my people. Do everything as I say, and all will be well!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CBut my people would not listen to me. They kept doing whatever
        they wanted, following the stubborn desires of their evil hearts. They went
        backward instead of forward. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "From the day your ancestors left Egypt until now, I have continued
        to send my servants, the prophets\u2014day in and day out. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "But my people have not listened to me or even tried to hear. They
        have been stubborn and sinful\u2014even worse than their ancestors.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CTell them all this, but do not expect them to listen. Shout
        out your warnings, but do not expect them to respond. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Say to them, \u2018This is the nation whose people will not obey
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> their God and who refuse to be taught. Truth
        has vanished from among them; it is no longer heard on their lips. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: The Valley of Slaughter'
      title: The Valley of Slaughter
      number: 29
      content: "Shave your head in mourning, and weep alone on the mountains. For
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has rejected and forsaken this generation
        that has provoked his fury.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "\u201CThe people of Judah have sinned before my very eyes,\u201D
        says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. \u201CThey have set up their abominable
        idols right in the Temple that bears my name, defiling it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'They have built pagan shrines at Topheth, the garbage dump in the
        valley of Ben-Hinnom, and there they burn their sons and daughters in the
        fire. I have never commanded such a horrible deed; it never even crossed
        my mind to command such a thing! '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "So beware, for the time is coming,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        \u201Cwhen that garbage dump will no longer be called Topheth or the valley
        of Ben-Hinnom, but the Valley of Slaughter. They will bury the bodies in
        Topheth until there is no more room for them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'The bodies of my people will be food for the vultures and wild animals,
        and no one will be left to scare them away. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: I will put an end to the happy singing and laughter in the streets
        of Jerusalem. The joyful voices of bridegrooms and brides will no longer
        be heard in the towns of Judah. The land will lie in complete desolation.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CIn that day,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        \u201Cthe enemy will break open the graves of the kings and officials of
        Judah, and the graves of the priests, prophets, and common people of Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "They will spread out their bones on the ground before the sun, moon,
        and stars\u2014the gods my people have loved, served, and worshiped. Their
        bones will not be gathered up again or buried but will be scattered on the
        ground like manure. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: Deception by False Prophets'
      title: Deception by False Prophets
      number: 3
      content: "And the people of this evil nation who survive will wish to die rather
        than live where I will send them. I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies, have spoken!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CJeremiah, say to the people, \u2018This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        says:\u201C\u2018When people fall down, don\u2019t they get up again?When
        they discover they\u2019re on the wrong road, don\u2019t they turn back?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then why do these people stay on their self-destructive path?Why
        do the people of Jerusalem refuse to turn back?They cling tightly to their
        liesand will not turn around.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "I listen to their conversationsand don\u2019t hear a word of truth.Is
        anyone sorry for doing wrong?Does anyone say, \u201CWhat a terrible thing
        I have done\u201D?No! All are running down the path of sinas swiftly as a
        horse galloping into battle!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Even the stork that flies across the skyknows the time of her migration,as
        do the turtledove, the swallow, and the crane.[[COMMENT(0)]]They all return
        at the proper time each year.But not my people!They do not know the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        laws.  "
      comments:
      - number: '8:7 '
        content: The identification of some of these birds is uncertain.
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201C\u2018How can you say, \u201CWe are wise because we have the
        word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,\u201Dwhen your teachers have twisted
        it by writing lies?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'These wise teachers will fallinto the trap of their own foolishness,for
        they have rejected the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.Are they so
        wise after all?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'I will give their wives to othersand their farms to strangers.From
        the least to the greatest,their lives are ruled by greed.Yes, even my prophets
        and priests are like that.They are all frauds.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "They offer superficial treatmentsfor my people\u2019s mortal wound.They
        give assurances of peacewhen there is no peace.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Are they ashamed of these disgusting actions?Not at all\u2014they
        don\u2019t even know how to blush!Therefore, they will lie among the slaughtered.They
        will be brought down when I punish them,says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "I will surely consume them.There will be no more harvests of figs
        and grapes.Their fruit trees will all die.Whatever I gave them will soon
        be gone.I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, have spoken!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CThen the people will say,\u2018Why should we wait here to die?Come,
        let\u2019s go to the fortified towns and die there.For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        our God has decreed our destructionand has given us a cup of poison to drinkbecause
        we sinned against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "We hoped for peace, but no peace came.We hoped for a time of healing,
        but found only terror.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CThe snorting of the enemies\u2019 warhorses can be heardall
        the way from the land of Dan in the north!The neighing of their stallions
        makes the whole land tremble.They are coming to devour the land and everything
        in it\u2014cities and people alike.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: Jeremiah Weeps for Sinful Judah'
      title: Jeremiah Weeps for Sinful Judah
      number: 17
      content: "I will send these enemy troops among youlike poisonous snakes you
        cannot charm.They will bite you, and you will die.I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        have spoken!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'My grief is beyond healing;my heart is broken.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Listen to the weeping of my people;it can be heard all across the
        land.\u201CHas the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> abandoned Jerusalem?[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201D
        the people ask.\u201CIs her King no longer there?\u201D\u201COh, why have
        they provoked my anger with their carved idolsand their worthless foreign
        gods?\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments:
      - number: '8:19 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Zion?</b>
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CThe harvest is finished,and the summer is gone,\u201D the people
        cry,\u201Cyet we are not saved!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'I hurt with the hurt of my people.I mourn and am overcome with grief.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Is there no medicine in Gilead?Is there no physician there?Why is
        there no healingfor the wounds of my people?
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '    [[COMMENT(0)]]If only my head were a pool of waterand my eyes
        a fountain of tears,I would weep day and nightfor all my people who have
        been slaughtered.  '
      comments:
      - number: '9:1 '
        content: '  Verse 9:1 is numbered 8:23 in Hebrew text.    '
    - name: '2: Judgment for Disobedience'
      title: Judgment for Disobedience
      number: 2
      content: "  [[COMMENT(0)]]Oh, that I could go away and forget my peopleand
        live in a travelers\u2019 shack in the desert.For they are all adulterers\u2014a
        pack of treacherous liars.  "
      comments:
      - number: '9:2 '
        content: '  Verses 9:2-26 are numbered 9:1-25 in Hebrew text.  '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CMy people bend their tongues like bowsto shoot out lies.They
        refuse to stand up for the truth.They only go from bad to worse.They do not
        know me,\u201Dsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CBeware of your neighbor!Don\u2019t even trust your brother!For
        brother takes advantage of brother,and friend slanders friend.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'They all fool and defraud each other;no one tells the truth.With
        practiced tongues they tell lies;they wear themselves out with all their
        sinning.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "They pile lie upon lieand utterly refuse to acknowledge me,\u201Dsays
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Therefore, this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies says:\u201CSee, I will melt them down in a crucibleand test them like
        metal.What else can I do with my people?[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '9:7 '
        content: Hebrew <b>with the daughter of my people? </b>Greek version reads
          <b>with the evil daughter of my people?</b>
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'For their tongues shoot lies like poisoned arrows.They speak friendly
        words to their neighborswhile scheming in their heart to kill them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Should I not punish them for this?\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201CShould
        I not avenge myself against such a nation?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'I will weep for the mountainsand wail for the wilderness pastures.For
        they are desolate and empty of life;the lowing of cattle is heard no more;the
        birds and wild animals have all fled.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CI will make Jerusalem into a heap of ruins,\u201D says the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201CIt will be a place haunted by jackals.The
        towns of Judah will be ghost towns,with no one living in them.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Who is wise enough to understand all this? Who has been instructed
        by the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and can explain it to others? Why has
        the land been so ruined that no one dares to travel through it?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> replies, \u201CThis has happened
        because my people have abandoned my instructions; they have refused to obey
        what I said. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Instead, they have stubbornly followed their own desires and worshiped
        the images of Baal, as their ancestors taught them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "So now, this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies, the God of Israel, says: Look! I will feed them with bitterness and
        give them poison to drink. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Weeping in Jerusalem'
      title: Weeping in Jerusalem
      number: 16
      content: "I will scatter them around the world, in places they and their ancestors
        never heard of, and even there I will chase them with the sword until I have
        destroyed them completely.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies
        says:\u201CConsider all this, and call for the mourners.Send for the women
        who mourn at funerals.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Quick! Begin your weeping!Let the tears flow from your eyes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Hear the people of Jerusalem[[COMMENT(0)]] crying in despair,\u2018We
        are ruined! We are completely humiliated!We must leave our land,because our
        homes have been torn down.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '9:19 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Zion.</b>
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Listen, you women, to the words of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;open
        your ears to what he has to say.Teach your daughters to wail;teach one another
        how to lament.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'For death has crept in through our windowsand has entered our mansions.It
        has killed off the flower of our youth:Children no longer play in the streets,and
        young men no longer gather in the squares.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\u201CBodies will
        be scattered across the fields like clumps of manure,like bundles of grain
        after the harvest.No one will be left to bury them.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\u201CDon\u2019t
        let the wise boast in their wisdom,or the powerful boast in their power,or
        the rich boast in their riches.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'But those who wish to boastshould boast in this alone:that they truly
        know me and understand that I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>who demonstrates
        unfailing loveand who brings justice and righteousness to the earth,and that
        I delight in these things.I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, have spoken!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CA time is coming,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        \u201Cwhen I will punish all those who are circumcised in body but not in
        spirit\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "the Egyptians, Edomites, Ammonites, Moabites, the people who live
        in the desert in remote places,[[COMMENT(0)]] and yes, even the people of
        Judah. And like all these pagan nations, the people of Israel also have uncircumcised
        hearts.\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: '9:26 '
        content: Or <b>in the desert and clip the corners of their hair.</b>
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Idolatry Brings Destruction'
      title: Idolatry Brings Destruction
      number: 1
      content: '  Hear the word that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> speaks to you,
        O Israel! '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\u201CDo not act
        like the other nations,who try to read their future in the stars.Do not be
        afraid of their predictions,even though other nations are terrified by them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Their ways are futile and foolish.They cut down a tree, and a craftsman
        carves an idol.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "They decorate it with gold and silverand then fasten it securely
        with hammer and nailsso it won\u2019t fall over.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Their gods are likehelpless scarecrows in a cucumber field!They cannot
        speak,and they need to be carried because they cannot walk.Do not be afraid
        of such gods,for they can neither harm you nor do you any good.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, there is no one like you!For you are
        great, and your name is full of power.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Who would not fear you, O King of nations?That title belongs to you
        alone!Among all the wise people of the earthand in all the kingdoms of the
        world,there is no one like you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'People who worship idols are stupid and foolish.The things they worship
        are made of wood!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'They bring beaten sheets of silver from Tarshishand gold from Uphaz,and
        they give these materials to skillful craftsmenwho make their idols.Then
        they dress these gods in royal blue and purple robesmade by expert tailors.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'But the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is the only true God.He is the
        living God and the everlasting King!The whole earth trembles at his anger.The
        nations cannot stand up to his wrath.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Say this to those who worship other gods: \u201CYour so-called gods,
        who did not make the heavens and earth, will vanish from the earth and from
        under the heavens.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '10:11 '
        content: The original text of this verse is in Aramaic.
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'But the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> made the earth by his power,and
        he preserves it by his wisdom.With his own understandinghe stretched out
        the heavens.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'When he speaks in the thunder,the heavens roar with rain.He causes
        the clouds to rise over the earth.He sends the lightning with the rainand
        releases the wind from his storehouses.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The whole human race is foolish and has no knowledge!The craftsmen
        are disgraced by the idols they make,for their carefully shaped works are
        a fraud.These idols have no breath or power.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Idols are worthless; they are ridiculous lies!On the day of reckoning
        they will all be destroyed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: The Coming Destruction'
      title: The Coming Destruction
      number: 16
      content: "But the God of Israel[[COMMENT(0)]] is no idol!He is the Creator
        of everything that exists,including Israel, his own special possession.The
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies is his name!  "
      comments:
      - number: '10:16 '
        content: Hebrew <b>the Portion of Jacob. </b>See note on 5:20.
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Pack your bags and prepare to leave;the siege is about to begin.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "For this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\u201CSuddenly,
        I will fling outall you who live in this land.I will pour great troubles
        upon you,and at last you will feel my anger.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'My wound is severe,and my grief is great.My sickness is incurable,but
        I must bear it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'My home is gone,and no one is left to help me rebuild it.My children
        have been taken away,and I will never see them again.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The shepherds of my people have lost their senses.They no longer
        seek wisdom from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.Therefore, they fail completely,and
        their flocks are scattered.  '
      comments: []
    - name: "22: Jeremiah\u2019s Prayer"
      title: "Jeremiah\u2019s Prayer"
      number: 22
      content: 'Listen! Hear the terrifying roar of great armiesas they roll down
        from the north.The towns of Judah will be destroyedand become a haunt for
        jackals.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'I know, <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, that our lives are not our own.We
        are not able to plan our own course.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'So correct me, <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, but please be gentle.Do
        not correct me in anger, for I would die.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Pour out your wrath on the nations that refuse to acknowledge you\u2014on
        the peoples that do not call upon your name.For they have devoured your people
        Israel[[COMMENT(0)]];they have devoured and consumed them,making the land
        a desolate wilderness."
      comments:
      - number: '10:25 '
        content: Hebrew <b>devoured Jacob. </b>See note on 5:20.
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Judah\u2019s Broken Covenant"
      title: "Judah\u2019s Broken Covenant"
      number: 1
      content: '  The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave another message to Jeremiah.
        He said, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CRemind the people of Judah and Jerusalem about the terms of
        my covenant with them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Say to them, \u2018This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        the God of Israel, says: Cursed is anyone who does not obey the terms of
        my covenant! "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "For I said to your ancestors when I brought them out of the iron-smelting
        furnace of Egypt, \u201CIf you obey me and do whatever I command you, then
        you will be my people, and I will be your God.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "I said this so I could keep my promise to your ancestors to give
        you a land flowing with milk and honey\u2014the land you live in today.\u2019\u201DThen
        I replied, \u201CAmen, <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>! May it be so.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said, \u201CBroadcast this message
        in the streets of Jerusalem. Go from town to town throughout the land and
        say, \u2018Remember the ancient covenant, and do everything it requires. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "For I solemnly warned your ancestors when I brought them out of Egypt,
        \u201CObey me!\u201D I have repeated this warning over and over to this day, "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "but your ancestors did not listen or even pay attention. Instead,
        they stubbornly followed their own evil desires. And because they refused
        to obey, I brought upon them all the curses described in this covenant.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Again the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> spoke to me and said, \u201CI
        have discovered a conspiracy against me among the people of Judah and Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'They have returned to the sins of their ancestors. They have refused
        to listen to me and are worshiping other gods. Israel and Judah have both
        broken the covenant I made with their ancestors. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Therefore, this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: I am
        going to bring calamity upon them, and they will not escape. Though they
        beg for mercy, I will not listen to their cries. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then the people of Judah and Jerusalem will pray to their idols and
        burn incense before them. But the idols will not save them when disaster
        strikes! '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Look now, people of Judah; you have as many gods as you have towns.
        You have as many altars of shame\u2014altars for burning incense to your
        god Baal\u2014as there are streets in Jerusalem.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CPray no more for these people, Jeremiah. Do not weep or pray
        for them, for I will not listen to them when they cry out to me in distress.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CWhat right do my beloved people have to come to my Temple,when
        they have done so many immoral things?Can their vows and sacrifices prevent
        their destruction?They actually rejoice in doing evil!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, once called them a thriving olive
        tree,beautiful to see and full of good fruit.But now I have sent the fury
        of their enemiesto burn them with fire,leaving them charred and broken.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: A Plot against Jeremiah'
      title: A Plot against Jeremiah
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CI, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies,
        who planted this olive tree, have ordered it destroyed. For the people of
        Israel and Judah have done evil, arousing my anger by burning incense to
        Baal.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> told me about the plots my enemies
        were making against me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "I was like a lamb being led to the slaughter. I had no idea that
        they were planning to kill me! \u201CLet\u2019s destroy this man and all
        his words,\u201D they said. \u201CLet\u2019s cut him down, so his name will
        be forgotten forever.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies,you make righteous
        judgments,and you examine the deepest thoughts and secrets.Let me see your
        vengeance against them,for I have committed my cause to you.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says about the men of
        Anathoth who wanted me dead. They had said, \u201CWe will kill you if you
        do not stop prophesying in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s name.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "So this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies says about them: \u201CI will punish them! Their young men will die
        in battle, and their boys and girls will starve to death. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Not one of these plotters from Anathoth will survive, for I will
        bring disaster upon them when their time of punishment comes.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Jeremiah Questions the \u2019s Justice"
      title: "Jeremiah Questions the \u2019s Justice"
      number: 1
      content: '<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>    <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, you always
        give me justicewhen I bring a case before you.So let me bring you this complaint:Why
        are the wicked so prosperous?Why are evil people so happy?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'You have planted them,and they have taken root and prospered.Your
        name is on their lips,but you are far from their hearts.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'But as for me, <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, you know my heart.You
        see me and test my thoughts.Drag these people away like sheep to be butchered!Set
        them aside to be slaughtered!  '
      comments: []
    - name: "4: The \u2019s Reply to Jeremiah"
      title: "The \u2019s Reply to Jeremiah"
      number: 4
      content: "How long must this land mourn?Even the grass in the fields has withered.The
        wild animals and birds have disappearedbecause of the evil in the land.For
        the people have said,\u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord </smallcaps>doesn\u2019t see
        what\u2019s ahead for us!\u201D<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CIf racing against mere men makes you tired,how will you race
        against horses?If you stumble and fall on open ground,what will you do in
        the thickets near the Jordan?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Even your brothers, members of your own family,have turned against
        you.They plot and raise complaints against you.Do not trust them,no matter
        how pleasantly they speak.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CI have abandoned my people, my special possession.I have surrendered
        my dearest ones to their enemies.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'My chosen people have roared at me like a lion of the forest,so I
        have treated them with contempt.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'My chosen people act like speckled vultures,[[COMMENT(0)]]but they
        themselves are surrounded by vultures.Bring on the wild animals to pick their
        corpses clean!  '
      comments:
      - number: '12:9 '
        content: Or <b>speckled hyenas.</b>
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CMany rulers have ravaged my vineyard,trampling down the vinesand
        turning all its beauty into a barren wilderness.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'They have made it an empty wasteland;I hear its mournful cry.The
        whole land is desolate,and no one even cares.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'On all the bare hilltops,destroying armies can be seen.The sword
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> devours peoplefrom one end of the nation
        to the other.No one will escape!  '
      comments: []
    - name: "13: A Message for Israel\u2019s Neighbors"
      title: "A Message for Israel\u2019s Neighbors"
      number: 13
      content: "My people have planted wheatbut are harvesting thorns.They have worn
        themselves out,but it has done them no good.They will harvest a crop of shamebecause
        of the fierce anger of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Now this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: \u201CI will
        uproot from their land all the evil nations reaching out for the possession
        I gave my people Israel. And I will uproot Judah from among them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'But afterward I will return and have compassion on all of them. I
        will bring them home to their own lands again, each nation to its own possession. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And if these nations truly learn the ways of my people, and if they
        learn to swear by my name, saying, \u2018As surely as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        lives\u2019 (just as they taught my people to swear by the name of Baal),
        then they will be given a place among my people. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "But any nation who refuses to obey me will be uprooted and destroyed.
        I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, have spoken!\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Jeremiah\u2019s Linen Loincloth"
      title: "Jeremiah\u2019s Linen Loincloth"
      number: 1
      content: "  This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me: \u201CGo
        and buy a linen loincloth and put it on, but do not wash it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So I bought the loincloth as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> directed
        me, and I put it on.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave me another message: '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CTake the linen loincloth you are wearing, and go to the Euphrates
        River.[[COMMENT(0)]] Hide it there in a hole in the rocks.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '13:4 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Perath; </b>also in 13:5, 6, 7.
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So I went and hid it by the Euphrates as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        had instructed me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "A long time afterward the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me,
        \u201CGo back to the Euphrates and get the loincloth I told you to hide there.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So I went to the Euphrates and dug it out of the hole where I had
        hidden it. But now it was rotting and falling apart. The loincloth was good
        for nothing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then I received this message from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: This shows
        how I will rot away the pride of Judah and Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "These wicked people refuse to listen to me. They stubbornly follow
        their own desires and worship other gods. Therefore, they will become like
        this loincloth\u2014good for nothing! "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "As a loincloth clings to a man\u2019s waist, so I created Judah and
        Israel to cling to me, says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. They were to
        be my people, my pride, my glory\u2014an honor to my name. But they would
        not listen to me.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CSo tell them, \u2018This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        the God of Israel, says: May all your jars be filled with wine.\u2019 And
        they will reply, \u2018Of course! Jars are made to be filled with wine!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CThen tell them, \u2018No, this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        means: I will fill everyone in this land with drunkenness\u2014from the king
        sitting on David\u2019s throne to the priests and the prophets, right down
        to the common people of Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: A Warning against Pride'
      title: A Warning against Pride
      number: 14
      content: "I will smash them against each other, even parents against children,
        says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. I will not let my pity or mercy or
        compassion keep me from destroying them.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Listen and pay attention!Do not be arrogant, for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has spoken.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Give glory to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your Godbefore it is
        too late.Acknowledge him before he brings darkness upon you,causing you to
        stumble and fall on the darkening mountains.For then, when you look for light,you
        will find only terrible darkness and gloom.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And if you still refuse to listen,I will weep alone because of your
        pride.My eyes will overflow with tears,because the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        flock will be led away into exile.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Say to the king and his mother,\u201CCome down from your thronesand
        sit in the dust,for your glorious crownswill soon be snatched from your heads.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The towns of the Negev will close their gates,and no one will be
        able to open them.The people of Judah will be taken away as captives.All
        will be carried into exile.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Open up your eyes and seethe armies marching down from the north!Where
        is your flock\u2014your beautiful flock\u2014that he gave you to care for?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'What will you say when the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> takes the
        allies you have cultivatedand appoints them as your rulers?Pangs of anguish
        will grip you,like those of a woman in labor!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "You may ask yourself,\u201CWhy is all this happening to me?\u201DIt
        is because of your many sins!That is why you have been strippedand raped
        by invading armies.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Can an Ethiopian[[COMMENT(0)]] change the color of his skin?Can a
        leopard take away its spots?Neither can you start doing good,for you have
        always done evil.  '
      comments:
      - number: '13:23 '
        content: Hebrew <b>a Cushite.</b>
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CI will scatter you like chaffthat is blown away by the desert
        winds.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "This is your allotment,the portion I have assigned to you,\u201Dsays
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,\u201Cfor you have forgotten me,putting your
        trust in false gods.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'I myself will strip youand expose you to shame.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "I have seen your adultery and lust,and your disgusting idol worship
        out in the fields and on the hills.What sorrow awaits you, Jerusalem!How
        long before you are pure?\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Judah\u2019s Terrible Drought"
      title: "Judah\u2019s Terrible Drought"
      number: 1
      content: '  This message came to Jeremiah from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        explaining why he was holding back the rain:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CJudah wilts;commerce at the city gates grinds to a halt.All
        the people sit on the ground in mourning,and a great cry rises from Jerusalem.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The nobles send servants to get water,but all the wells are dry.The
        servants return with empty pitchers,confused and desperate,covering their
        heads in grief.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The ground is parchedand cracked for lack of rain.The farmers are
        deeply troubled;they, too, cover their heads.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Even the doe abandons her newborn fawnbecause there is no grass in
        the field.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "The wild donkeys stand on the bare hillspanting like thirsty jackals.They
        strain their eyes looking for grass,but there is none to be found.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "The people say, \u201COur wickedness has caught up with us, <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,but
        help us for the sake of your own reputation.We have turned away from youand
        sinned against you again and again.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'O Hope of Israel, our Savior in times of trouble,why are you like
        a stranger to us?Why are you like a traveler passing through the land,stopping
        only for the night?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Are you also confused?Is our champion helpless to save us?You are
        right here among us, <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.We are known as your people.Please
        don\u2019t abandon us now!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: The  Forbids Jeremiah to Intercede'
      title: The  Forbids Jeremiah to Intercede
      number: 10
      content: "So this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says to his people:\u201CYou
        love to wander far from meand do not restrain yourselves.Therefore, I will
        no longer accept you as my people.Now I will remember all your wickednessand
        will punish you for your sins.\u201D<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me, \u201CDo not pray
        for these people anymore. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "When they fast, I will pay no attention. When they present their
        burnt offerings and grain offerings to me, I will not accept them. Instead,
        I will devour them with war, famine, and disease.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then I said, \u201CO Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, their
        prophets are telling them, \u2018All is well\u2014no war or famine will come.
        The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will surely send you peace.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said, \u201CThese prophets are
        telling lies in my name. I did not send them or tell them to speak. I did
        not give them any messages. They prophesy of visions and revelations they
        have never seen or heard. They speak foolishness made up in their own lying
        hearts. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Therefore, this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: I will
        punish these lying prophets, for they have spoken in my name even though
        I never sent them. They say that no war or famine will come, but they themselves
        will die by war and famine! '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "As for the people to whom they prophesy\u2014their bodies will be
        thrown out into the streets of Jerusalem, victims of famine and war. There
        will be no one left to bury them. Husbands, wives, sons, and daughters\u2014all
        will be gone. For I will pour out their own wickedness on them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Now, Jeremiah, say this to them:\u201CNight and day my eyes overflow
        with tears.I cannot stop weeping,for my virgin daughter\u2014my precious
        people\u2014has been struck downand lies mortally wounded.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: A Prayer for Healing'
      title: A Prayer for Healing
      number: 18
      content: "If I go out into the fields,I see the bodies of people slaughtered
        by the enemy.If I walk the city streets,I see people who have died of starvation.The
        prophets and priests continue with their work,but they don\u2019t know what
        they\u2019re doing.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '  <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, have you completely rejected Judah?Do
        you really hate Jerusalem?[[COMMENT(0)]]Why have you wounded us past all
        hope of healing?We hoped for peace, but no peace came.We hoped for a time
        of healing, but found only terror.  '
      comments:
      - number: '14:19 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Zion?</b>
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '  <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, we confess our wickednessand that
        of our ancestors, too.We all have sinned against you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'For the sake of your reputation, <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, do
        not abandon us.Do not disgrace your own glorious throne.Please remember us,and
        do not break your covenant with us.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Can any of the worthless foreign gods send us rain?Does it fall from
        the sky by itself?No, you are the one, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our
        God!Only you can do such things.So we will wait for you to help us.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Judah\u2019s Inevitable Doom"
      title: "Judah\u2019s Inevitable Doom"
      number: 1
      content: "  Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me, \u201CEven if
        Moses and Samuel stood before me pleading for these people, I wouldn\u2019t
        help them. Away with them! Get them out of my sight! "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And if they say to you, \u2018But where can we go?\u2019 tell them,
        \u2018This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\u201C\u2018Those
        who are destined for death, to death;those who are destined for war, to war;those
        who are destined for famine, to famine;those who are destined for captivity,
        to captivity.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CI will send four kinds of destroyers against them,\u201D says
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. \u201CI will send the sword to kill, the
        dogs to drag away, the vultures to devour, and the wild animals to finish
        up what is left. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Because of the wicked things Manasseh son of Hezekiah, king of Judah,
        did in Jerusalem, I will make my people an object of horror to all the kingdoms
        of the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CWho will feel sorry for you, Jerusalem?Who will weep for you?Who
        will even bother to ask how you are?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "You have abandoned meand turned your back on me,\u201Dsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201CTherefore,
        I will raise my fist to destroy you.I am tired of always giving you another
        chance.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'I will winnow you like grain at the gates of your citiesand take
        away the children you hold dear.I will destroy my own people,because they
        refuse to change their evil ways.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'There will be more widowsthan the grains of sand on the seashore.At
        noontime I will bring a destroyeragainst the mothers of young men.I will
        cause anguish and terrorto come upon them suddenly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: "9: Jeremiah\u2019s Complaint"
      title: "Jeremiah\u2019s Complaint"
      number: 9
      content: "The mother of seven grows faint and gasps for breath;her sun has
        gone down while it is still day.She sits childless now,disgraced and humiliated.And
        I will hand over those who are leftto be killed by the enemy.I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        have spoken!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then I said,\u201CWhat sorrow is mine, my mother.Oh, that I had died
        at birth!I am hated everywhere I go.I am neither a lender who threatens to
        foreclosenor a borrower who refuses to pay\u2014yet they all curse me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> replied,\u201CI will take care of
        you, Jeremiah.Your enemies will ask you to plead on their behalfin times
        of trouble and distress.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Can a man break a bar of iron from the north,or a bar of bronze?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'At no cost to them,I will hand over your wealth and treasuresas plunder
        to your enemies,for sin runs rampant in your land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "I will tell your enemies to take youas captives to a foreign land.For
        my anger blazes like a firethat will burn forever.[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '15:14 '
        content: As in some Hebrew manuscripts (see also 17:4); most Hebrew manuscripts
          read <b>will burn against you.</b>
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then I said,\u201C<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, you know what\u2019s
        happening to me.Please step in and help me. Punish my persecutors!Please
        give me time; don\u2019t let me die young.It\u2019s for your sake that I
        am suffering.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "When I discovered your words, I devoured them.They are my joy and
        my heart\u2019s delight,for I bear your name,O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        God of Heaven\u2019s Armies.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'I never joined the people in their merry feasts.I sat alone because
        your hand was on me.I was filled with indignation at their sins.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Why then does my suffering continue?Why is my wound so incurable?Your
        help seems as uncertain as a seasonal brook,like a spring that has gone dry.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "This is how the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> responds:\u201CIf you
        return to me, I will restore youso you can continue to serve me.If you speak
        good words rather than worthless ones,you will be my spokesman.You must influence
        them;do not let them influence you!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'They will fight against you like an attacking army,but I will make
        you as secure as a fortified wall of bronze.They will not conquer you,for
        I am with you to protect and rescue you.I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        have spoken!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Yes, I will certainly keep you safe from these wicked men.I will
        rescue you from their cruel hands.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jeremiah Forbidden to Marry'
      title: Jeremiah Forbidden to Marry
      number: 1
      content: '  The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave me another message. He said, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CDo not get married or have children in this place. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says about the children
        born here in this city and about their mothers and fathers: '
      comments: []
    - name: "4: Judah\u2019s Coming Punishment"
      title: "Judah\u2019s Coming Punishment"
      number: 4
      content: "They will die from terrible diseases. No one will mourn for them
        or bury them, and they will lie scattered on the ground like manure. They
        will die from war and famine, and their bodies will be food for the vultures
        and wild animals.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: \u201CDo not go
        to funerals to mourn and show sympathy for these people, for I have removed
        my protection and peace from them. I have taken away my unfailing love and
        my mercy. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Both the great and the lowly will die in this land. No one will bury
        them or mourn for them. Their friends will not cut themselves in sorrow or
        shave their heads in sadness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "No one will offer a meal to comfort those who mourn for the dead\u2014not
        even at the death of a mother or father. No one will send a cup of wine to
        console them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CAnd do not go to their feasts and parties. Do not eat and drink
        with them at all. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "For this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies, the God of Israel, says: In your own lifetime, before your very eyes,
        I will put an end to the happy singing and laughter in this land. The joyful
        voices of bridegrooms and brides will no longer be heard.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CWhen you tell the people all these things, they will ask, \u2018Why
        has the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> decreed such terrible things against
        us? What have we done to deserve such treatment? What is our sin against
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CThen you will give them the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        reply: \u2018It is because your ancestors were unfaithful to me. They worshiped
        other gods and served them. They abandoned me and did not obey my word. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And you are even worse than your ancestors! You stubbornly follow
        your own evil desires and refuse to listen to me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Hope despite the Disaster'
      title: Hope despite the Disaster
      number: 13
      content: "So I will throw you out of this land and send you into a foreign
        land where you and your ancestors have never been. There you can worship
        idols day and night\u2014and I will grant you no favors!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CBut the time is coming,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        \u201Cwhen people who are taking an oath will no longer say, \u2018As surely
        as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> lives, who rescued the people of Israel
        from the land of Egypt.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Instead, they will say, \u2018As surely as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        lives, who brought the people of Israel back to their own land from the land
        of the north and from all the countries to which he had exiled them.\u2019
        For I will bring them back to this land that I gave their ancestors.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CBut now I am sending for many fishermen who will catch them,\u201D
        says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. \u201CI am sending for hunters who
        will hunt them down in the mountains, hills, and caves. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'I am watching them closely, and I see every sin. They cannot hope
        to hide from me. '
      comments: []
    - name: "18: Jeremiah\u2019s Prayer of Confidence"
      title: "Jeremiah\u2019s Prayer of Confidence"
      number: 18
      content: "I will double their punishment for all their sins, because they have
        defiled my land with lifeless images of their detestable gods and have filled
        my territory with their evil deeds.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "  <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, you are my strength and fortress,my
        refuge in the day of trouble!Nations from around the worldwill come to you
        and say,\u201COur ancestors left us a foolish heritage,for they worshiped
        worthless idols.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Can people make their own gods?These are not real gods at all!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says,\u201CNow I will show them my
        power;now I will show them my might.At last they will know and understandthat
        I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Judah\u2019s Sin and Punishment"
      title: "Judah\u2019s Sin and Punishment"
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CThe sin of Judahis inscribed with an iron chisel\u2014engraved
        with a diamond point on their stony heartsand on the corners of their altars.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Even their children go to worshipat their pagan altars and Asherah
        poles,beneath every green treeand on every high hill.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "So I will hand over my holy mountain\u2014along with all your wealth
        and treasuresand your pagan shrines\u2014as plunder to your enemies,for sin
        runs rampant in your land.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: Wisdom from the '
      title: 'Wisdom from the '
      number: 4
      content: "The wonderful possession I have reserved for youwill slip from your
        hands.I will tell your enemies to take youas captives to a foreign land.For
        my anger blazes like a firethat will burn forever.\u201D<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\u201CCursed are
        those who put their trust in mere humans,who rely on human strengthand turn
        their hearts away from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'They are like stunted shrubs in the desert,with no hope for the future.They
        will live in the barren wilderness,in an uninhabited salty land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CBut blessed are those who trust in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>and
        have made the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> their hope and confidence.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'They are like trees planted along a riverbank,with roots that reach
        deep into the water.Such trees are not bothered by the heator worried by
        long months of drought.Their leaves stay green,and they never stop producing
        fruit.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CThe human heart is the most deceitful of all things,and desperately
        wicked.Who really knows how bad it is?  "
      comments: []
    - name: "10: Jeremiah\u2019s Trust in the "
      title: "Jeremiah\u2019s Trust in the "
      number: 10
      content: "But I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, search all heartsand examine
        secret motives.I give all people their due rewards,according to what their
        actions deserve.\u201D<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Like a partridge that hatches eggs she has not laid,so are those
        who get their wealth by unjust means.At midlife they will lose their riches;in
        the end, they will become poor old fools.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "But we worship at your throne\u2014eternal, high, and glorious!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the hope of Israel,all who turn away
        from you will be disgraced.They will be buried in the dust of the earth,for
        they have abandoned the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the fountain of living
        water.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, if you heal me, I will be truly healed;if
        you save me, I will be truly saved.My praises are for you alone!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "People scoff at me and say,\u201CWhat is this \u2018message from
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019 you talk about?Why don\u2019t your
        predictions come true?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "  <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, I have not abandoned my jobas a shepherd
        for your people.I have not urged you to send disaster.You have heard everything
        I\u2019ve said.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "  <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, don\u2019t terrorize me!You alone
        are my hope in the day of disaster.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: Observing the Sabbath'
      title: Observing the Sabbath
      number: 18
      content: "Bring shame and dismay on all who persecute me,but don\u2019t let
        me experience shame and dismay.Bring a day of terror on them.Yes, bring double
        destruction upon them!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me: \u201CGo
        and stand in the gates of Jerusalem, first in the gate where the king goes
        in and out, and then in each of the other gates. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Say to all the people, \u2018Listen to this message from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        you kings of Judah and all you people of Judah and everyone living in Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: Listen to my warning!
        Stop carrying on your trade at Jerusalem\u2019s gates on the Sabbath day. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Do not do your work on the Sabbath, but make it a holy day. I gave
        this command to your ancestors, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'but they did not listen or obey. They stubbornly refused to pay attention
        or accept my discipline.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201C\u2018But if you obey me, says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        and do not carry on your trade at the gates or work on the Sabbath day, and
        if you keep it holy, "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'then kings and their officials will go in and out of these gates
        forever. There will always be a descendant of David sitting on the throne
        here in Jerusalem. Kings and their officials will always ride in and out
        among the people of Judah in chariots and on horses, and this city will remain
        forever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "And from all around Jerusalem, from the towns of Judah and Benjamin,
        from the western foothills[[COMMENT(0)]] and the hill country and the Negev,
        the people will come with their burnt offerings and sacrifices. They will
        bring their grain offerings, frankincense, and thanksgiving offerings to
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s Temple.  "
      comments:
      - number: '17:26 '
        content: Hebrew <b>the Shephelah.</b>
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201C\u2018But if you do not listen to me and refuse to keep the
        Sabbath holy, and if on the Sabbath day you bring loads of merchandise through
        the gates of Jerusalem just as on other days, then I will set fire to these
        gates. The fire will spread to the palaces, and no one will be able to put
        out the roaring flames.\u2019\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Potter and the Clay'
      title: The Potter and the Clay
      number: 1
      content: '  The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave another message to Jeremiah.
        He said, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CGo down to the potter\u2019s shop, and I will speak to you
        there.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So I did as he told me and found the potter working at his wheel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But the jar he was making did not turn out as he had hoped, so he
        crushed it into a lump of clay again and started over.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave me this message: '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CO Israel, can I not do to you as this potter has done to his
        clay? As the clay is in the potter\u2019s hand, so are you in my hand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'If I announce that a certain nation or kingdom is to be uprooted,
        torn down, and destroyed, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'but then that nation renounces its evil ways, I will not destroy
        it as I had planned. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And if I announce that I will plant and build up a certain nation
        or kingdom, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'but then that nation turns to evil and refuses to obey me, I will
        not bless it as I said I would.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CTherefore, Jeremiah, go and warn all Judah and Jerusalem. Say
        to them, \u2018This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: I am planning
        disaster for you instead of good. So turn from your evil ways, each of you,
        and do what is right.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "But the people replied, \u201CDon\u2019t waste your breath. We will
        continue to live as we want to, stubbornly following our own evil desires.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "So this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\u201CHas anyone
        ever heard of such a thing,even among the pagan nations?My virgin daughter
        Israelhas done something terrible!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Does the snow ever disappear from the mountaintops of Lebanon?Do
        the cold streams flowing from those distant mountains ever run dry?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'But my people are not so reliable, for they have deserted me;they
        burn incense to worthless idols.They have stumbled off the ancient highwaysand
        walk in muddy paths.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Therefore, their land will become desolate,a monument to their stupidity.All
        who pass by will be astonishedand will shake their heads in amazement.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: A Plot against Jeremiah'
      title: A Plot against Jeremiah
      number: 17
      content: "I will scatter my people before their enemiesas the east wind scatters
        dust.And in all their trouble I will turn my back on themand refuse to notice
        their distress.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then the people said, \u201CCome on, let\u2019s plot a way to stop
        Jeremiah. We have plenty of priests and wise men and prophets. We don\u2019t
        need him to teach the word and give us advice and prophecies. Let\u2019s
        spread rumors about him and ignore what he says.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '  <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, hear me and help me!Listen to what
        my enemies are saying.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Should they repay evil for good?They have dug a pit to kill me,though
        I pleaded for themand tried to protect them from your anger.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'So let their children starve!Let them die by the sword!Let their
        wives become childless widows.Let their old men die in a plague,and let their
        young men be killed in battle!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Let screaming be heard from their homesas warriors come suddenly
        upon them.For they have dug a pit for meand have hidden traps along my path.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "  <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, you know all about their murderous
        plots against me.Don\u2019t forgive their crimes and blot out their sins.Let
        them die before you.Deal with them in your anger."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Jeremiah\u2019s Shattered Jar"
      title: "Jeremiah\u2019s Shattered Jar"
      number: 1
      content: "  This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me: \u201CGo
        and buy a clay jar. Then ask some of the leaders of the people and of the
        priests to follow you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Go out through the Gate of Broken Pots to the garbage dump in the
        valley of Ben-Hinnom, and give them this message. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Say to them, \u2018Listen to this message from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        you kings of Judah and citizens of Jerusalem! This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies, the God of Israel, says: I will bring a terrible
        disaster on this place, and the ears of those who hear about it will ring!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201C\u2018For Israel has forsaken me and turned this valley into
        a place of wickedness. The people burn incense to foreign gods\u2014idols
        never before acknowledged by this generation, by their ancestors, or by the
        kings of Judah. And they have filled this place with the blood of innocent
        children. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'They have built pagan shrines to Baal, and there they burn their
        sons as sacrifices to Baal. I have never commanded such a horrible deed;
        it never even crossed my mind to command such a thing! '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So beware, for the time is coming, says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        when this garbage dump will no longer be called Topheth or the valley of
        Ben-Hinnom, but the Valley of Slaughter.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201C\u2018For I will upset the careful plans of Judah and Jerusalem.
        I will allow the people to be slaughtered by invading armies, and I will
        leave their dead bodies as food for the vultures and wild animals. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'I will reduce Jerusalem to ruins, making it a monument to their stupidity.
        All who pass by will be astonished and will gasp at the destruction they
        see there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "I will see to it that your enemies lay siege to the city until all
        the food is gone. Then those trapped inside will eat their own sons and daughters
        and friends. They will be driven to utter despair.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CAs these men watch you, Jeremiah, smash the jar you brought. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then say to them, \u2018This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies says: As this jar lies shattered, so I will shatter
        the people of Judah and Jerusalem beyond all hope of repair. They will bury
        the bodies here in Topheth, the garbage dump, until there is no more room
        for them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'This is what I will do to this place and its people, says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        I will cause this city to become defiled like Topheth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Yes, all the houses in Jerusalem, including the palace of Judah\u2019s
        kings, will become like Topheth\u2014all the houses where you burned incense
        on the rooftops to your star gods, and where liquid offerings were poured
        out to your idols.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then Jeremiah returned from Topheth, the garbage dump where he had
        delivered this message, and he stopped in front of the Temple of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        He said to the people there, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies, the God of Israel, says: \u2018I will bring disaster upon this city
        and its surrounding towns as I promised, because you have stubbornly refused
        to listen to me.\u2019\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jeremiah and Pashhur'
      title: Jeremiah and Pashhur
      number: 1
      content: '  Now Pashhur son of Immer, the priest in charge of the Temple of
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, heard what Jeremiah was prophesying. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "So he arrested Jeremiah the prophet and had him whipped and put in
        stocks at the Benjamin Gate of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s Temple.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "The next day, when Pashhur finally released him, Jeremiah said, \u201CPashhur,
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has changed your name. From now on you are
        to be called \u2018The Man Who Lives in Terror.\u2019[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '20:3 '
        content: "Hebrew <b>Magor-missabib, </b>which means \u201Csurrounded by terror\u201D;
          also in 20:10."
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "For this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: \u2018I will
        send terror upon you and all your friends, and you will watch as they are
        slaughtered by the swords of the enemy. I will hand the people of Judah over
        to the king of Babylon. He will take them captive to Babylon or run them
        through with the sword. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And I will let your enemies plunder Jerusalem. All the famed treasures
        of the city\u2014the precious jewels and gold and silver of your kings\u2014will
        be carried off to Babylon. "
      comments: []
    - name: "6: Jeremiah\u2019s Complaint"
      title: "Jeremiah\u2019s Complaint"
      number: 6
      content: "As for you, Pashhur, you and all your household will go as captives
        to Babylon. There you will die and be buried, you and all your friends to
        whom you prophesied that everything would be all right.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, you misled me,and I allowed myself
        to be misled.You are stronger than I am,and you overpowered me.Now I am mocked
        every day;everyone laughs at me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "When I speak, the words burst out.\u201CViolence and destruction!\u201D
        I shout.So these messages from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>have made me
        a household joke.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "But if I say I\u2019ll never mention the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>or
        speak in his name,his word burns in my heart like a fire.It\u2019s like a
        fire in my bones!I am worn out trying to hold it in!I can\u2019t do it!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "I have heard the many rumors about me.They call me \u201CThe Man
        Who Lives in Terror.\u201DThey threaten, \u201CIf you say anything, we will
        report it.\u201DEven my old friends are watching me,waiting for a fatal slip.\u201CHe
        will trap himself,\u201D they say,\u201Cand then we will get our revenge
        on him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'But the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> stands beside me like a great
        warrior.Before him my persecutors will stumble.They cannot defeat me.They
        will fail and be thoroughly humiliated.Their dishonor will never be forgotten.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies,you test those
        who are righteous,and you examine the deepest thoughts and secrets.Let me
        see your vengeance against them,for I have committed my cause to you.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Sing to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>!Praise the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>!For
        though I was poor and needy,he rescued me from my oppressors.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Yet I curse the day I was born!May no one celebrate the day of my
        birth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "I curse the messenger who told my father,\u201CGood news\u2014you
        have a son!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Let him be destroyed like the cities of oldthat the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        overthrew without mercy.Terrify him all day long with battle shouts,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "because he did not kill me at birth.Oh, that I had died in my mother\u2019s
        womb,that her body had been my grave!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Why was I ever born?My entire life has been filledwith trouble, sorrow,
        and shame.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: No Deliverance from Babylon'
      title: No Deliverance from Babylon
      number: 1
      content: '  The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> spoke through Jeremiah when King
        Zedekiah sent Pashhur son of Malkijah and Zephaniah son of Maaseiah, the
        priest, to speak with him. They begged Jeremiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CPlease speak to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> for us and
        ask him to help us. King Nebuchadnezzar[[COMMENT(0)]] of Babylon is attacking
        Judah. Perhaps the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will be gracious and do a
        mighty miracle as he has done in the past. Perhaps he will force Nebuchadnezzar
        to withdraw his armies.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '21:2 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Nebuchadrezzar, </b>a variant spelling of Nebuchadnezzar;
          also in 21:7.
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Jeremiah replied, \u201CGo back to King Zedekiah and tell him, "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u2018This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of Israel,
        says: I will make your weapons useless against the king of Babylon and the
        Babylonians[[COMMENT(0)]] who are outside your walls attacking you. In fact,
        I will bring your enemies right into the heart of this city. "
      comments:
      - number: '21:4 '
        content: Or <b>Chaldeans; </b>also in 21:9.
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'I myself will fight against you with a strong hand and a powerful
        arm, for I am very angry. You have made me furious! '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'I will send a terrible plague upon this city, and both people and
        animals will die. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And after all that, says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, I will
        hand over King Zedekiah, his staff, and everyone else in the city who survives
        the disease, war, and famine. I will hand them over to King Nebuchadnezzar
        of Babylon and to their other enemies. He will slaughter them and show them
        no mercy, pity, or compassion.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CTell all the people, \u2018This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        says: Take your choice of life or death! "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Everyone who stays in Jerusalem will die from war, famine, or disease,
        but those who go out and surrender to the Babylonians will live. Their reward
        will be life! '
      comments: []
    - name: "10: Judgment on Judah\u2019s Kings"
      title: "Judgment on Judah\u2019s Kings"
      number: 10
      content: "For I have decided to bring disaster and not good upon this city,
        says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. It will be handed over to the king
        of Babylon, and he will reduce it to ashes.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CSay to the royal family of Judah, \u2018Listen to this message
        from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>! "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says to the dynasty
        of David:\u201C\u2018Give justice each morning to the people you judge!Help
        those who have been robbed;rescue them from their oppressors.Otherwise, my
        anger will burn like an unquenchable firebecause of all your sins.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "I will personally fight against the people in Jerusalem,that mighty
        fortress\u2014the people who boast, \u201CNo one can touch us here.No one
        can break in here.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And I myself will punish you for your sinfulness,says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.I
        will light a fire in your foreststhat will burn up everything around you.\u2019\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: A Message for Judah\u2019s Kings"
      title: "A Message for Judah\u2019s Kings"
      number: 1
      content: "  This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me: \u201CGo
        over and speak directly to the king of Judah. Say to him, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u2018Listen to this message from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        you king of Judah, sitting on David\u2019s throne. Let your attendants and
        your people listen, too. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: Be fair-minded
        and just. Do what is right! Help those who have been robbed; rescue them
        from their oppressors. Quit your evil deeds! Do not mistreat foreigners,
        orphans, and widows. Stop murdering the innocent! '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'If you obey me, there will always be a descendant of David sitting
        on the throne here in Jerusalem. The king will ride through the palace gates
        in chariots and on horses, with his parade of attendants and subjects. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: A Message about the Palace'
      title: A Message about the Palace
      number: 5
      content: "But if you refuse to pay attention to this warning, I swear by my
        own name, says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, that this palace will become
        a pile of rubble.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Now this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says concerning
        Judah\u2019s royal palace:\u201CI love you as much as fruitful Gileadand
        the green forests of Lebanon.But I will turn you into a desert,with no one
        living within your walls.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'I will call for wreckers,who will bring out their tools to dismantle
        you.They will tear out all your fine cedar beamsand throw them on the fire.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CPeople from many nations will pass by the ruins of this city
        and say to one another, \u2018Why did the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> destroy
        such a great city?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: A Message about Jehoahaz'
      title: A Message about Jehoahaz
      number: 9
      content: "And the answer will be, \u2018Because they violated their covenant
        with the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> their God by worshiping other gods.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Do not weep for the dead king or mourn his loss.Instead, weep for
        the captive king being led away!For he will never return to see his native
        land again.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "For this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says about Jehoahaz,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        who succeeded his father, King Josiah, and was taken away as a captive: \u201CHe
        will never return. "
      comments:
      - number: '22:11 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Shallum, </b>another name for Jehoahaz.
    - name: '12: A Message about Jehoiakim'
      title: A Message about Jehoiakim
      number: 12
      content: "He will die in a distant land and will never again see his own country.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says, \u201CWhat sorrow awaits
        Jehoiakim,[[COMMENT(0)]]who builds his palace with forced labor.[[COMMENT(1)]]He
        builds injustice into its walls,for he makes his neighbors work for nothing.He
        does not pay them for their labor.  "
      comments:
      - number: '22:13a '
        content: The brother and successor of the exiled Jehoahaz. See 22:18.
      - number: '22:13b '
        content: Hebrew <b>by unrighteousness.</b>
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "He says, \u2018I will build a magnificent palacewith huge rooms and
        many windows.I will panel it throughout with fragrant cedarand paint it a
        lovely red.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'But a beautiful cedar palace does not make a great king!Your father,
        Josiah, also had plenty to eat and drink.But he was just and right in all
        his dealings.That is why God blessed him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "He gave justice and help to the poor and needy,and everything went
        well for him.Isn\u2019t that what it means to know me?\u201Dsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CBut you! You have eyes only for greed and dishonesty!You murder
        the innocent,oppress the poor, and reign ruthlessly.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Therefore, this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says about
        Jehoiakim, son of King Josiah:\u201CThe people will not mourn for him, crying
        to one another,\u2018Alas, my brother! Alas, my sister!\u2019His subjects
        will not mourn for him, crying,\u2018Alas, our master is dead! Alas, his
        splendor is gone!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "He will be buried like a dead donkey\u2014dragged out of Jerusalem
        and dumped outside the gates!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Weep for your allies in Lebanon.Shout for them in Bashan.Search for
        them in the regions east of the river.[[COMMENT(0)]]See, they are all destroyed.Not
        one is left to help you.  '
      comments:
      - number: '22:20 '
        content: Or <b>in Abarim.</b>
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "I warned you when you were prosperous,but you replied, \u2018Don\u2019t
        bother me.\u2019You have been that way since childhood\u2014you simply will
        not obey me!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And now the wind will blow away your allies.All your friends will
        be taken away as captives.Surely then you will see your wickedness and be
        ashamed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: A Message for Jehoiachin'
      title: A Message for Jehoiachin
      number: 23
      content: "It may be nice to live in a beautiful palacepaneled with wood from
        the cedars of Lebanon,but soon you will groan with pangs of anguish\u2014anguish
        like that of a woman in labor.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CAs surely as I live,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        \u201CI will abandon you, Jehoiachin[[COMMENT(0)]] son of Jehoiakim, king
        of Judah. Even if you were the signet ring on my right hand, I would pull
        you off. "
      comments:
      - number: '22:24 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Coniah, </b>a variant spelling of Jehoiachin; also in
          22:28.
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "I will hand you over to those who seek to kill you, those you so
        desperately fear\u2014to King Nebuchadnezzar[[COMMENT(0)]] of Babylon and
        the mighty Babylonian[[COMMENT(1)]] army. "
      comments:
      - number: '22:25a '
        content: Hebrew <b>Nebuchadrezzar, </b>a variant spelling of Nebuchadnezzar.
      - number: '22:25b '
        content: Or <b>Chaldean.</b>
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'I will expel you and your mother from this land, and you will die
        in a foreign country, not in your native land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'You will never again return to the land you yearn for.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u201CWhy is this man Jehoiachin like a discarded, broken jar?Why
        are he and his children to be exiled to a foreign land?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'O earth, earth, earth!Listen to this message from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\u2018Let the record
        show that this man Jehoiachin was childless.He is a failure,for none of his
        children will succeed him on the throne of Davidto rule over Judah.\u2019"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Righteous Descendant'
      title: The Righteous Descendant
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CWhat sorrow awaits the leaders of my people\u2014the shepherds
        of my sheep\u2014for they have destroyed and scattered the very ones they
        were expected to care for,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Therefore, this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God
        of Israel, says to these shepherds: \u201CInstead of caring for my flock
        and leading them to safety, you have deserted them and driven them to destruction.
        Now I will pour out judgment on you for the evil you have done to them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'But I will gather together the remnant of my flock from the countries
        where I have driven them. I will bring them back to their own sheepfold,
        and they will be fruitful and increase in number. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then I will appoint responsible shepherds who will care for them,
        and they will never be afraid again. Not a single one will be lost or missing.
        I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, have spoken!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CFor the time is coming,\u201Dsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,\u201Cwhen
        I will raise up a righteous descendant[[COMMENT(0)]]from King David\u2019s
        line.He will be a King who rules with wisdom.He will do what is just and
        right throughout the land.  "
      comments:
      - number: '23:5 '
        content: Hebrew <b>a righteous branch.</b>
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And this will be his name:\u2018The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> Is
        Our Righteousness.\u2019[[COMMENT(0)]]In that day Judah will be saved,and
        Israel will live in safety.  "
      comments:
      - number: '23:6 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Yahweh Tsidqenu.</b>
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CIn that day,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, \u201Cwhen
        people are taking an oath, they will no longer say, \u2018As surely as the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> lives, who rescued the people of Israel from
        the land of Egypt.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: Judgment on False Prophets'
      title: Judgment on False Prophets
      number: 8
      content: "Instead, they will say, \u2018As surely as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        lives, who brought the people of Israel back to their own land from the land
        of the north and from all the countries to which he had exiled them.\u2019
        Then they will live in their own land.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'My heart is broken because of the false prophets,and my bones tremble.I
        stagger like a drunkard,like someone overcome by wine,because of the holy
        wordsthe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has spoken against them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "For the land is full of adultery,and it lies under a curse.The land
        itself is in mourning\u2014its wilderness pastures are dried up.For they
        all do eviland abuse what power they have.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CEven the priests and prophetsare ungodly, wicked men.I have
        seen their despicable actsright here in my own Temple,\u201Dsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CTherefore, the paths they takewill become slippery.They will
        be chased through the dark,and there they will fall.For I will bring disaster
        upon themat the time fixed for their punishment.I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        have spoken!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CI saw that the prophets of Samaria were terribly evil,for they
        prophesied in the name of Baaland led my people of Israel into sin.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "But now I see that the prophets of Jerusalem are even worse!They
        commit adultery and love dishonesty.They encourage those who are doing evilso
        that no one turns away from their sins.These prophets are as wickedas the
        people of Sodom and Gomorrah once were.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Therefore, this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies says concerning the prophets:\u201CI will feed them with bitternessand
        give them poison to drink.For it is because of Jerusalem\u2019s prophetsthat
        wickedness has filled this land.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies
        says to his people:\u201CDo not listen to these prophets when they prophesy
        to you,filling you with futile hopes.They are making up everything they say.They
        do not speak for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "They keep saying to those who despise my word,\u2018Don\u2019t worry!
        The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says you will have peace!\u2019And to those
        who stubbornly follow their own desires,they say, \u2018No harm will come
        your way!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CHave any of these prophets been in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        presenceto hear what he is really saying?Has even one of them cared enough
        to listen?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Look! The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s anger bursts out like
        a storm,a whirlwind that swirls down on the heads of the wicked.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The anger of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will not diminishuntil
        it has finished all he has planned.In the days to comeyou will understand
        all this very clearly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CI have not sent these prophets,yet they run around claiming
        to speak for me.I have given them no message,yet they go on prophesying.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'If they had stood before me and listened to me,they would have spoken
        my words,and they would have turned my peoplefrom their evil ways and deeds.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Am I a God who is only close at hand?\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201CNo,
        I am far away at the same time.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Can anyone hide from me in a secret place?Am I not everywhere in
        all the heavens and earth?\u201Dsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CI have heard these prophets say, \u2018Listen to the dream
        I had from God last night.\u2019 And then they proceed to tell lies in my
        name. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'How long will this go on? If they are prophets, they are prophets
        of deceit, inventing everything they say. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'By telling these false dreams, they are trying to get my people to
        forget me, just as their ancestors did by worshiping the idols of Baal.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u201CLet these false prophets tell their dreams,but let my true
        messengers faithfully proclaim my every word.There is a difference between
        straw and grain!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Does not my word burn like fire?\u201Dsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201CIs
        it not like a mighty hammerthat smashes a rock to pieces?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "\u201CTherefore,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, \u201CI
        am against these prophets who steal messages from each other and claim they
        are from me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "I am against these smooth-tongued prophets who say, \u2018This prophecy
        is from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>!\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: False Prophecies and False Prophets'
      title: False Prophecies and False Prophets
      number: 32
      content: 'I am against these false prophets. Their imaginary dreams are flagrant
        lies that lead my people into sin. I did not send or appoint them, and they
        have no message at all for my people. I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        have spoken!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "\u201CSuppose one of the people or one of the prophets or priests
        asks you, \u2018What prophecy has the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> burdened
        you with now?\u2019 You must reply, \u2018You are the burden![[COMMENT(0)]]
        The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says he will abandon you!\u2019  "
      comments:
      - number: '23:33 '
        content: As in Greek version and Latin Vulgate; Hebrew reads <b>What burden?</b>
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "\u201CIf any prophet, priest, or anyone else says, \u2018I have a
        prophecy from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,\u2019 I will punish that person
        along with his entire family. "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "You should keep asking each other, \u2018What is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        answer?\u2019 or \u2018What is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> saying?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "But stop using this phrase, \u2018prophecy from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u2019
        For people are using it to give authority to their own ideas, turning upside
        down the words of our God, the living God, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "\u201CThis is what you should say to the prophets: \u2018What is
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s answer?\u2019 or \u2018What is the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> saying?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "But suppose they respond, \u2018This is a prophecy from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>!\u2019
        Then you should say, \u2018This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:
        Because you have used this phrase, \u201Cprophecy from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,\u201D
        even though I warned you not to use it, "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'I will forget you completely.[[COMMENT(0)]] I will expel you from
        my presence, along with this city that I gave to you and your ancestors. '
      comments:
      - number: '23:39 '
        content: Some Hebrew manuscripts and Greek version read <b>I will surely
          lift you up.</b>
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "And I will make you an object of ridicule, and your name will be
        infamous throughout the ages.\u2019\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Good and Bad Figs'
      title: Good and Bad Figs
      number: 1
      content: "  After King Nebuchadnezzar[[COMMENT(0)]] of Babylon exiled Jehoiachin[[COMMENT(1)]]
        son of Jehoiakim, king of Judah, to Babylon along with the officials of Judah
        and all the craftsmen and artisans, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave
        me this vision. I saw two baskets of figs placed in front of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        Temple in Jerusalem. "
      comments:
      - number: '24:1a '
        content: Hebrew <b>Nebuchadrezzar, </b>a variant spelling of Nebuchadnezzar.
      - number: '24:1b '
        content: Hebrew <b>Jeconiah, </b>a variant spelling of Jehoiachin.
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'One basket was filled with fresh, ripe figs, while the other was
        filled with bad figs that were too rotten to eat.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me, \u201CWhat do you
        see, Jeremiah?\u201DI replied, \u201CFigs, some very good and some very bad,
        too rotten to eat.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave me this message: '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of Israel,
        says: The good figs represent the exiles I sent from Judah to the land of
        the Babylonians.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '24:5 '
        content: Or <b>Chaldeans.</b>
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'I will watch over and care for them, and I will bring them back here
        again. I will build them up and not tear them down. I will plant them and
        not uproot them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'I will give them hearts that recognize me as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        They will be my people, and I will be their God, for they will return to
        me wholeheartedly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CBut the bad figs,\u201D the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said,
        \u201Crepresent King Zedekiah of Judah, his officials, all the people left
        in Jerusalem, and those who live in Egypt. I will treat them like bad figs,
        too rotten to eat. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'I will make them an object of horror and a symbol of evil to every
        nation on earth. They will be disgraced and mocked, taunted and cursed, wherever
        I scatter them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And I will send war, famine, and disease until they have vanished
        from the land of Israel, which I gave to them and their ancestors.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Seventy Years of Captivity'
      title: Seventy Years of Captivity
      number: 1
      content: "  This message for all the people of Judah came to Jeremiah from
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> during the fourth year of Jehoiakim\u2019s
        reign over Judah.[[COMMENT(0)]] This was the year when King Nebuchadnezzar[[COMMENT(1)]]
        of Babylon began his reign.  "
      comments:
      - number: '25:1a '
        content: "The fourth year of Jehoiakim\u2019s reign and the accession year
          of Nebuchadnezzar\u2019s reign was 605 <span class=\"ChapterContent_sc__Hg9da\">b.c.</span>"
      - number: '25:1b '
        content: Hebrew <b>Nebuchadrezzar, </b>a variant spelling of Nebuchadnezzar;
          also in 25:9.
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Jeremiah the prophet said to all the people in Judah and Jerusalem, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CFor the past twenty-three years\u2014from the thirteenth year
        of the reign of Josiah son of Amon,[[COMMENT(0)]] king of Judah, until now\u2014the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has been giving me his messages. I have faithfully
        passed them on to you, but you have not listened.  "
      comments:
      - number: '25:3 '
        content: "The thirteenth year of Josiah\u2019s reign was 627 <span class=\"ChapterContent_sc__Hg9da\">b.c.</span>"
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CAgain and again the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has sent you
        his servants, the prophets, but you have not listened or even paid attention. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Each time the message was this: \u2018Turn from the evil road you
        are traveling and from the evil things you are doing. Only then will I let
        you live in this land that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave to you and
        your ancestors forever. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Do not provoke my anger by worshiping idols you made with your own
        hands. Then I will not harm you.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CBut you would not listen to me,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        \u201CYou made me furious by worshiping idols you made with your own hands,
        bringing on yourselves all the disasters you now suffer. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And now the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies says:
        Because you have not listened to me, "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: I will gather together all the armies of the north under King Nebuchadnezzar
        of Babylon, whom I have appointed as my deputy. I will bring them all against
        this land and its people and against the surrounding nations. I will completely
        destroy[[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps> you and make you an object of horror and
        contempt and a ruin forever. </smallcaps>
      comments:
      - number: '25:9 '
        content: The Hebrew term used here refers to the complete consecration of
          things or people to the <span class="ChapterContent_nd__ECPAf">Lord</span>,
          either by destroying them or by giving them as an offering.
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'I will take away your happy singing and laughter. The joyful voices
        of bridegrooms and brides will no longer be heard. Your millstones will fall
        silent, and the lights in your homes will go out. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'This entire land will become a desolate wasteland. Israel and her
        neighboring lands will serve the king of Babylon for seventy years.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CThen, after the seventy years of captivity are over, I will
        punish the king of Babylon and his people for their sins,\u201D says the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. \u201CI will make the country of the Babylonians[[COMMENT(0)]]
        a wasteland forever. "
      comments:
      - number: '25:12 '
        content: Or <b>Chaldeans.</b>
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "I will bring upon them all the terrors I have promised in this book\u2014all
        the penalties announced by Jeremiah against the nations. "
      comments: []
    - name: "14: The Cup of the \u2019s Anger"
      title: "The Cup of the \u2019s Anger"
      number: 14
      content: "Many nations and great kings will enslave the Babylonians, just as
        they enslaved my people. I will punish them in proportion to the suffering
        they cause my people.\u201D<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of Israel,
        said to me: \u201CTake from my hand this cup filled to the brim with my anger,
        and make all the nations to whom I send you drink from it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "When they drink from it, they will stagger, crazed by the warfare
        I will send against them.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "So I took the cup of anger from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and
        made all the nations drink from it\u2014every nation to which the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        sent me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'I went to Jerusalem and the other towns of Judah, and their kings
        and officials drank from the cup. From that day until this, they have been
        a desolate ruin, an object of horror, contempt, and cursing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'I gave the cup to Pharaoh, king of Egypt, his attendants, his officials,
        and all his people, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'along with all the foreigners living in that land. I also gave it
        to all the kings of the land of Uz and the kings of the Philistine cities
        of Ashkelon, Gaza, Ekron, and what remains of Ashdod. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then I gave the cup to the nations of Edom, Moab, and Ammon, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'and the kings of Tyre and Sidon, and the kings of the regions across
        the sea. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'I gave it to Dedan, Tema, and Buz, and to the people who live in
        distant places.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '25:23 '
        content: Or <b>who clip the corners of their hair.</b>
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'I gave it to the kings of Arabia, the kings of the nomadic tribes
        of the desert, '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'and to the kings of Zimri, Elam, and Media. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "And I gave it to the kings of the northern countries, far and near,
        one after the other\u2014all the kingdoms of the world. And finally, the
        king of Babylon[[COMMENT(0)]] himself drank from the cup of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        anger.  "
      comments:
      - number: '25:26 '
        content: Hebrew <b>of Sheshach, </b>a code name for Babylon.
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me, \u201CNow tell them,
        \u2018This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies,
        the God of Israel, says: Drink from this cup of my anger. Get drunk and vomit;
        fall to rise no more, for I am sending terrible wars against you.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "And if they refuse to accept the cup, tell them, \u2018The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies says: You have no choice but to drink from it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "I have begun to punish Jerusalem, the city that bears my name. Now
        should I let you go unpunished? No, you will not escape disaster. I will
        call for war against all the nations of the earth. I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies, have spoken!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "\u201CNow prophesy all these things, and say to them,\u201C\u2018The
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will roar against his own landfrom his holy dwelling
        in heaven.He will shout like those who tread grapes;he will shout against
        everyone on earth.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "His cry of judgment will reach the ends of the earth,for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will bring his case against all the nations.He will judge all the people
        of the earth,slaughtering the wicked with the sword.I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        have spoken!\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies
        says:\u201CLook! Disaster will fall upon nation after nation!A great whirlwind
        of fury is risingfrom the most distant corners of the earth!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'In that day those the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has slaughtered
        will fill the earth from one end to the other. No one will mourn for them
        or gather up their bodies to bury them. They will be scattered on the ground
        like manure.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Weep and moan, you evil shepherds!Roll in the dust, you leaders of
        the flock!The time of your slaughter has arrived;you will fall and shatter
        like a fragile vase.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'You will find no place to hide;there will be no way to escape.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Listen to the frantic cries of the shepherds.The leaders of the flock
        are wailing in despair,for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is ruining their
        pastures.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Peaceful meadows will be turned into a wastelandby the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        fierce anger.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "He has left his den like a strong lion seeking its prey,and their
        land will be made desolateby the sword[[COMMENT(0)]] of the enemyand the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s fierce anger."
      comments:
      - number: '25:38 '
        content: As in some Hebrew manuscripts and Greek version; Masoretic Text
          reads <b>by the anger.</b>
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Jeremiah\u2019s Escape from Death"
      title: "Jeremiah\u2019s Escape from Death"
      number: 1
      content: '  This message came to Jeremiah from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        early in the reign of Jehoiakim son of Josiah,[[COMMENT(0)]] king of Judah. '
      comments:
      - number: '26:1 '
        content: "The first year of Jehoiakim\u2019s reign was 608 <span class=\"ChapterContent_sc__Hg9da\">b.c.</span>"
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: Stand in
        the courtyard in front of the Temple of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        and make an announcement to the people who have come there to worship from
        all over Judah. Give them my entire message; include every word. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Perhaps they will listen and turn from their evil ways. Then I will
        change my mind about the disaster I am ready to pour out on them because
        of their sins.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CSay to them, \u2018This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        says: If you will not listen to me and obey my word I have given you, "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "and if you will not listen to my servants, the prophets\u2014for
        I sent them again and again to warn you, but you would not listen to them\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "then I will destroy this Temple as I destroyed Shiloh, the place
        where the Tabernacle was located. And I will make Jerusalem an object of
        cursing in every nation on earth.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "The priests, the prophets, and all the people listened to Jeremiah
        as he spoke in front of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s Temple. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But when Jeremiah had finished his message, saying everything the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had told him to say, the priests and prophets
        and all the people at the Temple mobbed him. \u201CKill him!\u201D they shouted. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CWhat right do you have to prophesy in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        name that this Temple will be destroyed like Shiloh? What do you mean, saying
        that Jerusalem will be destroyed and left with no inhabitants?\u201D And
        all the people threatened him as he stood in front of the Temple.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'When the officials of Judah heard what was happening, they rushed
        over from the palace and sat down at the New Gate of the Temple to hold court. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "The priests and prophets presented their accusations to the officials
        and the people. \u201CThis man should die!\u201D they said. \u201CYou have
        heard with your own ears what a traitor he is, for he has prophesied against
        this city.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then Jeremiah spoke to the officials and the people in his own defense.
        \u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> sent me to prophesy against this Temple
        and this city,\u201D he said. \u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave
        me every word that I have spoken. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'But if you stop your sinning and begin to obey the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God, he will change his mind about this disaster that he has announced
        against you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "As for me, I am in your hands\u2014do with me as you think best. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "But if you kill me, rest assured that you will be killing an innocent
        man! The responsibility for such a deed will lie on you, on this city, and
        on every person living in it. For it is absolutely true that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        sent me to speak every word you have heard.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then the officials and the people said to the priests and prophets,
        \u201CThis man does not deserve the death sentence, for he has spoken to
        us in the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then some of the wise old men stood and spoke to all the people assembled
        there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "They said, \u201CRemember when Micah of Moresheth prophesied during
        the reign of King Hezekiah of Judah. He told the people of Judah,\u2018This
        is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies says:Mount
        Zion will be plowed like an open field;Jerusalem will be reduced to ruins!A
        thicket will grow on the heightswhere the Temple now stands.\u2019[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '26:18 '
        content: Mic 3:12.
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "But did King Hezekiah and the people kill him for saying this? No,
        they turned from their sins and worshiped the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        They begged him for mercy. Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> changed his
        mind about the terrible disaster he had pronounced against them. So we are
        about to do ourselves great harm.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'At this time Uriah son of Shemaiah from Kiriath-jearim was also prophesying
        for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. And he predicted the same terrible disaster
        against the city and nation as Jeremiah did. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'When King Jehoiakim and the army officers and officials heard what
        he was saying, the king sent someone to kill him. But Uriah heard about the
        plan and escaped in fear to Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Then King Jehoiakim sent Elnathan son of Acbor to Egypt along with
        several other men to capture Uriah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'They took him prisoner and brought him back to King Jehoiakim. The
        king then killed Uriah with a sword and had him buried in an unmarked grave.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: Nevertheless, Ahikam son of Shaphan stood up for Jeremiah and persuaded
        the court not to turn him over to the mob to be killed.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jeremiah Wears an Ox Yoke'
      title: Jeremiah Wears an Ox Yoke
      number: 1
      content: '  This message came to Jeremiah from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        early in the reign of Zedekiah[[COMMENT(0)]] son of Josiah, king of Judah.  '
      comments:
      - number: '27:1 '
        content: As in some Hebrew manuscripts and Syriac version (see also 27:3,
          12); most Hebrew manuscripts read <b>Jehoiakim.</b>
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me: \u201CMake
        a yoke, and fasten it on your neck with leather straps. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then send messages to the kings of Edom, Moab, Ammon, Tyre, and Sidon
        through their ambassadors who have come to see King Zedekiah in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Give them this message for their masters: \u2018This is what the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies, the God of Israel, says: "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'With my great strength and powerful arm I made the earth and all
        its people and every animal. I can give these things of mine to anyone I
        choose. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Now I will give your countries to King Nebuchadnezzar of Babylon,
        who is my servant. I have put everything, even the wild animals, under his
        control. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'All the nations will serve him, his son, and his grandson until his
        time is up. Then many nations and great kings will conquer and rule over
        Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "So you must submit to Babylon\u2019s king and serve him; put your
        neck under Babylon\u2019s yoke! I will punish any nation that refuses to
        be his slave, says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. I will send war, famine,
        and disease upon that nation until Babylon has conquered it.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201C\u2018Do not listen to your false prophets, fortune-tellers,
        interpreters of dreams, mediums, and sorcerers who say, \u201CThe king of
        Babylon will not conquer you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'They are all liars, and their lies will lead to your being driven
        out of your land. I will drive you out and send you far away to die. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "But the people of any nation that submits to the king of Babylon
        will be allowed to stay in their own country to farm the land as usual. I,
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, have spoken!\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then I repeated this same message to King Zedekiah of Judah. \u201CIf
        you want to live, submit to the yoke of the king of Babylon and his people. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Why do you insist on dying\u2014you and your people? Why should you
        choose war, famine, and disease, which the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will
        bring against every nation that refuses to submit to Babylon\u2019s king? "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Do not listen to the false prophets who keep telling you, \u2018The
        king of Babylon will not conquer you.\u2019 They are liars. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: \u2018I have not
        sent these prophets! They are telling you lies in my name, so I will drive
        you from this land. You will all die\u2014you and all these prophets, too.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then I spoke to the priests and the people and said, \u201CThis is
        what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: \u2018Do not listen to your prophets
        who claim that soon the gold articles taken from my Temple will be returned
        from Babylon. It is all a lie! "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Do not listen to them. Surrender to the king of Babylon, and you
        will live. Why should this whole city be destroyed? '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "If they really are prophets and speak the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        messages, let them pray to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies. Let them pray that the articles remaining in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        Temple and in the king\u2019s palace and in the palaces of Jerusalem will
        not be carried away to Babylon!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CFor the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies
        has spoken about the pillars in front of the Temple, the great bronze basin
        called the Sea, the water carts, and all the other ceremonial articles. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'King Nebuchadnezzar of Babylon left them here when he exiled Jehoiachin[[COMMENT(0)]]
        son of Jehoiakim, king of Judah, to Babylon, along with all the other nobles
        of Judah and Jerusalem. '
      comments:
      - number: '27:20 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Jeconiah, </b>a variant spelling of Jehoiachin.
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Yes, this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies, the God of Israel, says about the precious things still in the Temple,
        in the palace of Judah\u2019s king, and in Jerusalem: "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u2018They will all be carried away to Babylon and will stay there
        until I send for them,\u2019 says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. \u2018Then
        I will bring them back to Jerusalem again.\u2019\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jeremiah Condemns Hananiah'
      title: Jeremiah Condemns Hananiah
      number: 1
      content: "  One day in late summer[[COMMENT(0)]] of that same year\u2014the
        fourth year of the reign of Zedekiah, king of Judah\u2014Hananiah son of
        Azzur, a prophet from Gibeon, addressed me publicly in the Temple while all
        the priests and people listened. He said, "
      comments:
      - number: '28:1 '
        content: "Hebrew <b>In the fifth month, </b>of the ancient Hebrew lunar calendar.
          The fifth month in the fourth year of Zedekiah\u2019s reign occurred within
          the months of August and September 593 <span class=\"ChapterContent_sc__Hg9da\">b.c.</span>
          Also see note on 1:3."
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies, the God of Israel, says: \u2018I will remove the yoke of the king
        of Babylon from your necks. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Within two years I will bring back all the Temple treasures that
        King Nebuchadnezzar carried off to Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And I will bring back Jehoiachin[[COMMENT(0)]] son of Jehoiakim,
        king of Judah, and all the other captives that were taken to Babylon. I will
        surely break the yoke that the king of Babylon has put on your necks. I,
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, have spoken!\u2019\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '28:4 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Jeconiah, </b>a variant spelling of Jehoiachin.
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Jeremiah responded to Hananiah as they stood in front of all the
        priests and people at the Temple. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "He said, \u201CAmen! May your prophecies come true! I hope the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        does everything you say. I hope he does bring back from Babylon the treasures
        of this Temple and all the captives. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'But listen now to the solemn words I speak to you in the presence
        of all these people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The ancient prophets who preceded you and me spoke against many nations,
        always warning of war, disaster, and disease. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So a prophet who predicts peace must show he is right. Only when
        his predictions come true can we know that he is really from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then Hananiah the prophet took the yoke off Jeremiah\u2019s neck
        and broke it in pieces. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And Hananiah said again to the crowd that had gathered, \u201CThis
        is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: \u2018Just as this yoke has
        been broken, within two years I will break the yoke of oppression from all
        the nations now subject to King Nebuchadnezzar of Babylon.\u2019\u201D With
        that, Jeremiah left the Temple area.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Soon after this confrontation with Hananiah, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        gave this message to Jeremiah: '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CGo and tell Hananiah, \u2018This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        says: You have broken a wooden yoke, but you have replaced it with a yoke
        of iron. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies, the God
        of Israel, says: I have put a yoke of iron on the necks of all these nations,
        forcing them into slavery under King Nebuchadnezzar of Babylon. I have put
        everything, even the wild animals, under his control.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then Jeremiah the prophet said to Hananiah, \u201CListen, Hananiah!
        The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has not sent you, but the people believe
        your lies. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Therefore, this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: \u2018You
        must die. Your life will end this very year because you have rebelled against
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Two months later[[COMMENT(0)]] the prophet Hananiah died.
      comments:
      - number: '28:17 '
        content: Hebrew <b>In the seventh month of that same year. </b>See 28:1 and
          the note there.
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Letter to the Exiles'
      title: A Letter to the Exiles
      number: 1
      content: '  Jeremiah wrote a letter from Jerusalem to the elders, priests,
        prophets, and all the people who had been exiled to Babylon by King Nebuchadnezzar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'This was after King Jehoiachin,[[COMMENT(0)]] the queen mother, the
        court officials, the other officials of Judah, and all the craftsmen and
        artisans had been deported from Jerusalem. '
      comments:
      - number: '29:2 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Jeconiah, </b>a variant spelling of Jehoiachin.
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "He sent the letter with Elasah son of Shaphan and Gemariah son of
        Hilkiah when they went to Babylon as King Zedekiah\u2019s ambassadors to
        Nebuchadnezzar. This is what Jeremiah\u2019s letter said:  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies,
        the God of Israel, says to all the captives he has exiled to Babylon from
        Jerusalem: "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CBuild homes, and plan to stay. Plant gardens, and eat the food
        they produce. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Marry and have children. Then find spouses for them so that you may
        have many grandchildren. Multiply! Do not dwindle away! '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And work for the peace and prosperity of the city where I sent you
        into exile. Pray to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> for it, for its welfare
        will determine your welfare.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies,
        the God of Israel, says: \u201CDo not let your prophets and fortune-tellers
        who are with you in the land of Babylon trick you. Do not listen to their
        dreams, "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "because they are telling you lies in my name. I have not sent them,\u201D
        says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: \u201CYou will
        be in Babylon for seventy years. But then I will come and do for you all
        the good things I have promised, and I will bring you home again. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "For I know the plans I have for you,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        \u201CThey are plans for good and not for disaster, to give you a future
        and a hope. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'In those days when you pray, I will listen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'If you look for me wholeheartedly, you will find me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "I will be found by you,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        \u201CI will end your captivity and restore your fortunes. I will gather
        you out of the nations where I sent you and will bring you home again to
        your own land.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'You claim that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has raised up prophets
        for you in Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "But this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says about the king
        who sits on David\u2019s throne and all those still living here in Jerusalem\u2014your
        relatives who were not exiled to Babylon. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies
        says: \u201CI will send war, famine, and disease upon them and make them
        like bad figs, too rotten to eat. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Yes, I will pursue them with war, famine, and disease, and I will
        scatter them around the world. In every nation where I send them, I will
        make them an object of damnation, horror, contempt, and mockery. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "For they refuse to listen to me, though I have spoken to them repeatedly
        through the prophets I sent. And you who are in exile have not listened either,\u201D
        says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Therefore, listen to this message from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        all you captives there in Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies,
        the God of Israel, says about your prophets\u2014Ahab son of Kolaiah and
        Zedekiah son of Maaseiah\u2014who are telling you lies in my name: \u201CI
        will turn them over to Nebuchadnezzar[[COMMENT(0)]] for execution before
        your eyes. "
      comments:
      - number: '29:21 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Nebuchadrezzar, </b>a variant spelling of Nebuchadnezzar.
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Their terrible fate will become proverbial, so that the Judean exiles
        will curse someone by saying, \u2018May the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> make
        you like Zedekiah and Ahab, whom the king of Babylon burned alive!\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: A Message for Shemaiah'
      title: A Message for Shemaiah
      number: 23
      content: "For these men have done terrible things among my people. They have
        committed adultery with their neighbors\u2019 wives and have lied in my name,
        saying things I did not command. I am a witness to this. I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        have spoken.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> sent this message to Shemaiah the
        Nehelamite in Babylon: '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies, the God of Israel, says: You wrote a letter on your own authority
        to Zephaniah son of Maaseiah, the priest, and you sent copies to the other
        priests and people in Jerusalem. You wrote to Zephaniah,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has appointed you to replace
        Jehoiada as the priest in charge of the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        You are responsible to put into stocks and neck irons any crazy man who claims
        to be a prophet. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'So why have you done nothing to stop Jeremiah from Anathoth, who
        pretends to be a prophet among you? '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Jeremiah sent a letter here to Babylon, predicting that our captivity
        will be a long one. He said, \u2018Build homes, and plan to stay. Plant gardens,
        and eat the food they produce.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "But when Zephaniah the priest received Shemaiah\u2019s letter, he
        took it to Jeremiah and read it to him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave this message to Jeremiah: '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "\u201CSend an open letter to all the exiles in Babylon. Tell them,
        \u2018This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says concerning Shemaiah
        the Nehelamite: Since he has prophesied to you when I did not send him and
        has tricked you into believing his lies, "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "I will punish him and his family. None of his descendants will see
        the good things I will do for my people, for he has incited you to rebel
        against me. I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, have spoken!\u2019\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Promises of Deliverance'
      title: Promises of Deliverance
      number: 1
      content: '  The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave another message to Jeremiah.
        He said, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of Israel,
        says: Write down for the record everything I have said to you, Jeremiah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "For the time is coming when I will restore the fortunes of my people
        of Israel and Judah. I will bring them home to this land that I gave to their
        ancestors, and they will possess it again. I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        have spoken!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'This is the message the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave concerning
        Israel and Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\u201CI hear cries
        of fear;there is terror and no peace.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Now let me ask you a question:Do men give birth to babies?Then why
        do they stand there, ashen-faced,hands pressed against their sideslike a
        woman in labor?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'In all history there has never been such a time of terror.It will
        be a time of trouble for my people Israel.[[COMMENT(0)]]Yet in the end they
        will be saved!  '
      comments:
      - number: '30:7 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Jacob; </b>also in 30:10b, 18. See note on 5:20.
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "For in that day,\u201Dsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies,\u201CI will break the yoke from their necksand snap their chains.Foreigners
        will no longer be their masters.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "For my people will serve the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> their Godand
        their king descended from David\u2014the king I will raise up for them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CSo do not be afraid, Jacob, my servant;do not be dismayed,
        Israel,\u201Dsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201CFor I will bring
        you home again from distant lands,and your children will return from their
        exile.Israel will return to a life of peace and quiet,and no one will terrorize
        them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "For I am with you and will save you,\u201Dsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201CI
        will completely destroy the nations where I have scattered you,but I will
        not completely destroy you.I will discipline you, but with justice;I cannot
        let you go unpunished.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\u201CYour injury
        is incurable\u2014a terrible wound.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'There is no one to help youor to bind up your injury.No medicine
        can heal you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "All your lovers\u2014your allies\u2014have left youand do not care
        about you anymore.I have wounded you cruelly,as though I were your enemy.For
        your sins are many,and your guilt is great.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Why do you protest your punishment\u2014this wound that has no cure?I
        have had to punish youbecause your sins are manyand your guilt is great.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CBut all who devour you will be devoured,and all your enemies
        will be sent into exile.All who plunder you will be plundered,and all who
        attack you will be attacked.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "I will give you back your healthand heal your wounds,\u201D says
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201CFor you are called an outcast\u2014\u2018Jerusalem[[COMMENT(0)]]
        for whom no one cares.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '30:17 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Zion.</b>
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\u201CWhen I bring
        Israel home again from captivityand restore their fortunes,Jerusalem will
        be rebuilt on its ruins,and the palace reconstructed as before.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'There will be joy and songs of thanksgiving,and I will multiply my
        people, not diminish them;I will honor them, not despise them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Their children will prosper as they did long ago.I will establish
        them as a nation before me,and I will punish anyone who hurts them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "They will have their own ruler again,and he will come from their
        own people.I will invite him to approach me,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,\u201Cfor
        who would dare to come unless invited?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "You will be my people,and I will be your God.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Look! The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s anger bursts out like
        a storm,a driving wind that swirls down on the heads of the wicked.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: The fierce anger of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will not diminishuntil
        it has finished all he has planned.In the days to comeyou will understand
        all this.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Hope for Restoration'
      title: Hope for Restoration
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CIn that day,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        \u201CI will be the God of all the families of Israel, and they will be my
        people. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\u201CThose who
        survive the coming destructionwill find blessings even in the barren land,for
        I will give rest to the people of Israel.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Long ago the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Israel:\u201CI have
        loved you, my people, with an everlasting love.With unfailing love I have
        drawn you to myself.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'I will rebuild you, my virgin Israel.You will again be happyand dance
        merrily with your tambourines.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Again you will plant your vineyards on the mountains of Samariaand
        eat from your own gardens there.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "The day will come when watchmen will shoutfrom the hill country of
        Ephraim,\u2018Come, let us go up to Jerusalem[[COMMENT(0)]]to worship the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '31:6 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Zion; </b>also in 31:12.
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Now this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\u201CSing
        with joy for Israel.[[COMMENT(0)]]Shout for the greatest of nations!Shout
        out with praise and joy:\u2018Save your people, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,the
        remnant of Israel!\u2019  "
      comments:
      - number: '31:7 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Jacob; </b>also in 31:11. See note on 5:20.
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'For I will bring them from the northand from the distant corners
        of the earth.I will not forget the blind and lame,the expectant mothers and
        women in labor.A great company will return!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Tears of joy will stream down their faces,and I will lead them home
        with great care.They will walk beside quiet streamsand on smooth paths where
        they will not stumble.For I am Israel\u2019s father,and Ephraim is my oldest
        child.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CListen to this message from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,you
        nations of the world;proclaim it in distant coastlands:The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        who scattered his people,will gather them and watch over themas a shepherd
        does his flock.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has redeemed Israelfrom those
        too strong for them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "They will come home and sing songs of joy on the heights of Jerusalem.They
        will be radiant because of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s good gifts\u2014the
        abundant crops of grain, new wine, and olive oil,and the healthy flocks and
        herds.Their life will be like a watered garden,and all their sorrows will
        be gone.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "The young women will dance for joy,and the men\u2014old and young\u2014will
        join in the celebration.I will turn their mourning into joy.I will comfort
        them and exchange their sorrow for rejoicing.  "
      comments: []
    - name: "14: Rachel\u2019s Sadness Turns to Joy"
      title: "Rachel\u2019s Sadness Turns to Joy"
      number: 14
      content: "The priests will enjoy abundance,and my people will feast on my good
        gifts.I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, have spoken!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\u201CA cry is
        heard in Ramah\u2014deep anguish and bitter weeping.Rachel weeps for her
        children,refusing to be comforted\u2014for her children are gone.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "But now this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\u201CDo
        not weep any longer,for I will reward you,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201CYour
        children will come back to youfrom the distant land of the enemy.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "There is hope for your future,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201CYour
        children will come again to their own land.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "I have heard Israel[[COMMENT(0)]] saying,\u2018You disciplined me
        severely,like a calf that needs training for the yoke.Turn me again to you
        and restore me,for you alone are the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> my God.  "
      comments:
      - number: '31:18 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Ephraim, </b>referring to the northern kingdom of Israel;
          also in 31:20.
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "I turned away from God,but then I was sorry.I kicked myself for my
        stupidity!I was thoroughly ashamed of all I did in my younger days.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CIs not Israel still my son,my darling child?\u201D says the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201CI often have to punish him,but I still
        love him.That\u2019s why I long for himand surely will have mercy on him.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Set up road signs;put up guideposts.Mark well the pathby which you
        came.Come back again, my virgin Israel;return to your towns here.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "How long will you wander,my wayward daughter?For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will cause something new to happen\u2014Israel will embrace her God.[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '31:22 '
        content: Hebrew <b>a woman will surround a man.</b>
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies,
        the God of Israel, says: \u201CWhen I bring them back from captivity, the
        people of Judah and its towns will again say, \u2018The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        bless you, O righteous home, O holy mountain!\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Townspeople and farmers and shepherds alike will live together in
        peace and happiness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "For I have given rest to the weary and joy to the sorrowing.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'At this, I woke up and looked around. My sleep had been very sweet.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CThe day is coming,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        \u201Cwhen I will greatly increase the human population and the number of
        animals here in Israel and Judah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'In the past I deliberately uprooted and tore down this nation. I
        overthrew it, destroyed it, and brought disaster upon it. But in the future
        I will just as deliberately plant it and build it up. I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        have spoken!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CThe people will no longer quote this proverb:\u2018The parents
        have eaten sour grapes,but their children\u2019s mouths pucker at the taste.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "All people will die for their own sins\u2014those who eat the sour
        grapes will be the ones whose mouths will pucker.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "\u201CThe day is coming,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        \u201Cwhen I will make a new covenant with the people of Israel and Judah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "This covenant will not be like the one I made with their ancestors
        when I took them by the hand and brought them out of the land of Egypt. They
        broke that covenant, though I loved them as a husband loves his wife,\u201D
        says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "\u201CBut this is the new covenant I will make with the people of
        Israel after those days,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. \u201CI
        will put my instructions deep within them, and I will write them on their
        hearts. I will be their God, and they will be my people. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "And they will not need to teach their neighbors, nor will they need
        to teach their relatives, saying, \u2018You should know the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u2019
        For everyone, from the least to the greatest, will know me already,\u201D
        says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. \u201CAnd I will forgive their wickedness,
        and I will never again remember their sins.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "It is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> who provides the sun to light
        the dayand the moon and stars to light the night,and who stirs the sea into
        roaring waves.His name is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies,and this is what he says:  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "\u201CI am as likely to reject my people Israelas I am to abolish
        the laws of nature!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\u201CJust as the
        heavens cannot be measuredand the foundations of the earth cannot be explored,so
        I will not consider casting them awayfor the evil they have done.I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        have spoken!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "\u201CThe day is coming,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        \u201Cwhen all Jerusalem will be rebuilt for me, from the Tower of Hananel
        to the Corner Gate. "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'A measuring line will be stretched out over the hill of Gareb and
        across to Goah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "And the entire area\u2014including the graveyard and ash dump in
        the valley, and all the fields out to the Kidron Valley on the east as far
        as the Horse Gate\u2014will be holy to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. The
        city will never again be captured or destroyed.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Jeremiah\u2019s Land Purchase"
      title: "Jeremiah\u2019s Land Purchase"
      number: 1
      content: '  The following message came to Jeremiah from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        in the tenth year of the reign of Zedekiah,[[COMMENT(0)]] king of Judah.
        This was also the eighteenth year of the reign of King Nebuchadnezzar.[[COMMENT(1)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '32:1a '
        content: "The tenth year of Zedekiah\u2019s reign and the eighteenth year
          of Nebuchadnezzar\u2019s reign was 587 <span class=\"ChapterContent_sc__Hg9da\">b.c.</span>"
      - number: '32:1b '
        content: Hebrew <b>Nebuchadrezzar, </b>a variant spelling of Nebuchadnezzar;
          also in 32:28.
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Jerusalem was then under siege from the Babylonian army, and Jeremiah
        was imprisoned in the courtyard of the guard in the royal palace. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "King Zedekiah had put him there, asking why he kept giving this prophecy:
        \u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: \u2018I am about
        to hand this city over to the king of Babylon, and he will take it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'King Zedekiah will be captured by the Babylonians[[COMMENT(0)]] and
        taken to meet the king of Babylon face to face. '
      comments:
      - number: '32:4 '
        content: Or <b>Chaldeans; </b>also in 32:5, 24, 25, 28, 29, 43.
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "He will take Zedekiah to Babylon, and I will deal with him there,\u2019
        says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. \u2018If you fight against the Babylonians,
        you will never succeed.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'At that time the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> sent me a message. He
        said, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CYour cousin Hanamel son of Shallum will come and say to you,
        \u2018Buy my field at Anathoth. By law you have the right to buy it before
        it is offered to anyone else.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then, just as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had said he would,
        my cousin Hanamel came and visited me in the prison. He said, \u201CPlease
        buy my field at Anathoth in the land of Benjamin. By law you have the right
        to buy it before it is offered to anyone else, so buy it for yourself.\u201D
        Then I knew that the message I had heard was from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So I bought the field at Anathoth, paying Hanamel seventeen pieces[[COMMENT(0)]]
        of silver for it. '
      comments:
      - number: '32:9 '
        content: Hebrew <b>17 shekels, </b>about 7 ounces or 194 grams in weight.
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'I signed and sealed the deed of purchase before witnesses, weighed
        out the silver, and paid him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then I took the sealed deed and an unsealed copy of the deed, which
        contained the terms and conditions of the purchase, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'and I handed them to Baruch son of Neriah and grandson of Mahseiah.
        I did all this in the presence of my cousin Hanamel, the witnesses who had
        signed the deed, and all the men of Judah who were there in the courtyard
        of the guardhouse.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then I said to Baruch as they all listened, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies, the God of Israel, says: \u2018Take both this sealed deed and the
        unsealed copy, and put them into a pottery jar to preserve them for a long
        time.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: "15: Jeremiah\u2019s Prayer"
      title: "Jeremiah\u2019s Prayer"
      number: 15
      content: "For this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies, the God of Israel, says: \u2018Someday people will again own property
        here in this land and will buy and sell houses and vineyards and fields.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then after I had given the papers to Baruch, I prayed to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CO Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>! You made the heavens
        and earth by your strong hand and powerful arm. Nothing is too hard for you! "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "You show unfailing love to thousands, but you also bring the consequences
        of one generation\u2019s sin upon the next. You are the great and powerful
        God, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'You have all wisdom and do great and mighty miracles. You see the
        conduct of all people, and you give them what they deserve. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "You performed miraculous signs and wonders in the land of Egypt\u2014things
        still remembered to this day! And you have continued to do great miracles
        in Israel and all around the world. You have made your name famous to this
        day.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CYou brought Israel out of Egypt with mighty signs and wonders,
        with a strong hand and powerful arm, and with overwhelming terror. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "You gave the people of Israel this land that you had promised their
        ancestors long before\u2014a land flowing with milk and honey. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Our ancestors came and conquered it and lived in it, but they refused
        to obey you or follow your word. They have not done anything you commanded.
        That is why you have sent this terrible disaster upon them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CSee how the siege ramps have been built against the city walls!
        Through war, famine, and disease, the city will be handed over to the Babylonians,
        who will conquer it. Everything has happened just as you said. "
      comments: []
    - name: "25: A Prediction of Jerusalem\u2019s Fall"
      title: "A Prediction of Jerusalem\u2019s Fall"
      number: 25
      content: "And yet, O Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, you have told me
        to buy the field\u2014paying good money for it before these witnesses\u2014even
        though the city will soon be handed over to the Babylonians.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Then this message came to Jeremiah from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CI am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of all the peoples
        of the world. Is anything too hard for me? "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Therefore, this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: I will
        hand this city over to the Babylonians and to Nebuchadnezzar, king of Babylon,
        and he will capture it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'The Babylonians outside the walls will come in and set fire to the
        city. They will burn down all these houses where the people provoked my anger
        by burning incense to Baal on the rooftops and by pouring out liquid offerings
        to other gods. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Israel and Judah have done nothing but wrong since their earliest
        days. They have infuriated me with all their evil deeds,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "\u201CFrom the time this city was built until now, it has done nothing
        but anger me, so I am determined to get rid of it.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "\u201CThe sins of Israel and Judah\u2014the sins of the people of
        Jerusalem, the kings, the officials, the priests, and the prophets\u2014have
        stirred up my anger. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'My people have turned their backs on me and have refused to return.
        Even though I diligently taught them, they would not receive instruction
        or obey. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'They have set up their abominable idols right in my own Temple, defiling
        it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: A Promise of Restoration'
      title: A Promise of Restoration
      number: 35
      content: 'They have built pagan shrines to Baal in the valley of Ben-Hinnom,
        and there they sacrifice their sons and daughters to Molech. I have never
        commanded such a horrible deed; it never even crossed my mind to command
        such a thing. What an incredible evil, causing Judah to sin so greatly!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "\u201CNow I want to say something more about this city. You have
        been saying, \u2018It will fall to the king of Babylon through war, famine,
        and disease.\u2019 But this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the
        God of Israel, says: "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'I will certainly bring my people back again from all the countries
        where I will scatter them in my fury. I will bring them back to this very
        city and let them live in peace and safety. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'They will be my people, and I will be their God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'And I will give them one heart and one purpose: to worship me forever,
        for their own good and for the good of all their descendants. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'And I will make an everlasting covenant with them: I will never stop
        doing good for them. I will put a desire in their hearts to worship me, and
        they will never leave me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'I will find joy doing good for them and will faithfully and wholeheartedly
        replant them in this land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "\u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: Just as
        I have brought all these calamities on them, so I will do all the good I
        have promised them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "Fields will again be bought and sold in this land about which you
        now say, \u2018It has been ravaged by the Babylonians, a desolate land where
        people and animals have all disappeared.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "Yes, fields will once again be bought and sold\u2014deeds signed
        and sealed and witnessed\u2014in the land of Benjamin and here in Jerusalem,
        in the towns of Judah and in the hill country, in the foothills of Judah[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and in the Negev, too. For someday I will restore prosperity to them. I,
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, have spoken!\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: '32:44 '
        content: Hebrew <b>the Shephelah.</b>
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Promises of Peace and Prosperity'
      title: Promises of Peace and Prosperity
      number: 1
      content: '  While Jeremiah was still confined in the courtyard of the guard,
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave him this second message: '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says\u2014the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> who made the earth, who formed and established
        it, whose name is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Ask me and I will tell you remarkable secrets you do not know about
        things to come. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "For this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of Israel,
        says: You have torn down the houses of this city and even the king\u2019s
        palace to get materials to strengthen the walls against the siege ramps and
        swords of the enemy. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'You expect to fight the Babylonians,[[COMMENT(0)]] but the men of
        this city are already as good as dead, for I have determined to destroy them
        in my terrible anger. I have abandoned them because of all their wickedness.  '
      comments:
      - number: '33:5 '
        content: Or <b>Chaldeans.</b>
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CNevertheless, the time will come when I will heal Jerusalem\u2019s
        wounds and give it prosperity and true peace. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'I will restore the fortunes of Judah and Israel and rebuild their
        towns. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'I will cleanse them of their sins against me and forgive all their
        sins of rebellion. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then this city will bring me joy, glory, and honor before all the
        nations of the earth! The people of the world will see all the good I do
        for my people, and they will tremble with awe at the peace and prosperity
        I provide for them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: You have
        said, \u2018This is a desolate land where people and animals have all disappeared.\u2019
        Yet in the empty streets of Jerusalem and Judah\u2019s other towns, there
        will be heard once more "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "the sounds of joy and laughter. The joyful voices of bridegrooms
        and brides will be heard again, along with the joyous songs of people bringing
        thanksgiving offerings to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. They will sing,\u2018Give
        thanks to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies,for the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is good.His faithful love endures forever!\u2019For
        I will restore the prosperity of this land to what it was in the past, says
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies says: This land\u2014though it is now desolate and has no people and
        animals\u2014will once more have pastures where shepherds can lead their
        flocks. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Once again shepherds will count their flocks in the towns of the
        hill country, the foothills of Judah,[[COMMENT(0)]] the Negev, the land of
        Benjamin, the vicinity of Jerusalem, and all the towns of Judah. I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        have spoken!  '
      comments:
      - number: '33:13 '
        content: Hebrew <b>the Shephelah.</b>
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CThe day will come, says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, when
        I will do for Israel and Judah all the good things I have promised them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CIn those days and at that timeI will raise up a righteous descendant[[COMMENT(0)]]
        from King David\u2019s line.He will do what is just and right throughout
        the land.  "
      comments:
      - number: '33:15 '
        content: Hebrew <b>a righteous branch.</b>
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "In that day Judah will be saved,and Jerusalem will live in safety.And
        this will be its name:\u2018The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> Is Our Righteousness.\u2019[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '33:16 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Yahweh Tsidqenu.</b>
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'For this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: David will
        have a descendant sitting on the throne of Israel forever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And there will always be Levitical priests to offer burnt offerings
        and grain offerings and sacrifices to me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Then this message came to Jeremiah from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: If you can
        break my covenant with the day and the night so that one does not follow
        the other, "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'only then will my covenant with my servant David be broken. Only
        then will he no longer have a descendant to reign on his throne. The same
        is true for my covenant with the Levitical priests who minister before me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And as the stars of the sky cannot be counted and the sand on the
        seashore cannot be measured, so I will multiply the descendants of my servant
        David and the Levites who minister before me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave another message to Jeremiah.
        He said, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CHave you noticed what people are saying?\u2014\u2018The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        chose Judah and Israel and then abandoned them!\u2019 They are sneering and
        saying that Israel is not worthy to be counted as a nation. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'But this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: I would no
        more reject my people than I would change my laws that govern night and day,
        earth and sky. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "I will never abandon the descendants of Jacob or David, my servant,
        or change the plan that David\u2019s descendants will rule the descendants
        of Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob. Instead, I will restore them to their land
        and have mercy on them.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Warning for Zedekiah'
      title: A Warning for Zedekiah
      number: 1
      content: '  King Nebuchadnezzar[[COMMENT(0)]] of Babylon came with all the
        armies from the kingdoms he ruled, and he fought against Jerusalem and the
        towns of Judah. At that time this message came to Jeremiah from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: '
      comments:
      - number: '34:1 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Nebuchadrezzar, </b>a variant spelling of Nebuchadnezzar.
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CGo to King Zedekiah of Judah, and tell him, \u2018This is what
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of Israel, says: I am about to hand
        this city over to the king of Babylon, and he will burn it down. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'You will not escape his grasp but will be captured and taken to meet
        the king of Babylon face to face. Then you will be exiled to Babylon.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201C\u2018But listen to this promise from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        O Zedekiah, king of Judah. This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:
        You will not be killed in war "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "but will die peacefully. People will burn incense in your memory,
        just as they did for your ancestors, the kings who preceded you. They will
        mourn for you, crying, \u201CAlas, our master is dead!\u201D This I have
        decreed, says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So Jeremiah the prophet delivered the message to King Zedekiah of
        Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Freedom for Hebrew Slaves'
      title: Freedom for Hebrew Slaves
      number: 7
      content: "At this time the Babylonian army was besieging Jerusalem, Lachish,
        and Azekah\u2014the only fortified cities of Judah not yet captured.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'This message came to Jeremiah from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        after King Zedekiah made a covenant with the people, proclaiming freedom
        for the slaves. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "He had ordered all the people to free their Hebrew slaves\u2014both
        men and women. No one was to keep a fellow Judean in bondage. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "The officials and all the people had obeyed the king\u2019s command, "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'but later they changed their minds. They took back the men and women
        they had freed, forcing them to be slaves again.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'So the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave them this message through
        Jeremiah: '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of Israel,
        says: I made a covenant with your ancestors long ago when I rescued them
        from their slavery in Egypt. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'I told them that every Hebrew slave must be freed after serving six
        years. But your ancestors paid no attention to me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Recently you repented and did what was right, following my command.
        You freed your slaves and made a solemn covenant with me in the Temple that
        bears my name. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'But now you have shrugged off your oath and defiled my name by taking
        back the men and women you had freed, forcing them to be slaves once again.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CTherefore, this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:
        Since you have not obeyed me by setting your countrymen free, I will set
        you free to be destroyed by war, disease, and famine. You will be an object
        of horror to all the nations of the earth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Because you have broken the terms of our covenant, I will cut you
        apart just as you cut apart the calf when you walked between its halves to
        solemnize your vows. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Yes, I will cut you apart, whether you are officials of Judah or
        Jerusalem, court officials, priests, or common people\u2014for you have broken
        your oath. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'I will give you to your enemies, and they will kill you. Your bodies
        will be food for the vultures and wild animals.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CI will hand over King Zedekiah of Judah and his officials to
        the army of the king of Babylon. And although they have left Jerusalem for
        a while, "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "I will call the Babylonian armies back again. They will fight against
        this city and will capture it and burn it down. I will see to it that all
        the towns of Judah are destroyed, with no one living there.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Faithful Recabites'
      title: The Faithful Recabites
      number: 1
      content: '  This is the message the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave Jeremiah
        when Jehoiakim son of Josiah was king of Judah: '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CGo to the settlement where the families of the Recabites live,
        and invite them to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s Temple. Take them
        into one of the inner rooms, and offer them some wine.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "So I went to see Jaazaniah son of Jeremiah and grandson of Habazziniah
        and all his brothers and sons\u2014representing all the Recabite families. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'I took them to the Temple, and we went into the room assigned to
        the sons of Hanan son of Igdaliah, a man of God. This room was located next
        to the one used by the Temple officials, directly above the room of Maaseiah
        son of Shallum, the Temple gatekeeper.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'I set cups and jugs of wine before them and invited them to have
        a drink, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "but they refused. \u201CNo,\u201D they said, \u201Cwe don\u2019t
        drink wine, because our ancestor Jehonadab[[COMMENT(0)]] son of Recab gave
        us this command: \u2018You and your descendants must never drink wine. "
      comments:
      - number: '35:6 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Jonadab, </b>a variant spelling of Jehonadab; also in
          35:10, 19. See 2 Kgs 10:15.
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And do not build houses or plant crops or vineyards, but always live
        in tents. If you follow these commands, you will live long, good lives in
        the land.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So we have obeyed him in all these things. We have never had a drink
        of wine to this day, nor have our wives, our sons, or our daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "We haven\u2019t built houses or owned vineyards or farms or planted
        crops. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'We have lived in tents and have fully obeyed all the commands of
        Jehonadab, our ancestor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "But when King Nebuchadnezzar[[COMMENT(0)]] of Babylon attacked this
        country, we were afraid of the Babylonian and Syrian[[COMMENT(1)]] armies.
        So we decided to move to Jerusalem. That is why we are here.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '35:11a '
        content: Hebrew <b>Nebuchadrezzar, </b>a variant spelling of Nebuchadnezzar.
      - number: '35:11b '
        content: Or <b>Chaldean and Aramean.</b>
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave this message to Jeremiah: '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies, the God of Israel, says: Go and say to the people in Judah and Jerusalem,
        \u2018Come and learn a lesson about how to obey me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The Recabites do not drink wine to this day because their ancestor
        Jehonadab told them not to. But I have spoken to you again and again, and
        you refuse to obey me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Time after time I sent you prophets, who told you, \u201CTurn from
        your wicked ways, and start doing things right. Stop worshiping other gods
        so that you might live in peace here in the land I have given to you and
        your ancestors.\u201D But you would not listen to me or obey me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "The descendants of Jehonadab son of Recab have obeyed their ancestor
        completely, but you have refused to listen to me.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CTherefore, this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> God
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies, the God of Israel, says: \u2018Because you refuse
        to listen or answer when I call, I will send upon Judah and Jerusalem all
        the disasters I have threatened.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then Jeremiah turned to the Recabites and said, \u201CThis is what
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies, the God of Israel,
        says: \u2018You have obeyed your ancestor Jehonadab in every respect, following
        all his instructions.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Therefore, this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies, the God of Israel, says: \u2018Jehonadab son of Recab will always
        have descendants who serve me.\u2019\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Baruch Reads the \u2019s Messages"
      title: "Baruch Reads the \u2019s Messages"
      number: 1
      content: '<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  During the fourth year that Jehoiakim
        son of Josiah was king in Judah,[[COMMENT(0)]] the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        gave this message to Jeremiah: '
      comments:
      - number: '36:1 '
        content: "The fourth year of Jehoiakim\u2019s reign was 605 <span class=\"ChapterContent_sc__Hg9da\">b.c.</span>"
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CGet a scroll, and write down all my messages against Israel,
        Judah, and the other nations. Begin with the first message back in the days
        of Josiah, and write down every message, right up to the present time. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Perhaps the people of Judah will repent when they hear again all
        the terrible things I have planned for them. Then I will be able to forgive
        their sins and wrongdoings.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So Jeremiah sent for Baruch son of Neriah, and as Jeremiah dictated
        all the prophecies that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had given him, Baruch
        wrote them on a scroll. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then Jeremiah said to Baruch, \u201CI am a prisoner here and unable
        to go to the Temple. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So you go to the Temple on the next day of fasting, and read the
        messages from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> that I have had you write on
        this scroll. Read them so the people who are there from all over Judah will
        hear them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Perhaps even yet they will turn from their evil ways and ask the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s forgiveness before it is too late. For
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has threatened them with his terrible anger.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Baruch did as Jeremiah told him and read these messages from the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> to the people at the Temple. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'He did this on a day of sacred fasting held in late autumn,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        during the fifth year of the reign of Jehoiakim son of Josiah. People from
        all over Judah had come to Jerusalem to attend the services at the Temple
        on that day. '
      comments:
      - number: '36:9 '
        content: "Hebrew <b>in the ninth month, </b>of the ancient Hebrew lunar calendar
          (also in 36:22). The ninth month in the fifth year of Jehoiakim\u2019s
          reign occurred within the months of November and December 604 <span class=\"ChapterContent_sc__Hg9da\">b.c.</span>
          Also see note on 1:3."
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Baruch read Jeremiah\u2019s words on the scroll to all the people.
        He stood in front of the Temple room of Gemariah, son of Shaphan the secretary.
        This room was just off the upper courtyard of the Temple, near the New Gate
        entrance.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'When Micaiah son of Gemariah and grandson of Shaphan heard the messages
        from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "he went down to the secretary\u2019s room in the palace where the
        administrative officials were meeting. Elishama the secretary was there,
        along with Delaiah son of Shemaiah, Elnathan son of Acbor, Gemariah son of
        Shaphan, Zedekiah son of Hananiah, and all the other officials. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'When Micaiah told them about the messages Baruch was reading to the
        people, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'the officials sent Jehudi son of Nethaniah, grandson of Shelemiah
        and great-grandson of Cushi, to ask Baruch to come and read the messages
        to them, too. So Baruch took the scroll and went to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CSit down and read the scroll to us,\u201D the officials said,
        and Baruch did as they requested.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "When they heard all the messages, they looked at one another in alarm.
        \u201CWe must tell the king what we have heard,\u201D they said to Baruch. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CBut first, tell us how you got these messages. Did they come
        directly from Jeremiah?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "So Baruch explained, \u201CJeremiah dictated them, and I wrote them
        down in ink, word for word, on this scroll.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CYou and Jeremiah should both hide,\u201D the officials told
        Baruch. \u201CDon\u2019t tell anyone where you are!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: King Jehoiakim Burns the Scroll'
      title: King Jehoiakim Burns the Scroll
      number: 20
      content: 'Then the officials left the scroll for safekeeping in the room of
        Elishama the secretary and went to tell the king what had happened.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "The king sent Jehudi to get the scroll. Jehudi brought it from Elishama\u2019s
        room and read it to the king as all his officials stood by. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'It was late autumn, and the king was in a winterized part of the
        palace, sitting in front of a fire to keep warm. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Each time Jehudi finished reading three or four columns, the king
        took a knife and cut off that section of the scroll. He then threw it into
        the fire, section by section, until the whole scroll was burned up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Neither the king nor his attendants showed any signs of fear or repentance
        at what they heard. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Even when Elnathan, Delaiah, and Gemariah begged the king not to
        burn the scroll, he wouldn\u2019t listen.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: Jeremiah Rewrites the Scroll'
      title: Jeremiah Rewrites the Scroll
      number: 26
      content: 'Then the king commanded his son Jerahmeel, Seraiah son of Azriel,
        and Shelemiah son of Abdeel to arrest Baruch and Jeremiah. But the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        had hidden them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "After the king had burned the scroll on which Baruch had written
        Jeremiah\u2019s words, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave Jeremiah another
        message. He said, "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u201CGet another scroll, and write everything again just as you
        did on the scroll King Jehoiakim burned. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Then say to the king, \u2018This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        says: You burned the scroll because it said the king of Babylon would destroy
        this land and empty it of people and animals. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Now this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says about King
        Jehoiakim of Judah: He will have no heirs to sit on the throne of David.
        His dead body will be thrown out to lie unburied\u2014exposed to the heat
        of the day and the frost of the night. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "I will punish him and his family and his attendants for their sins.
        I will pour out on them and on all the people of Jerusalem and Judah all
        the disasters I promised, for they would not listen to my warnings.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: So Jeremiah took another scroll and dictated again to his secretary,
        Baruch. He wrote everything that had been on the scroll King Jehoiakim had
        burned in the fire. Only this time he added much more!
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Zedekiah Calls for Jeremiah'
      title: Zedekiah Calls for Jeremiah
      number: 1
      content: '  Zedekiah son of Josiah succeeded Jehoiachin[[COMMENT(0)]] son of
        Jehoiakim as the king of Judah. He was appointed by King Nebuchadnezzar[[COMMENT(1)]]
        of Babylon. '
      comments:
      - number: '37:1a '
        content: Hebrew <b>Coniah, </b>a variant spelling of Jehoiachin.
      - number: '37:1b '
        content: Hebrew <b>Nebuchadrezzar, </b>a variant spelling of Nebuchadnezzar.
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'But neither King Zedekiah nor his attendants nor the people who were
        left in the land listened to what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said through
        Jeremiah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Nevertheless, King Zedekiah sent Jehucal son of Shelemiah, and Zephaniah
        the priest, son of Maaseiah, to ask Jeremiah, \u201CPlease pray to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        our God for us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Jeremiah had not yet been imprisoned, so he could come and go among
        the people as he pleased.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'At this time the army of Pharaoh Hophra[[COMMENT(0)]] of Egypt appeared
        at the southern border of Judah. When the Babylonian[[COMMENT(1)]] army heard
        about it, they withdrew from their siege of Jerusalem.  '
      comments:
      - number: '37:5a '
        content: Hebrew <b>army of Pharaoh; </b>see 44:30.
      - number: '37:5b '
        content: Or <b>Chaldean; </b>also in 37:10, 11.
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave this message to Jeremiah: '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of Israel,
        says: The king of Judah sent you to ask me what is going to happen. Tell
        him, \u2018Pharaoh\u2019s army is about to return to Egypt, though he came
        here to help you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then the Babylonians[[COMMENT(0)]] will come back and capture this
        city and burn it to the ground.\u2019  "
      comments:
      - number: '37:8 '
        content: Or <b>Chaldeans; </b>also in 37:9, 13.
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: Do not fool
        yourselves into thinking that the Babylonians are gone for good. They aren\u2019t! "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Jeremiah Is Imprisoned'
      title: Jeremiah Is Imprisoned
      number: 10
      content: "Even if you were to destroy the entire Babylonian army, leaving only
        a handful of wounded survivors, they would still stagger from their tents
        and burn this city to the ground!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "When the Babylonian army left Jerusalem because of Pharaoh\u2019s
        approaching army, "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Jeremiah started to leave the city on his way to the territory of
        Benjamin, to claim his share of the property among his relatives there.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '37:12 '
        content: Hebrew <b>to separate from there in the midst of the people.</b>
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "But as he was walking through the Benjamin Gate, a sentry arrested
        him and said, \u201CYou are defecting to the Babylonians!\u201D The sentry
        making the arrest was Irijah son of Shelemiah, grandson of Hananiah.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CThat\u2019s not true!\u201D Jeremiah protested. \u201CI had
        no intention of doing any such thing.\u201D But Irijah wouldn\u2019t listen,
        and he took Jeremiah before the officials. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "They were furious with Jeremiah and had him flogged and imprisoned
        in the house of Jonathan the secretary. Jonathan\u2019s house had been converted
        into a prison. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Jeremiah was put into a dungeon cell, where he remained for many
        days.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Later King Zedekiah secretly requested that Jeremiah come to the
        palace, where the king asked him, \u201CDo you have any messages from the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>?\u201D\u201CYes, I do!\u201D said Jeremiah. \u201CYou
        will be defeated by the king of Babylon.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then Jeremiah asked the king, \u201CWhat crime have I committed?
        What have I done against you, your attendants, or the people that I should
        be imprisoned like this? "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Where are your prophets now who told you the king of Babylon would
        not attack you or this land? '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Listen, my lord the king, I beg you. Don\u2019t send me back to the
        dungeon in the house of Jonathan the secretary, for I will die there.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: So King Zedekiah commanded that Jeremiah not be returned to the dungeon.
        Instead, he was imprisoned in the courtyard of the guard in the royal palace.
        The king also commanded that Jeremiah be given a loaf of fresh bread every
        day as long as there was any left in the city. So Jeremiah was put in the
        palace prison.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jeremiah in a Cistern'
      title: Jeremiah in a Cistern
      number: 1
      content: '  Now Shephatiah son of Mattan, Gedaliah son of Pashhur, Jehucal[[COMMENT(0)]]
        son of Shelemiah, and Pashhur son of Malkijah heard what Jeremiah had been
        telling the people. He had been saying, '
      comments:
      - number: '38:1 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Jucal, </b>a variant spelling of Jehucal; see 37:3.
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: \u2018Everyone
        who stays in Jerusalem will die from war, famine, or disease, but those who
        surrender to the Babylonians[[COMMENT(0)]] will live. Their reward will be
        life. They will live!\u2019 "
      comments:
      - number: '38:2 '
        content: Or <b>Chaldeans; </b>also in 38:18, 19, 23.
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> also says: \u2018The city of Jerusalem
        will certainly be handed over to the army of the king of Babylon, who will
        capture it.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "So these officials went to the king and said, \u201CSir, this man
        must die! That kind of talk will undermine the morale of the few fighting
        men we have left, as well as that of all the people. This man is a traitor!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "King Zedekiah agreed. \u201CAll right,\u201D he said. \u201CDo as
        you like. I can\u2019t stop you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So the officials took Jeremiah from his cell and lowered him by ropes
        into an empty cistern in the prison yard. It belonged to Malkijah, a member
        of the royal family. There was no water in the cistern, but there was a thick
        layer of mud at the bottom, and Jeremiah sank down into it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'But Ebed-melech the Ethiopian,[[COMMENT(0)]] an important court official,
        heard that Jeremiah was in the cistern. At that time the king was holding
        court at the Benjamin Gate, '
      comments:
      - number: '38:7 '
        content: Hebrew <b>the Cushite.</b>
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'so Ebed-melech rushed from the palace to speak with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CMy lord the king,\u201D he said, \u201Cthese men have done
        a very evil thing in putting Jeremiah the prophet into the cistern. He will
        soon die of hunger, for almost all the bread in the city is gone.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So the king told Ebed-melech, \u201CTake thirty of my men with you,
        and pull Jeremiah out of the cistern before he dies.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'So Ebed-melech took the men with him and went to a room in the palace
        beneath the treasury, where he found some old rags and discarded clothing.
        He carried these to the cistern and lowered them to Jeremiah on a rope. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Ebed-melech called down to Jeremiah, \u201CPut these rags under your
        armpits to protect you from the ropes.\u201D Then when Jeremiah was ready, "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Zedekiah Questions Jeremiah'
      title: Zedekiah Questions Jeremiah
      number: 13
      content: "they pulled him out. So Jeremiah was returned to the courtyard of
        the guard\u2014the palace prison\u2014where he remained.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "One day King Zedekiah sent for Jeremiah and had him brought to the
        third entrance of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s Temple. \u201CI
        want to ask you something,\u201D the king said. \u201CAnd don\u2019t try
        to hide the truth.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Jeremiah said, \u201CIf I tell you the truth, you will kill me. And
        if I give you advice, you won\u2019t listen to me anyway.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "So King Zedekiah secretly promised him, \u201CAs surely as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        our Creator lives, I will not kill you or hand you over to the men who want
        you dead.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then Jeremiah said to Zedekiah, \u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        God of Heaven\u2019s Armies, the God of Israel, says: \u2018If you surrender
        to the Babylonian officers, you and your family will live, and the city will
        not be burned down. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "But if you refuse to surrender, you will not escape! This city will
        be handed over to the Babylonians, and they will burn it to the ground.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CBut I am afraid to surrender,\u201D the king said, \u201Cfor
        the Babylonians may hand me over to the Judeans who have defected to them.
        And who knows what they will do to me!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Jeremiah replied, \u201CYou won\u2019t be handed over to them if
        you choose to obey the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. Your life will be spared,
        and all will go well for you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'But if you refuse to surrender, this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has revealed to me: '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "All the women left in your palace will be brought out and given to
        the officers of the Babylonian army. Then the women will taunt you, saying,\u2018What
        fine friends you have!They have betrayed and misled you.When your feet sank
        in the mud,they left you to your fate!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "All your wives and children will be led out to the Babylonians, and
        you will not escape. You will be seized by the king of Babylon, and this
        city will be burned down.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then Zedekiah said to Jeremiah, \u201CDon\u2019t tell anyone you
        told me this, or you will die! "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "My officials may hear that I spoke to you, and they may say, \u2018Tell
        us what you and the king were talking about. If you don\u2019t tell us, we
        will kill you.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "If this happens, just tell them you begged me not to send you back
        to Jonathan\u2019s dungeon, for fear you would die there.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Sure enough, it wasn\u2019t long before the king\u2019s officials
        came to Jeremiah and asked him why the king had called for him. But Jeremiah
        followed the king\u2019s instructions, and they left without finding out
        the truth. No one had overheard the conversation between Jeremiah and the
        king. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: And Jeremiah remained a prisoner in the courtyard of the guard until
        the day Jerusalem was captured.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Fall of Jerusalem'
      title: The Fall of Jerusalem
      number: 1
      content: "  In January[[COMMENT(0)]] of the ninth year of King Zedekiah\u2019s
        reign, King Nebuchadnezzar[[COMMENT(1)]] of Babylon came with his entire
        army to besiege Jerusalem. "
      comments:
      - number: '39:1a '
        content: Hebrew <b>In the tenth month, </b>of the ancient Hebrew lunar calendar.
          A number of events in Jeremiah can be cross-checked with dates in surviving
          Babylonian records and related accurately to our modern calendar. This
          event occurred on January 15, 588 <span class="ChapterContent_sc__Hg9da">b.c.</span>;
          see 52:4a and the note there.
      - number: '39:1b '
        content: Hebrew <b>Nebuchadrezzar, </b>a variant spelling of Nebuchadnezzar;
          also in 39:5, 11.
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Two and a half years later, on July 18[[COMMENT(0)]] in the eleventh
        year of Zedekiah\u2019s reign, a section of the city wall was broken down. "
      comments:
      - number: '39:2 '
        content: Hebrew <b>On the ninth day of the fourth month. </b>This day was
          July 18, 586 <span class="ChapterContent_sc__Hg9da">b.c.</span>; also see
          note on 39:1a.
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "All the officers of the Babylonian army came in and sat in triumph
        at the Middle Gate: Nergal-sharezer of Samgar, and Nebo-sarsekim,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        a chief officer, and Nergal-sharezer, the king\u2019s adviser, and all the
        other officers of the king of Babylon.  "
      comments:
      - number: '39:3 '
        content: Or <b>Nergal-sharezer, Samgar-nebo, Sarsekim.</b>
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "When King Zedekiah of Judah and all the soldiers saw that the Babylonians
        had broken into the city, they fled. They waited for nightfall and then slipped
        through the gate between the two walls behind the king\u2019s garden and
        headed toward the Jordan Valley.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '39:4 '
        content: Hebrew <b>the Arabah.</b>
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But the Babylonian[[COMMENT(0)]] troops chased them and overtook
        Zedekiah on the plains of Jericho. They captured him and took him to King
        Nebuchadnezzar of Babylon, who was at Riblah in the land of Hamath. There
        the king of Babylon pronounced judgment upon Zedekiah. '
      comments:
      - number: '39:5 '
        content: Or <b>Chaldean; </b>similarly in 39:8.
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The king of Babylon made Zedekiah watch as he slaughtered his sons
        at Riblah. The king of Babylon also slaughtered all the nobles of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then he gouged out Zedekiah\u2019s eyes and bound him in bronze chains
        to lead him away to Babylon.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Meanwhile, the Babylonians burned Jerusalem, including the royal
        palace and the houses of the people, and they tore down the walls of the
        city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then Nebuzaradan, the captain of the guard, took as exiles to Babylon
        the rest of the people who remained in the city, those who had defected to
        him, and everyone else who remained. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Jeremiah Remains in Judah'
      title: Jeremiah Remains in Judah
      number: 10
      content: 'But Nebuzaradan allowed some of the poorest people to stay behind
        in the land of Judah, and he assigned them to care for the vineyards and
        fields.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'King Nebuchadnezzar had told Nebuzaradan, the captain of the guard,
        to find Jeremiah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CSee that he isn\u2019t hurt,\u201D he said. \u201CLook after
        him well, and give him anything he wants.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "So Nebuzaradan, the captain of the guard; Nebushazban, a chief officer;
        Nergal-sharezer, the king\u2019s adviser; and the other officers of Babylon\u2019s
        king "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'sent messengers to bring Jeremiah out of the prison. They put him
        under the care of Gedaliah son of Ahikam and grandson of Shaphan, who took
        him back to his home. So Jeremiah stayed in Judah among his own people.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had given the following message to
        Jeremiah while he was still in prison: '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CSay to Ebed-melech the Ethiopian,[[COMMENT(0)]] \u2018This
        is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies, the God
        of Israel, says: I will do to this city everything I have threatened. I will
        send disaster, not prosperity. You will see its destruction, "
      comments:
      - number: '39:16 '
        content: Hebrew <b>the Cushite.</b>
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'but I will rescue you from those you fear so much. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Because you trusted me, I will give you your life as a reward. I
        will rescue you and keep you safe. I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, have
        spoken!\u2019\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '  The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave a message to Jeremiah after
        Nebuzaradan, the captain of the guard, had released him at Ramah. He had
        found Jeremiah bound in chains among all the other captives of Jerusalem
        and Judah who were being sent to exile in Babylon.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "The captain of the guard called for Jeremiah and said, \u201CThe
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God has brought this disaster on this land, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'just as he said he would. For these people have sinned against the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and disobeyed him. That is why it happened. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "But I am going to take off your chains and let you go. If you want
        to come with me to Babylon, you are welcome. I will see that you are well
        cared for. But if you don\u2019t want to come, you may stay here. The whole
        land is before you\u2014go wherever you like. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "If you decide to stay, then return to Gedaliah son of Ahikam and
        grandson of Shaphan. He has been appointed governor of Judah by the king
        of Babylon. Stay there with the people he rules. But it\u2019s up to you;
        go wherever you like.\u201DThen Nebuzaradan, the captain of the guard, gave
        Jeremiah some food and money and let him go. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: Gedaliah Governs in Judah'
      title: Gedaliah Governs in Judah
      number: 6
      content: 'So Jeremiah returned to Gedaliah son of Ahikam at Mizpah, and he
        lived in Judah with the few who were still left in the land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "The leaders of the Judean military groups in the countryside heard
        that the king of Babylon had appointed Gedaliah son of Ahikam as governor
        over the poor people who were left behind in Judah\u2014the men, women, and
        children who hadn\u2019t been exiled to Babylon. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So they went to see Gedaliah at Mizpah. These included: Ishmael son
        of Nethaniah, Johanan and Jonathan sons of Kareah, Seraiah son of Tanhumeth,
        the sons of Ephai the Netophathite, Jezaniah son of the Maacathite, and all
        their men.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Gedaliah vowed to them that the Babylonians[[COMMENT(0)]] meant them
        no harm. \u201CDon\u2019t be afraid to serve them. Live in the land and serve
        the king of Babylon, and all will go well for you,\u201D he promised. "
      comments:
      - number: '40:9 '
        content: Or <b>Chaldeans; </b>also in 40:10.
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CAs for me, I will stay at Mizpah to represent you before the
        Babylonians who come to meet with us. Settle in the towns you have taken,
        and live off the land. Harvest the grapes and summer fruits and olives, and
        store them away.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'When the Judeans in Moab, Ammon, Edom, and the other nearby countries
        heard that the king of Babylon had left a few people in Judah and that Gedaliah
        was the governor, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: A Plot against Gedaliah'
      title: A Plot against Gedaliah
      number: 12
      content: 'they began to return to Judah from the places to which they had fled.
        They stopped at Mizpah to meet with Gedaliah and then went into the Judean
        countryside to gather a great harvest of grapes and other crops.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Soon after this, Johanan son of Kareah and the other military leaders
        came to Gedaliah at Mizpah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "They said to him, \u201CDid you know that Baalis, king of Ammon,
        has sent Ishmael son of Nethaniah to assassinate you?\u201D But Gedaliah
        refused to believe them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Later Johanan had a private conference with Gedaliah and volunteered
        to kill Ishmael secretly. \u201CWhy should we let him come and murder you?\u201D
        Johanan asked. \u201CWhat will happen then to the Judeans who have returned?
        Why should the few of us who are still left be scattered and lost?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "But Gedaliah said to Johanan, \u201CI forbid you to do any such thing,
        for you are lying about Ishmael.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Murder of Gedaliah'
      title: The Murder of Gedaliah
      number: 1
      content: "  But in midautumn of that year,[[COMMENT(0)]] Ishmael son of Nethaniah
        and grandson of Elishama, who was a member of the royal family and had been
        one of the king\u2019s high officials, went to Mizpah with ten men to meet
        Gedaliah. While they were eating together, "
      comments:
      - number: '41:1 '
        content: Hebrew <b>in the seventh month, </b>of the ancient Hebrew lunar
          calendar. This month occurred within the months of October and November
          586 <span class="ChapterContent_sc__Hg9da">b.c.</span>; also see note on
          39:1a.
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Ishmael and his ten men suddenly jumped up, drew their swords, and
        killed Gedaliah, whom the king of Babylon had appointed governor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Ishmael also killed all the Judeans and the Babylonian[[COMMENT(0)]]
        soldiers who were with Gedaliah at Mizpah.  '
      comments:
      - number: '41:3 '
        content: Or <b>Chaldean.</b>
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "The next day, before anyone had heard about Gedaliah\u2019s murder, "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'eighty men arrived from Shechem, Shiloh, and Samaria to worship at
        the Temple of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. They had shaved off their
        beards, torn their clothes, and cut themselves, and had brought along grain
        offerings and frankincense. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Ishmael left Mizpah to meet them, weeping as he went. When he reached
        them, he said, \u201COh, come and see what has happened to Gedaliah!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'But as soon as they were all inside the town, Ishmael and his men
        killed all but ten of them and threw their bodies into a cistern. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The other ten had talked Ishmael into letting them go by promising
        to bring him their stores of wheat, barley, olive oil, and honey that they
        had hidden away. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The cistern where Ishmael dumped the bodies of the men he murdered
        was the large one[[COMMENT(0)]] dug by King Asa when he fortified Mizpah
        to protect himself against King Baasha of Israel. Ishmael son of Nethaniah
        filled it with corpses.  '
      comments:
      - number: '41:9 '
        content: As in Greek version; Hebrew reads <b>murdered because of Gedaliah
          was one.</b>
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then Ishmael made captives of the king\u2019s daughters and the other
        people who had been left under Gedaliah\u2019s care in Mizpah by Nebuzaradan,
        the captain of the guard. Taking them with him, he started back toward the
        land of Ammon.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "But when Johanan son of Kareah and the other military leaders heard
        about Ishmael\u2019s crimes, "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'they took all their men and set out to stop him. They caught up with
        him at the large pool near Gibeon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The people Ishmael had captured shouted for joy when they saw Johanan
        and the other military leaders. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And all the captives from Mizpah escaped and began to help Johanan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Meanwhile, Ishmael and eight of his men escaped from Johanan into
        the land of Ammon.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then Johanan son of Kareah and the other military leaders took all
        the people they had rescued in Gibeon\u2014the soldiers, women, children,
        and court officials[[COMMENT(0)]] whom Ishmael had captured after he killed
        Gedaliah. "
      comments:
      - number: '41:16 '
        content: Or <b>eunuchs.</b>
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'They took them all to the village of Geruth-kimham near Bethlehem,
        where they prepared to leave for Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: They were afraid of what the Babylonians[[COMMENT(0)]] would do when
        they heard that Ishmael had killed Gedaliah, the governor appointed by the
        Babylonian king.
      comments:
      - number: '41:18 '
        content: Or <b>Chaldeans.</b>
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Warning to Stay in Judah'
      title: Warning to Stay in Judah
      number: 1
      content: '  Then all the military leaders, including Johanan son of Kareah
        and Jezaniah[[COMMENT(0)]] son of Hoshaiah, and all the people, from the
        least to the greatest, approached '
      comments:
      - number: '42:1 '
        content: Greek version reads <b>Azariah; </b>compare 43:2.
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Jeremiah the prophet. They said, \u201CPlease pray to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God for us. As you can see, we are only a tiny remnant compared to what
        we were before. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Pray that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God will show us what
        to do and where to go.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CAll right,\u201D Jeremiah replied. \u201CI will pray to the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God, as you have asked, and I will tell
        you everything he says. I will hide nothing from you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then they said to Jeremiah, \u201CMay the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God be a faithful witness against us if we refuse to obey whatever he
        tells us to do! "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Whether we like it or not, we will obey the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        our God to whom we are sending you with our plea. For if we obey him, everything
        will turn out well for us.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Ten days later the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave his reply to
        Jeremiah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So he called for Johanan son of Kareah and the other military leaders,
        and for all the people, from the least to the greatest. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "He said to them, \u201CYou sent me to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        the God of Israel, with your request, and this is his reply: "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u2018Stay here in this land. If you do, I will build you up and
        not tear you down; I will plant you and not uproot you. For I am sorry about
        all the punishment I have had to bring upon you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Do not fear the king of Babylon anymore,\u2019 says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        \u2018For I am with you and will save you and rescue you from his power. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "I will be merciful to you by making him kind, so he will let you
        stay here in your land.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CBut if you refuse to obey the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your
        God, and if you say, \u2018We will not stay here; "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "instead, we will go to Egypt where we will be free from war, the
        call to arms, and hunger,\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "then hear the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s message to the remnant
        of Judah. This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies,
        the God of Israel, says: \u2018If you are determined to go to Egypt and live
        there, "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'the very war and famine you fear will catch up to you, and you will
        die there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "That is the fate awaiting every one of you who insists on going to
        live in Egypt. Yes, you will die from war, famine, and disease. None of you
        will escape the disaster I will bring upon you there.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies, the God of Israel, says: \u2018Just as my anger and fury have been
        poured out on the people of Jerusalem, so they will be poured out on you
        when you enter Egypt. You will be an object of damnation, horror, cursing,
        and mockery. And you will never see your homeland again.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CListen, you remnant of Judah. The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has told you: \u2018Do not go to Egypt!\u2019 Don\u2019t forget this warning
        I have given you today. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "For you were not being honest when you sent me to pray to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God for you. You said, \u2018Just tell us what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        our God says, and we will do it!\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And today I have told you exactly what he said, but you will not
        obey the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God any better now than you have
        in the past. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "So you can be sure that you will die from war, famine, and disease
        in Egypt, where you insist on going.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jeremiah Taken to Egypt'
      title: Jeremiah Taken to Egypt
      number: 1
      content: '  When Jeremiah had finished giving this message from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        their God to all the people, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Azariah son of Hoshaiah and Johanan son of Kareah and all the other
        proud men said to Jeremiah, \u201CYou lie! The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        our God hasn\u2019t forbidden us to go to Egypt! "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Baruch son of Neriah has convinced you to say this, because he wants
        us to stay here and be killed by the Babylonians[[COMMENT(0)]] or be carried
        off into exile.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '43:3 '
        content: Or <b>Chaldeans.</b>
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "So Johanan and the other military leaders and all the people refused
        to obey the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s command to stay in Judah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Johanan and the other leaders took with them all the people who had
        returned from the nearby countries to which they had fled. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "In the crowd were men, women, and children, the king\u2019s daughters,
        and all those whom Nebuzaradan, the captain of the guard, had left with Gedaliah.
        The prophet Jeremiah and Baruch were also included. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The people refused to obey the voice of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        and went to Egypt, going as far as the city of Tahpanhes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then at Tahpanhes, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave another message
        to Jeremiah. He said, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CWhile the people of Judah are watching, take some large rocks
        and bury them under the pavement stones at the entrance of Pharaoh\u2019s
        palace here in Tahpanhes. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then say to the people of Judah, \u2018This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies, the God of Israel, says: I will certainly bring
        my servant Nebuchadnezzar,[[COMMENT(0)]] king of Babylon, here to Egypt.
        I will set his throne over these stones that I have hidden. He will spread
        his royal canopy over them. "
      comments:
      - number: '43:10 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Nebuchadrezzar, </b>a variant spelling of Nebuchadnezzar.
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And when he comes, he will destroy the land of Egypt. He will bring
        death to those destined for death, captivity to those destined for captivity,
        and war to those destined for war. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "He will set fire to the temples of Egypt\u2019s gods; he will burn
        the temples and carry the idols away as plunder. He will pick clean the land
        of Egypt as a shepherd picks fleas from his cloak. And he himself will leave
        unharmed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "He will break down the sacred pillars standing in the temple of the
        sun[[COMMENT(0)]] in Egypt, and he will burn down the temples of Egypt\u2019s
        gods.\u2019\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: '43:13 '
        content: Or <b>in Heliopolis.</b>
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Judgment for Idolatry'
      title: Judgment for Idolatry
      number: 1
      content: '  This is the message Jeremiah received concerning the Judeans living
        in northern Egypt in the cities of Migdol, Tahpanhes, and Memphis,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and in southern Egypt[[COMMENT(1)]] as well: '
      comments:
      - number: '44:1a '
        content: Hebrew <b>Noph.</b>
      - number: '44:1b '
        content: Hebrew <b>in Pathros.</b>
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies, the God of Israel, says: You saw the calamity I brought on Jerusalem
        and all the towns of Judah. They now lie deserted and in ruins. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "They provoked my anger with all their wickedness. They burned incense
        and worshiped other gods\u2014gods that neither they nor you nor any of your
        ancestors had ever even known.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CAgain and again I sent my servants, the prophets, to plead
        with them, \u2018Don\u2019t do these horrible things that I hate so much.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But my people would not listen or turn back from their wicked ways.
        They kept on burning incense to these gods. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And so my fury boiled over and fell like fire on the towns of Judah
        and into the streets of Jerusalem, and they are still a desolate ruin today.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CAnd now the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> God of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies, the God of Israel, asks you: Why are you destroying yourselves? For
        not one of you will survive\u2014not a man, woman, or child among you who
        has come here from Judah, not even the babies in your arms. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Why provoke my anger by burning incense to the idols you have made
        here in Egypt? You will only destroy yourselves and make yourselves an object
        of cursing and mockery for all the nations of the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Have you forgotten the sins of your ancestors, the sins of the kings
        and queens of Judah, and the sins you and your wives committed in Judah and
        Jerusalem? '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'To this very hour you have shown no remorse or reverence. No one
        has chosen to follow my word and the decrees I gave to you and your ancestors
        before you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CTherefore, this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of
        Heaven\u2019s Armies, the God of Israel, says: I am determined to destroy
        every one of you! "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "I will take this remnant of Judah\u2014those who were determined
        to come here and live in Egypt\u2014and I will consume them. They will fall
        here in Egypt, killed by war and famine. All will die, from the least to
        the greatest. They will be an object of damnation, horror, cursing, and mockery. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'I will punish them in Egypt just as I punished them in Jerusalem,
        by war, famine, and disease. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Of that remnant who fled to Egypt, hoping someday to return to Judah,
        there will be no survivors. Even though they long to return home, only a
        handful will do so.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then all the women present and all the men who knew that their wives
        had burned incense to idols\u2014a great crowd of all the Judeans living
        in northern Egypt and southern Egypt[[COMMENT(0)]]\u2014answered Jeremiah, "
      comments:
      - number: '44:15 '
        content: Hebrew <b>in Egypt, in Pathros.</b>
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CWe will not listen to your messages from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>! "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "We will do whatever we want. We will burn incense and pour out liquid
        offerings to the Queen of Heaven just as much as we like\u2014just as we,
        and our ancestors, and our kings and officials have always done in the towns
        of Judah and in the streets of Jerusalem. For in those days we had plenty
        to eat, and we were well off and had no troubles! "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "But ever since we quit burning incense to the Queen of Heaven and
        stopped worshiping her with liquid offerings, we have been in great trouble
        and have been dying from war and famine.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CBesides,\u201D the women added, \u201Cdo you suppose that we
        were burning incense and pouring out liquid offerings to the Queen of Heaven,
        and making cakes marked with her image, without our husbands knowing it and
        helping us? Of course not!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Then Jeremiah said to all of them, men and women alike, who had given
        him that answer, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CDo you think the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> did not know that
        you and your ancestors, your kings and officials, and all the people were
        burning incense to idols in the towns of Judah and in the streets of Jerusalem? "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "It was because the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> could no longer bear
        all the disgusting things you were doing that he made your land an object
        of cursing\u2014a desolate ruin without inhabitants\u2014as it is today. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "All these terrible things happened to you because you have burned
        incense to idols and sinned against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. You
        have refused to obey him and have not followed his instructions, his decrees,
        and his laws.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then Jeremiah said to them all, including the women, \u201CListen
        to this message from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, all you citizens of
        Judah who live in Egypt. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies,
        the God of Israel, says: \u2018You and your wives have said, \u201CWe will
        keep our promises to burn incense and pour out liquid offerings to the Queen
        of Heaven,\u201D and you have proved by your actions that you meant it. So
        go ahead and carry out your promises and vows to her!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CBut listen to this message from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        all you Judeans now living in Egypt: \u2018I have sworn by my great name,\u2019
        says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, \u2018that my name will no longer be
        spoken by any of the Judeans in the land of Egypt. None of you may invoke
        my name or use this oath: \u201CAs surely as the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        lives.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'For I will watch over you to bring you disaster and not good. Everyone
        from Judah who is now living in Egypt will suffer war and famine until all
        of you are dead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Only a small number will escape death and return to Judah from Egypt.
        Then all those who came to Egypt will find out whose words are true\u2014mine
        or theirs!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201C\u2018And this is the proof I give you,\u2019 says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        \u2018that all I have threatened will happen to you and that I will punish
        you here.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: \u2018I will turn
        Pharaoh Hophra, king of Egypt, over to his enemies who want to kill him,
        just as I turned King Zedekiah of Judah over to King Nebuchadnezzar[[COMMENT(0)]]
        of Babylon.\u2019\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: '44:30 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Nebuchadrezzar, </b>a variant spelling of Nebuchadnezzar.
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Message for Baruch'
      title: A Message for Baruch
      number: 1
      content: '  The prophet Jeremiah gave a message to Baruch son of Neriah in
        the fourth year of the reign of Jehoiakim son of Josiah,[[COMMENT(0)]] after
        Baruch had written down everything Jeremiah had dictated to him. He said, '
      comments:
      - number: '45:1 '
        content: "The fourth year of Jehoiakim\u2019s reign was 605 <span class=\"ChapterContent_sc__Hg9da\">b.c.</span>"
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of Israel,
        says to you, Baruch: "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "You have said, \u2018I am overwhelmed with trouble! Haven\u2019t
        I had enough pain already? And now the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has added
        more! I am worn out from sighing and can find no rest.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CBaruch, this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:
        \u2018I will destroy this nation that I built. I will uproot what I planted. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Are you seeking great things for yourself? Don\u2019t do it! I will
        bring great disaster upon all these people; but I will give you your life
        as a reward wherever you go. I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, have spoken!\u2019\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Messages for the NationsMessages about Egypt'
      title: Messages for the NationsMessages about Egypt
      number: 1
      content: '  The following messages were given to Jeremiah the prophet from
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> concerning foreign nations.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'This message concerning Egypt was given in the fourth year of the
        reign of Jehoiakim son of Josiah, the king of Judah, on the occasion of the
        battle of Carchemish[[COMMENT(0)]] when Pharaoh Neco, king of Egypt, and
        his army were defeated beside the Euphrates River by King Nebuchadnezzar[[COMMENT(1)]]
        of Babylon.  '
      comments:
      - number: '46:2a '
        content: "This event occurred in 605 <span class=\"ChapterContent_sc__Hg9da\">b.c.</span>,
          during the fourth year of Jehoiakim\u2019s reign (according to the calendar
          system in which the new year begins in the spring)."
      - number: '46:2b '
        content: Hebrew <b>Nebuchadrezzar, </b>a variant spelling of Nebuchadnezzar;
          also in 46:13, 26.
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CPrepare your shields,and advance into battle!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Harness the horses,and mount the stallions.Take your positions.Put
        on your helmets.Sharpen your spears,and prepare your armor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "But what do I see?The Egyptian army flees in terror.The bravest of
        its fighting men runwithout a backward glance.They are terrorized at every
        turn,\u201Dsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CThe swiftest runners cannot flee;the mightiest warriors cannot
        escape.By the Euphrates River to the north,they stumble and fall.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CWho is this, rising like the Nile at floodtime,overflowing
        all the land?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'It is the Egyptian army,overflowing all the land,boasting that it
        will cover the earth like a flood,destroying cities and their people.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Charge, you horses and chariots;attack, you mighty warriors of Egypt!Come,
        all you allies from Ethiopia, Libya, and Lydia[[COMMENT(0)]]who are skilled
        with the shield and bow!  '
      comments:
      - number: '46:9 '
        content: Hebrew <b>from Cush, Put, and Lud.</b>
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "For this is the day of the Lord, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies,a day of vengeance on his enemies.The sword will
        devour until it is satisfied,yes, until it is drunk with your blood!The Lord,
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies, will receive a sacrifice
        todayin the north country beside the Euphrates River.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CGo up to Gilead to get medicine,O virgin daughter of Egypt!But
        your many treatmentswill bring you no healing.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "The nations have heard of your shame.The earth is filled with your
        cries of despair.Your mightiest warriors will run into each otherand fall
        down together.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave the prophet Jeremiah this
        message about King Nebuchadnezzar\u2019s plans to attack Egypt.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CShout it out in Egypt!Publish it in the cities of Migdol, Memphis,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and Tahpanhes!Mobilize for battle,for the sword will devour everyone around
        you.  "
      comments:
      - number: '46:14 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Noph; </b>also in 46:19.
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Why have your warriors fallen?They cannot stand, for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has knocked them down.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "They stumble and fall over each otherand say among themselves,\u2018Come,
        let\u2019s go back to our people,to the land of our birth.Let\u2019s get
        away from the sword of the enemy!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "There they will say,\u2018Pharaoh, the king of Egypt, is a loudmouthwho
        missed his opportunity!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CAs surely as I live,\u201D says the King,whose name is the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies,\u201Cone is coming against
        Egyptwho is as tall as Mount Tabor,or as Mount Carmel by the sea!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Pack up! Get ready to leave for exile,you citizens of Egypt!The city
        of Memphis will be destroyed,without a single inhabitant.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Egypt is as sleek as a beautiful heifer,but a horsefly from the north
        is on its way!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Egypt\u2019s mercenaries have become like fattened calves.They, too,
        will turn and run,for it is a day of great disaster for Egypt,a time of great
        punishment.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Egypt flees, silent as a serpent gliding away.The invading army marches
        in;they come against her with axes like woodsmen.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "They will cut down her people like trees,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,\u201Cfor
        they are more numerous than locusts.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Egypt will be humiliated;she will be handed over to people from the
        north.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies, the God
        of Israel, says: \u201CI will punish Amon, the god of Thebes,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and all the other gods of Egypt. I will punish its rulers and Pharaoh, too,
        and all who trust in him. "
      comments:
      - number: '46:25 '
        content: Hebrew <b>of No.</b>
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "I will hand them over to those who want them killed\u2014to King
        Nebuchadnezzar of Babylon and his army. But afterward the land will recover
        from the ravages of war. I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, have spoken!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CBut do not be afraid, Jacob, my servant;do not be dismayed,
        Israel.For I will bring you home again from distant lands,and your children
        will return from their exile.Israel[[COMMENT(0)]] will return to a life of
        peace and quiet,and no one will terrorize them.  "
      comments:
      - number: '46:27 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Jacob. </b>See note on 5:20.
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Do not be afraid, Jacob, my servant,for I am with you,\u201D says
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201CI will completely destroy the nations
        to which I have exiled you,but I will not completely destroy you.I will discipline
        you, but with justice;I cannot let you go unpunished.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Message about Philistia'
      title: A Message about Philistia
      number: 1
      content: "  This is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s message to the prophet
        Jeremiah concerning the Philistines of Gaza, before it was captured by the
        Egyptian army. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\u201CA flood is
        coming from the northto overflow the land.It will destroy the land and everything
        in it\u2014cities and people alike.People will scream in terror,and everyone
        in the land will wail.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Hear the clatter of stallions\u2019 hoovesand the rumble of wheels
        as the chariots rush by.Terrified fathers run madly,without a backward glance
        at their helpless children.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CThe time has come for the Philistines to be destroyed,along
        with their allies from Tyre and Sidon.Yes, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        is destroying the remnant of the Philistines,those colonists from the island
        of Crete.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '47:4 '
        content: Hebrew <b>from Caphtor.</b>
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Gaza will be humiliated, its head shaved bald;Ashkelon will lie silent.You
        remnant from the Mediterranean coast,[[COMMENT(0)]]how long will you cut
        yourselves in mourning?  '
      comments:
      - number: '47:5 '
        content: Hebrew <b>the plain.</b>
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CNow, O sword of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,when will you
        be at rest again?Go back into your sheath;rest and be still.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CBut how can it be stillwhen the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has sent it on a mission?For the city of Ashkelonand the people living along
        the seamust be destroyed.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Message about Moab'
      title: A Message about Moab
      number: 1
      content: "  This message was given concerning Moab. This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies, the God of Israel, says:\u201CWhat sorrow awaits
        the city of Nebo;it will soon lie in ruins.The city of Kiriathaim will be
        humiliated and captured;the fortress will be humiliated and broken down.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "No one will ever brag about Moab again,for in Heshbon there is a
        plot to destroy her.\u2018Come,\u2019 they say, \u2018we will cut her off
        from being a nation.\u2019The town of Madmen,[[COMMENT(0)]] too, will be
        silenced;the sword will follow you there.  "
      comments:
      - number: '48:2 '
        content: "<b>Madmen </b>sounds like the Hebrew word for \u201Csilence\u201D;
          it should not be confused with the English word <b>madmen.</b>"
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Listen to the cries from Horonaim,cries of devastation and great
        destruction.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'All Moab is destroyed.Her little ones will cry out.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '48:4 '
        content: Greek version reads <b>Her cries are heard as far away as Zoar.</b>
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Her refugees weep bitterly,climbing the slope to Luhith.They cry
        out in terror,descending the slope to Horonaim.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Flee for your lives!Hide[[COMMENT(0)]] in the wilderness!  '
      comments:
      - number: '48:6 '
        content: Or <b>Hide like a wild donkey; </b>or <b>Hide like a juniper shrub;
          </b>or <b>Be like </b>[the town of] <b>Aroer. </b>The meaning of the Hebrew
          is uncertain.
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Because you have trusted in your wealth and skill,you will be taken
        captive.Your god Chemosh, with his priests and officials,will be hauled off
        to distant lands!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CAll the towns will be destroyed,and no one will escape\u2014either
        on the plateaus or in the valleys,for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has
        spoken.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Oh, that Moab had wingsso she could fly away,[[COMMENT(0)]]for her
        towns will be left empty,with no one living in them.  '
      comments:
      - number: '48:9 '
        content: Or <b>Put salt on Moab, / for she will be laid waste.</b>
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Cursed are those who refuse to do the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        work,who hold back their swords from shedding blood!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CFrom his earliest history, Moab has lived in peace,never going
        into exile.He is like wine that has been allowed to settle.He has not been
        poured from flask to flask,and he is now fragrant and smooth.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "But the time is coming soon,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,\u201Cwhen
        I will send men to pour him from his jar.They will pour him out,then shatter
        the jar!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'At last Moab will be ashamed of his idol Chemosh,as the people of
        Israel were ashamed of their gold calf at Bethel.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '48:13 '
        content: Hebrew <b>ashamed when they trusted in Bethel.</b>
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CYou used to boast, \u2018We are heroes,mighty men of war.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "But now Moab and his towns will be destroyed.His most promising youth
        are doomed to slaughter,\u201Dsays the King, whose name is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CDestruction is coming fast for Moab;calamity threatens ominously.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'You friends of Moab,weep for him and cry!See how the strong scepter
        is broken,how the beautiful staff is shattered!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CCome down from your gloryand sit in the dust, you people of
        Dibon,for those who destroy Moab will shatter Dibon, too.They will tear down
        all your towers.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "You people of Aroer,stand beside the road and watch.Shout to those
        who flee from Moab,\u2018What has happened there?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CAnd the reply comes back,\u2018Moab lies in ruins, disgraced;weep
        and wail!Tell it by the banks of the Arnon River:Moab has been destroyed!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Judgment has been poured out on the towns of the plateau\u2014on
        Holon and Jahaz[[COMMENT(0)]] and Mephaath,  "
      comments:
      - number: '48:21 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Jahzah, </b>a variant spelling of Jahaz.
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'on Dibon and Nebo and Beth-diblathaim,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'on Kiriathaim and Beth-gamul and Beth-meon,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "on Kerioth and Bozrah\u2014all the towns of Moab, far and near.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CThe strength of Moab has ended.His arm has been broken,\u201D
        says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CLet him stagger and fall like a drunkard,for he has rebelled
        against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.Moab will wallow in his own vomit,ridiculed
        by all.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Did you not ridicule the people of Israel?Were they caught in the
        company of thievesthat you should despise them as you do?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u201CYou people of Moab,flee from your towns and live in the caves.Hide
        like doves that nestin the clefts of the rocks.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'We have all heard of the pride of Moab,for his pride is very great.We
        know of his lofty pride,his arrogance, and his haughty heart.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "I know about his insolence,\u201Dsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,\u201Cbut
        his boasts are empty\u2014as empty as his deeds.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'So now I wail for Moab;yes, I will mourn for Moab.My heart is broken
        for the men of Kir-hareseth.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '48:31 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Kir-heres, </b>a variant spelling of Kir-hareseth; also
          in 48:36.
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "\u201CYou people of Sibmah, rich in vineyards,I will weep for you
        even more than I did for Jazer.Your spreading vines once reached as far as
        the Dead Sea,[[COMMENT(0)]]but the destroyer has stripped you bare!He has
        harvested your grapes and summer fruits.  "
      comments:
      - number: '48:32 '
        content: Hebrew <b>the sea of Jazer.</b>
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Joy and gladness are gone from fruitful Moab.The presses yield no
        wine.No one treads the grapes with shouts of joy.There is shouting, yes,
        but not of joy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "\u201CInstead, their awful cries of terror can be heard from Heshbon
        clear across to Elealeh and Jahaz; from Zoar all the way to Horonaim and
        Eglath-shelishiyah. Even the waters of Nimrim are dried up now.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "\u201CI will put an end to Moab,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        \u201Cfor the people offer sacrifices at the pagan shrines and burn incense
        to their false gods. "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'My heart moans like a flute for Moab and Kir-hareseth, for all their
        wealth has disappeared. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'The people shave their heads and beards in mourning. They slash their
        hands and put on clothes made of burlap. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'There is crying and sorrow in every Moabite home and on every street.
        For I have smashed Moab like an old, unwanted jar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "How it is shattered! Hear the wailing! See the shame of Moab! It
        has become an object of ridicule, an example of ruin to all its neighbors.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\u201CLook! The
        enemy swoops down like an eagle,spreading his wings over Moab.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'Its cities will fall,and its strongholds will be seized.Even the
        mightiest warriors will be in anguishlike a woman in labor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'Moab will no longer be a nation,for it has boasted against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "\u201CTerror and traps and snares will be your lot,O Moab,\u201D
        says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "\u201CThose who flee in terror will fall into a trap,and those who
        escape the trap will step into a snare.I will see to it that you do not get
        away,for the time of your judgment has come,\u201Dsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "\u201CThe people flee as far as Heshbonbut are unable to go on.For
        a fire comes from Heshbon,King Sihon\u2019s ancient home,to devour the entire
        landwith all its rebellious people.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: "\u201CWhat sorrow awaits you, O people of Moab!The people of the
        god Chemosh are destroyed!Your sons and your daughtershave been taken away
        as captives.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "But I will restore the fortunes of Moabin days to come.I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        have spoken!\u201DThis is the end of Jeremiah\u2019s prophecy concerning
        Moab."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Message about Ammon'
      title: A Message about Ammon
      number: 1
      content: "  This message was given concerning the Ammonites. This is what the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\u201CAre there no descendants of Israelto
        inherit the land of Gad?Why are you, who worship Molech,[[COMMENT(0)]]living
        in its towns?  "
      comments:
      - number: '49:1 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Malcam, </b>a variant spelling of Molech; also in 49:3.
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "In the days to come,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,\u201CI
        will sound the battle cry against your city of Rabbah.It will become a desolate
        heap of ruins,and the neighboring towns will be burned.Then Israel will take
        back the landyou took from her,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CCry out, O Heshbon,for the town of Ai is destroyed.Weep, O
        people of Rabbah!Put on your clothes of mourning.Weep and wail, hiding in
        the hedges,for your god Molech, with his priests and officials,will be hauled
        off to distant lands.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'You are proud of your fertile valleys,but they will soon be ruined.You
        trusted in your wealth,you rebellious daughter,and thought no one could ever
        harm you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "But look! I will bring terror upon you,\u201Dsays the Lord, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies.\u201CYour neighbors will chase you from your land,and
        no one will help your exiles as they flee.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: Messages about Edom'
      title: Messages about Edom
      number: 6
      content: "But I will restore the fortunes of the Ammonitesin days to come.I,
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, have spoken.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "This message was given concerning Edom. This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies says:\u201CIs there no wisdom in Teman?Is no one
        left to give wise counsel?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Turn and flee!Hide in deep caves, you people of Dedan!For when I
        bring disaster on Edom,[[COMMENT(0)]]I will punish you, too!  '
      comments:
      - number: '49:8 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Esau; </b>also in 49:10.
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Those who harvest grapesalways leave a few for the poor.If thieves
        came at night,they would not take everything.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'But I will strip bare the land of Edom,and there will be no place
        left to hide.Its children, its brothers, and its neighborswill all be destroyed,and
        Edom itself will be no more.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "But I will protect the orphans who remain among you.Your widows,
        too, can depend on me for help.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: \u201CIf the
        innocent must suffer, how much more must you! You will not go unpunished!
        You must drink this cup of judgment! "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "For I have sworn by my own name,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        \u201Cthat Bozrah will become an object of horror and a heap of ruins; it
        will be mocked and cursed. All its towns and villages will be desolate forever.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "I have heard a message from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>that an
        ambassador was sent to the nations to say,\u201CForm a coalition against
        Edom,and prepare for battle!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says to Edom,\u201CI will cut you
        down to size among the nations.You will be despised by all.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "You have been deceivedby the fear you inspire in othersand by your
        own pride.You live in a rock fortressand control the mountain heights.But
        even if you make your nest among the peaks with the eagles,I will bring you
        crashing down,\u201Dsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CEdom will be an object of horror.All who pass by will be appalledand
        will gasp at the destruction they see there.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "It will be like the destruction of Sodom and Gomorrahand their neighboring
        towns,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201CNo one will live
        there;no one will inhabit it.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "I will come like a lion from the thickets of the Jordan,leaping on
        the sheep in the pasture.I will chase Edom from its land,and I will appoint
        the leader of my choice.For who is like me, and who can challenge me?What
        ruler can oppose my will?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Listen to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s plans against Edomand
        the people of Teman.Even the little children will be dragged off like sheep,and
        their homes will be destroyed.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "The earth will shake with the noise of Edom\u2019s fall,and its cry
        of despair will be heard all the way to the Red Sea.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '49:21 '
        content: Hebrew <b>sea of reeds.</b>
    - name: '22: A Message about Damascus'
      title: A Message about Damascus
      number: 22
      content: 'Look! The enemy swoops down like an eagle,spreading his wings over
        Bozrah.Even the mightiest warriors will be in anguishlike a woman in labor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "This message was given concerning Damascus. This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        says:\u201CThe towns of Hamath and Arpad are struck with fear,for they have
        heard the news of their destruction.Their hearts are troubledlike a wild
        sea in a raging storm.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Damascus has become feeble,and all her people turn to flee.Fear,
        anguish, and pain have gripped heras they grip a woman in labor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'That famous city, a city of joy,will be forsaken!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Her young men will fall in the streets and die.Her soldiers will
        all be killed,\u201Dsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: A Message about Kedar and Hazor'
      title: A Message about Kedar and Hazor
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CAnd I will set fire to the walls of Damascusthat will burn
        up the palaces of Ben-hadad.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "This message was given concerning Kedar and the kingdoms of Hazor,
        which were attacked by King Nebuchadnezzar[[COMMENT(0)]] of Babylon. This
        is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\u201CAdvance against Kedar!Destroy
        the warriors from the East!  "
      comments:
      - number: '49:28 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Nebuchadrezzar, </b>a variant spelling of Nebuchadnezzar;
          also in 49:30.
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Their flocks and tents will be captured,and their household goods
        and camels will be taken away.Everywhere shouts of panic will be heard:\u2018We
        are terrorized at every turn!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Run for your lives,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201CHide
        yourselves in deep caves, you people of Hazor,for King Nebuchadnezzar of
        Babylon has plotted against youand is preparing to destroy you.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "\u201CGo up and attack that complacent nation,\u201Dsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201CIts
        people live alone in the desertwithout walls or gates.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Their camels and other livestock will all be yours.I will scatter
        to the winds these peoplewho live in remote places.[[COMMENT(0)]]I will bring
        calamity upon themfrom every direction,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments:
      - number: '49:32 '
        content: Or <b>who clip the corners of their hair.</b>
    - name: '33: A Message about Elam'
      title: A Message about Elam
      number: 33
      content: "\u201CHazor will be inhabited by jackals,and it will be desolate
        forever.No one will live there;no one will inhabit it.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'This message concerning Elam came to the prophet Jeremiah from the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> at the beginning of the reign of King Zedekiah
        of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies
        says:\u201CI will destroy the archers of Elam\u2014the best of their forces.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'I will bring enemies from all directions,and I will scatter the people
        of Elam to the four winds.They will be exiled to countries around the world.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "I myself will go with Elam\u2019s enemies to shatter it.In my fierce
        anger, I will bring great disasterupon the people of Elam,\u201D says the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201CTheir enemies will chase them with the
        sworduntil I have destroyed them completely.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "I will set my throne in Elam,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,\u201Cand
        I will destroy its king and officials.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "But I will restore the fortunes of Elamin days to come.I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        have spoken!\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Message about Babylon'
      title: A Message about Babylon
      number: 1
      content: '  The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave Jeremiah the prophet this
        message concerning Babylon and the land of the Babylonians.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '50:1 '
        content: Or <b>Chaldeans; </b>also in 50:8, 25, 35, 45.
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\u201CTell the
        whole world,and keep nothing back.Raise a signal flagto tell everyone that
        Babylon will fall!Her images and idols[[COMMENT(0)]] will be shattered.Her
        gods Bel and Marduk will be utterly disgraced.  "
      comments:
      - number: '50:2 '
        content: The Hebrew term (literally <b>round things</b>) probably alludes
          to dung.
    - name: '3: Hope for Israel and Judah'
      title: Hope for Israel and Judah
      number: 3
      content: 'For a nation will attack her from the northand bring such destruction
        that no one will live there again.Everything will be gone;both people and
        animals will flee.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CIn those coming days,\u201Dsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,\u201Cthe
        people of Israel will return hometogether with the people of Judah.They will
        come weepingand seeking the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> their God.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'They will ask the way to Jerusalem[[COMMENT(0)]]and will start back
        home again.They will bind themselves to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>with
        an eternal covenant that will never be forgotten.  '
      comments:
      - number: '50:5 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Zion; </b>also in 50:28.
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CMy people have been lost sheep.Their shepherds have led them
        astrayand turned them loose in the mountains.They have lost their wayand
        can\u2019t remember how to get back to the sheepfold.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "All who found them devoured them.Their enemies said,\u2018We did
        nothing wrong in attacking them,for they sinned against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,their
        true place of rest,and the hope of their ancestors.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CBut now, flee from Babylon!Leave the land of the Babylonians.Like
        male goats at the head of the flock,lead my people home again.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "For I am raising up an armyof great nations from the north.They will
        join forces to attack Babylon,and she will be captured.The enemies\u2019
        arrows will go straight to the mark;they will not miss!  "
      comments: []
    - name: "10: Babylon\u2019s Sure Fall"
      title: "Babylon\u2019s Sure Fall"
      number: 10
      content: 'Babylonia[[COMMENT(0)]] will be looteduntil the attackers are glutted
        with loot.I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, have spoken!  '
      comments:
      - number: '50:10 '
        content: Or <b>Chaldea.</b>
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CYou rejoice and are glad,you who plundered my chosen people.You
        frisk about like a calf in a meadowand neigh like a stallion.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "But your homeland[[COMMENT(0)]] will be overwhelmedwith shame and
        disgrace.You will become the least of nations\u2014a wilderness, a dry and
        desolate land.  "
      comments:
      - number: '50:12 '
        content: Hebrew <b>your mother.</b>
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Because of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s anger,Babylon will
        become a deserted wasteland.All who pass by will be horrifiedand will gasp
        at the destruction they see there.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CYes, prepare to attack Babylon,all you surrounding nations.Let
        your archers shoot at her; spare no arrows.For she has sinned against the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Shout war cries against her from every side.Look! She surrenders!Her
        walls have fallen.It is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s vengeance,so
        take vengeance on her.Do to her as she has done to others!  "
      comments: []
    - name: "16: Hope for God\u2019s People"
      title: "Hope for God\u2019s People"
      number: 16
      content: 'Take from Babylon all those who plant crops;send all the harvesters
        away.Because of the sword of the enemy,everyone will run away and rush back
        to their own lands.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CThe Israelites are like sheepthat have been scattered by lions.First
        the king of Assyria ate them up.Then King Nebuchadnezzar[[COMMENT(0)]] of
        Babylon cracked their bones.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '50:17 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Nebuchadrezzar, </b>a variant spelling of Nebuchadnezzar.
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Therefore, this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies,the God of Israel, says:\u201CNow I will punish the king of Babylon
        and his land,just as I punished the king of Assyria.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And I will bring Israel home again to its own land,to feed in the
        fields of Carmel and Bashan,and to be satisfied once morein the hill country
        of Ephraim and Gilead.  '
      comments: []
    - name: "20: The \u2019s Judgment on Babylon"
      title: "The \u2019s Judgment on Babylon"
      number: 20
      content: "In those days,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,\u201Cno
        sin will be found in Israel or in Judah,for I will forgive the remnant I
        preserve.<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CGo up, my warriors, against the land of Merathaimand against
        the people of Pekod.Pursue, kill, and completely destroy[[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps>
        them,</smallcaps>as I have commanded you,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments:
      - number: '50:21 '
        content: The Hebrew term used here refers to the complete consecration of
          things or people to the <span class="ChapterContent_nd__ECPAf">Lord</span>,
          either by destroying them or by giving them as an offering.
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CLet the battle cry be heard in the land,a shout of great destruction.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Babylon, the mightiest hammer in all the earth,lies broken and shattered.Babylon
        is desolate among the nations!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Listen, Babylon, for I have set a trap for you.You are caught, for
        you have fought against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has opened his armoryand brought
        out weapons to vent his fury.The terror that falls upon the Babylonianswill
        be the work of the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Yes, come against her from distant lands.Break open her granaries.Crush
        her walls and houses into heaps of rubble.Destroy her completely, and leave
        nothing!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Destroy even her young bulls\u2014it will be terrible for them, too!Slaughter
        them all!For Babylon\u2019s day of reckoning has come.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Listen to the people who have escaped from Babylon,as they tell in
        Jerusalemhow the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God has taken vengeanceagainst
        those who destroyed his Temple.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CSend out a call for archers to come to Babylon.Surround the
        city so none can escape.Do to her as she has done to others,for she has defied
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the Holy One of Israel.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Her young men will fall in the streets and die.Her soldiers will
        all be killed,\u201Dsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "\u201CSee, I am your enemy, you arrogant people,\u201Dsays the Lord,
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies.\u201CYour day of
        reckoning has arrived\u2014the day when I will punish you.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "O land of arrogance, you will stumble and fall,and no one will raise
        you up.For I will light a fire in the cities of Babylonthat will burn up
        everything around them.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies
        says:\u201CThe people of Israel and Judah have been wronged.Their captors
        hold them and refuse to let them go.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "But the one who redeems them is strong.His name is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies.He will defend themand give them rest again in Israel.But
        for the people of Babylonthere will be no rest!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "\u201CThe sword of destruction will strike the Babylonians,\u201Dsays
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201CIt will strike the people of Babylon\u2014her
        officials and wise men, too.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'The sword will strike her wise counselors,and they will become fools.The
        sword will strike her mightiest warriors,and panic will seize them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'The sword will strike her horses and chariotsand her allies from
        other lands,and they will all become like women.The sword will strike her
        treasures,and they all will be plundered.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'A drought[[COMMENT(0)]] will strike her water supply,causing it to
        dry up.And why? Because the whole land is filled with idols,and the people
        are madly in love with them.  '
      comments:
      - number: '50:38 '
        content: Or <b>sword; </b>the Hebrew words for <b>drought </b>and <b>sword
          </b>are very similar.
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "\u201CSoon Babylon will be inhabited by desert animals and hyenas.It
        will be a home for owls.Never again will people live there;it will lie desolate
        forever.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "I will destroy it as I[[COMMENT(0)]] destroyed Sodom and Gomorrahand
        their neighboring towns,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201CNo
        one will live there;no one will inhabit it.  "
      comments:
      - number: '50:40 '
        content: Hebrew <b>as God.</b>
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "\u201CLook! A great army is coming from the north.A great nation
        and many kingsare rising against you from far-off lands.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'They are armed with bows and spears.They are cruel and show no mercy.As
        they ride forward on horses,they sound like a roaring sea.They are coming
        in battle formation,planning to destroy you, Babylon.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'The king of Babylon has heard reports about the enemy,and he is weak
        with fright.Pangs of anguish have gripped him,like those of a woman in labor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "\u201CI will come like a lion from the thickets of the Jordan,leaping
        on the sheep in the pasture.I will chase Babylon from its land,and I will
        appoint the leader of my choice.For who is like me, and who can challenge
        me?What ruler can oppose my will?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "Listen to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s plans against Babylonand
        the land of the Babylonians.Even the little children will be dragged off
        like sheep,and their homes will be destroyed.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: "The earth will shake with the shout, \u201CBabylon has been taken!\u201Dand
        its cry of despair will be heard around the world."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "  This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\u201CI will
        stir up a destroyer against Babylonand the people of Babylonia.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '51:1 '
        content: Hebrew <b>of Leb-kamai, </b>a code name for Babylonia.
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Foreigners will come and winnow her,blowing her away as chaff.They
        will come from every sideto rise against her in her day of trouble.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Don\u2019t let the archers put on their armoror draw their bows.Don\u2019t
        spare even her best soldiers!Let her army be completely destroyed.[[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps> 
        </smallcaps>"
      comments:
      - number: '51:3 '
        content: The Hebrew term used here refers to the complete consecration of
          things or people to the <span class="ChapterContent_nd__ECPAf">Lord</span>,
          either by destroying them or by giving them as an offering.
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'They will fall dead in the land of the Babylonians,[[COMMENT(0)]]slashed
        to death in her streets.  '
      comments:
      - number: '51:4 '
        content: Or <b>Chaldeans; </b>also in 51:54.
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armieshas not
        abandoned Israel and Judah.He is still their God,even though their land was
        filled with sinagainst the Holy One of Israel.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Flee from Babylon! Save yourselves!Don\u2019t get trapped in her
        punishment!It is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s time for vengeance;he
        will repay her in full.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Babylon has been a gold cup in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        hands,a cup that made the whole earth drunk.The nations drank Babylon\u2019s
        wine,and it drove them all mad.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But suddenly Babylon, too, has fallen.Weep for her.Give her medicine.Perhaps
        she can yet be healed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'We would have helped her if we could,but nothing can save her now.Let
        her go; abandon her.Return now to your own land.For her punishment reaches
        to the heavens;it is so great it cannot be measured.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has vindicated us.Come, let us announce
        in Jerusalem[[COMMENT(0)]]everything the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our
        God has done.  '
      comments:
      - number: '51:10 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Zion; </b>also in 51:24.
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Sharpen the arrows!Lift up the shields![[COMMENT(0)]]For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has inspired the kings of the Medesto march against Babylon and destroy her.This
        is his vengeance against thosewho desecrated his Temple.  '
      comments:
      - number: '51:11 '
        content: Greek version reads <b>Fill up the quivers.</b>
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Raise the battle flag against Babylon!Reinforce the guard and station
        the watchmen.Prepare an ambush,for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will fulfill
        all his plans against Babylon.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'You are a city by a great river,a great center of commerce,but your
        end has come.The thread of your life is cut.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: A Hymn of Praise to the '
      title: 'A Hymn of Praise to the '
      number: 14
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies has taken
        this vowand has sworn to it by his own name:\u201CYour cities will be filled
        with enemies,like fields swarming with locusts,and they will shout in triumph
        over you.\u201D<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> made the earth by his power,and he
        preserves it by his wisdom.With his own understandinghe stretched out the
        heavens.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'When he speaks in the thunder,the heavens roar with rain.He causes
        the clouds to rise over the earth.He sends the lightning with the rainand
        releases the wind from his storehouses.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The whole human race is foolish and has no knowledge!The craftsmen
        are disgraced by the idols they make,for their carefully shaped works are
        a fraud.These idols have no breath or power.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Idols are worthless; they are ridiculous lies!On the day of reckoning
        they will all be destroyed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: "19: Babylon\u2019s Great Punishment"
      title: "Babylon\u2019s Great Punishment"
      number: 19
      content: "But the God of Israel[[COMMENT(0)]] is no idol!He is the Creator
        of everything that exists,including his people, his own special possession.The
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies is his name!  "
      comments:
      - number: '51:19 '
        content: Hebrew <b>the Portion of Jacob. </b>See note on 5:20.
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CYou[[COMMENT(0)]] are my battle-ax and sword,\u201Dsays the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201CWith you I will shatter nationsand destroy
        many kingdoms.  "
      comments:
      - number: '51:20 '
        content: Possibly Cyrus, whom God used to conquer Babylon. Compare Isa 44:28;
          45:1.
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "With you I will shatter armies\u2014destroying the horse and rider,the
        chariot and charioteer.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'With you I will shatter men and women,old people and children,young
        men and young women.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'With you I will shatter shepherds and flocks,farmers and oxen,captains
        and officers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CI will repay Babylonand the people of Babylonia[[COMMENT(0)]]for
        all the wrong they have doneto my people in Jerusalem,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments:
      - number: '51:24 '
        content: Or <b>Chaldea; </b>also in 51:35.
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CLook, O mighty mountain, destroyer of the earth!I am your enemy,\u201D
        says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201CI will raise my fist against you,to
        knock you down from the heights.When I am finished,you will be nothing but
        a heap of burnt rubble.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "You will be desolate forever.Even your stones will never again be
        used for building.You will be completely wiped out,\u201Dsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Raise a signal flag to the nations.Sound the battle cry!Mobilize
        them all against Babylon.Prepare them to fight against her!Bring out the
        armies of Ararat, Minni, and Ashkenaz.Appoint a commander,and bring a multitude
        of horses like swarming locusts!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Bring against her the armies of the nations\u2014led by the kings
        of the Medesand all their captains and officers.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'The earth trembles and writhes in pain,for everything the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has planned against Babylon stands unchanged.Babylon will be left desolate
        without a single inhabitant.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Her mightiest warriors no longer fight.They stay in their barracks,
        their courage gone.They have become like women.The invaders have burned the
        housesand broken down the city gates.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'The news is passed from one runner to the nextas the messengers hurry
        to tell the kingthat his city has been captured.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'All the escape routes are blocked.The marshes have been set aflame,and
        the army is in a panic.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies,the
        God of Israel, says:\u201CBabylon is like wheat on a threshing floor,about
        to be trampled.In just a little whileher harvest will begin.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "\u201CKing Nebuchadnezzar[[COMMENT(0)]] of Babylon has eaten and
        crushed usand drained us of strength.He has swallowed us like a great monsterand
        filled his belly with our riches.He has thrown us out of our own country.  "
      comments:
      - number: '51:34 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Nebuchadrezzar, </b>a variant spelling of Nebuchadnezzar.
    - name: "35: The \u2019s Vengeance on Babylon"
      title: "The \u2019s Vengeance on Babylon"
      number: 35
      content: "Make Babylon suffer as she made us suffer,\u201Dsay the people of
        Zion.\u201CMake the people of Babylonia pay for spilling our blood,\u201Dsays
        Jerusalem.<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says to Jerusalem:\u201CI
        will be your lawyer to plead your case,and I will avenge you.I will dry up
        her river,as well as her springs,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'and Babylon will become a heap of ruins,haunted by jackals.She will
        be an object of horror and contempt,a place where no one lives.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Her people will roar together like strong lions.They will growl like
        lion cubs.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "And while they lie inflamed with all their wine,I will prepare a
        different kind of feast for them.I will make them drink until they fall asleep,and
        they will never wake up again,\u201Dsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "\u201CI will bring them downlike lambs to the slaughter,like rams
        and goats to be sacrificed.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "\u201CHow Babylon[[COMMENT(0)]] is fallen\u2014great Babylon, praised
        throughout the earth!Now she has become an object of horroramong the nations.  "
      comments:
      - number: '51:41 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Sheshach, </b>a code name for Babylon.
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'The sea has risen over Babylon;she is covered by its crashing waves.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'Her cities now lie in ruins;she is a dry wastelandwhere no one lives
        or even passes by.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: A Message for the Exiles'
      title: A Message for the Exiles
      number: 44
      content: 'And I will punish Bel, the god of Babylon,and make him vomit up all
        he has eaten.The nations will no longer come and worship him.The wall of
        Babylon has fallen!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "\u201CCome out, my people, flee from Babylon.Save yourselves! Run
        from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s fierce anger.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: "But do not panic; don\u2019t be afraidwhen you hear the first rumor
        of approaching forces.For rumors will keep coming year by year.Violence will
        erupt in the landas the leaders fight against each other.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'For the time is surely comingwhen I will punish this great city and
        all her idols.Her whole land will be disgraced,and her dead will lie in the
        streets.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: "Then the heavens and earth will rejoice,for out of the north will
        come destroying armiesagainst Babylon,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "\u201CJust as Babylon killed the people of Israeland others throughout
        the world,so must her people be killed.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: "Get out, all you who have escaped the sword!Do not stand and watch\u2014flee
        while you can!Remember the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, though you are in
        a far-off land,and think about your home in Jerusalem.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: "\u201CWe are ashamed,\u201D the people say.\u201CWe are insulted
        and disgracedbecause the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s Templehas been
        defiled by foreigners.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: "\u201CYes,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, \u201Cbut
        the time is comingwhen I will destroy Babylon\u2019s idols.The groans of
        her wounded peoplewill be heard throughout the land.  "
      comments: []
    - name: "53: Babylon\u2019s Complete Destruction"
      title: "Babylon\u2019s Complete Destruction"
      number: 53
      content: 'Though Babylon reaches as high as the heavensand makes her fortifications
        incredibly strong,I will still send enemies to plunder her.I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        have spoken!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: "\u201CListen! Hear the cry of Babylon,the sound of great destruction
        from the land of the Babylonians.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: 'For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is destroying Babylon.He will
        silence her loud voice.Waves of enemies pound against her;the noise of battle
        rings through the city.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: 'Destroying armies come against Babylon.Her mighty men are captured,and
        their weapons break in their hands.For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is
        a God who gives just punishment;he always repays in full.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: "I will make her officials and wise men drunk,along with her captains,
        officers, and warriors.They will fall asleepand never wake up again!\u201Dsays
        the King, whose name isthe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies.  "
      comments: []
    - name: "58: Jeremiah\u2019s Message Sent to Babylon"
      title: "Jeremiah\u2019s Message Sent to Babylon"
      number: 58
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies
        says:\u201CThe thick walls of Babylon will be leveled to the ground,and her
        massive gates will be burned.The builders from many lands have worked in
        vain,for their work will be destroyed by fire!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '59: '
      title: 
      number: 59
      content: "The prophet Jeremiah gave this message to Seraiah son of Neriah and
        grandson of Mahseiah, a staff officer, when Seraiah went to Babylon with
        King Zedekiah of Judah. This was during the fourth year of Zedekiah\u2019s
        reign.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '51:59 '
        content: "The fourth year of Zedekiah\u2019s reign was 593 <span class=\"ChapterContent_sc__Hg9da\">b.c.</span>"
    - name: '60: '
      title: 
      number: 60
      content: "Jeremiah had recorded on a scroll all the terrible disasters that
        would soon come upon Babylon\u2014all the words written here. "
      comments: []
    - name: '61: '
      title: 
      number: 61
      content: "He said to Seraiah, \u201CWhen you get to Babylon, read aloud everything
        on this scroll. "
      comments: []
    - name: '62: '
      title: 
      number: 62
      content: "Then say, \u2018<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, you have said that you
        will destroy Babylon so that neither people nor animals will remain here.
        She will lie empty and abandoned forever.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '63: '
      title: 
      number: 63
      content: 'When you have finished reading the scroll, tie it to a stone and
        throw it into the Euphrates River. '
      comments: []
    - name: '64: '
      title: 
      number: 64
      content: "Then say, \u2018In this same way Babylon and her people will sink,
        never again to rise, because of the disasters I will bring upon her.\u2019\u201DThis
        is the end of Jeremiah\u2019s messages."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Fall of Jerusalem'
      title: The Fall of Jerusalem
      number: 1
      content: '  Zedekiah was twenty-one years old when he became king, and he reigned
        in Jerusalem eleven years. His mother was Hamutal, the daughter of Jeremiah
        from Libnah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "But Zedekiah did what was evil in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        sight, just as Jehoiakim had done. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "These things happened because of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        anger against the people of Jerusalem and Judah, until he finally banished
        them from his presence and sent them into exile.Zedekiah rebelled against
        the king of Babylon. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "So on January 15,[[COMMENT(0)]] during the ninth year of Zedekiah\u2019s
        reign, King Nebuchadnezzar[[COMMENT(1)]] of Babylon led his entire army against
        Jerusalem. They surrounded the city and built siege ramps against its walls. "
      comments:
      - number: '52:4a '
        content: Hebrew <b>on the tenth day of the tenth month, </b>of the ancient
          Hebrew lunar calendar. A number of events in Jeremiah can be cross-checked
          with dates in surviving Babylonian records and related accurately to our
          modern calendar. This day was January 15, 588 <span class="ChapterContent_sc__Hg9da">b.c.</span>
      - number: '52:4b '
        content: Hebrew <b>Nebuchadrezzar, </b>a variant spelling of Nebuchadnezzar;
          also in 52:12, 28, 29, 30.
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Jerusalem was kept under siege until the eleventh year of King Zedekiah\u2019s
        reign.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "By July 18 in the eleventh year of Zedekiah\u2019s reign,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        the famine in the city had become very severe, and the last of the food was
        entirely gone. "
      comments:
      - number: '52:6 '
        content: "Hebrew <b>By the ninth day of the fourth month </b>[in the eleventh
          year of Zedekiah\u2019s reign]. This day was July 18, 586 <span class=\"ChapterContent_sc__Hg9da\">b.c.</span>;
          also see note on 52:4a."
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then a section of the city wall was broken down, and all the soldiers
        fled. Since the city was surrounded by the Babylonians,[[COMMENT(0)]] they
        waited for nightfall. Then they slipped through the gate between the two
        walls behind the king\u2019s garden and headed toward the Jordan Valley.[[COMMENT(1)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '52:7a '
        content: Or <b>the Chaldeans; </b>similarly in 52:8, 17.
      - number: '52:7b '
        content: Hebrew <b>the Arabah.</b>
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But the Babylonian troops chased King Zedekiah and overtook him on
        the plains of Jericho, for his men had all deserted him and scattered. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'They captured the king and took him to the king of Babylon at Riblah
        in the land of Hamath. There the king of Babylon pronounced judgment upon
        Zedekiah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The king of Babylon made Zedekiah watch as he slaughtered his sons.
        He also slaughtered all the officials of Judah at Riblah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: The Temple Destroyed'
      title: The Temple Destroyed
      number: 11
      content: "Then he gouged out Zedekiah\u2019s eyes and bound him in bronze chains,
        and the king of Babylon led him away to Babylon. Zedekiah remained there
        in prison until the day of his death.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "On August 17 of that year,[[COMMENT(0)]] which was the nineteenth
        year of King Nebuchadnezzar\u2019s reign, Nebuzaradan, the captain of the
        guard and an official of the Babylonian king, arrived in Jerusalem. "
      comments:
      - number: '52:12 '
        content: Hebrew <b>On the tenth day of the fifth month, </b>of the ancient
          Hebrew lunar calendar. This day was August 17, 586 <span class="ChapterContent_sc__Hg9da">b.c.</span>;
          also see note on 52:4a.
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'He burned down the Temple of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the
        royal palace, and all the houses of Jerusalem. He destroyed all the important
        buildings[[COMMENT(0)]] in the city. '
      comments:
      - number: '52:13 '
        content: Or <b>destroyed the houses of all the important people.</b>
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then he supervised the entire Babylonian[[COMMENT(0)]] army as they
        tore down the walls of Jerusalem on every side. '
      comments:
      - number: '52:14 '
        content: Or <b>Chaldean.</b>
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then Nebuzaradan, the captain of the guard, took as exiles some of
        the poorest of the people, the rest of the people who remained in the city,
        the defectors who had declared their allegiance to the king of Babylon, and
        the rest of the craftsmen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'But Nebuzaradan allowed some of the poorest people to stay behind
        to care for the vineyards and fields.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "The Babylonians broke up the bronze pillars in front of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        Temple, the bronze water carts, and the great bronze basin called the Sea,
        and they carried all the bronze away to Babylon. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'They also took all the ash buckets, shovels, lamp snuffers, basins,
        dishes, and all the other bronze articles used for making sacrifices at the
        Temple. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The captain of the guard also took the small bowls, incense burners,
        basins, pots, lampstands, ladles, bowls used for liquid offerings, and all
        the other articles made of pure gold or silver.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "The weight of the bronze from the two pillars, the Sea with the twelve
        bronze oxen beneath it, and the water carts was too great to be measured.
        These things had been made for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s Temple
        in the days of King Solomon. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Each of the pillars was 27 feet tall and 18 feet in circumference.[[COMMENT(0)]]
        They were hollow, with walls 3 inches thick.[[COMMENT(1)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '52:21a '
        content: Hebrew <b>18 cubits </b>[8.3 meters] <b>tall and 12 cubits </b>[5.5
          meters] <b>in circumference.</b>
      - number: '52:21b '
        content: Hebrew <b>4 fingers thick </b>[8 centimeters].
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The bronze capital on top of each pillar was 7-1/2 feet[[COMMENT(0)]]
        high and was decorated with a network of bronze pomegranates all the way
        around. '
      comments:
      - number: '52:22 '
        content: Hebrew <b>5 cubits </b>[2.3 meters].
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'There were 96 pomegranates on the sides, and a total of 100 pomegranates
        on the network around the top.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Nebuzaradan, the captain of the guard, took with him as prisoners
        Seraiah the high priest, Zephaniah the priest of the second rank, and the
        three chief gatekeepers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And from among the people still hiding in the city, he took an officer
        who had been in charge of the Judean army; seven of the king\u2019s personal
        advisers; the army commander\u2019s chief secretary, who was in charge of
        recruitment; and sixty other citizens. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Nebuzaradan, the captain of the guard, took them all to the king
        of Babylon at Riblah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And there at Riblah, in the land of Hamath, the king of Babylon had
        them all put to death. So the people of Judah were sent into exile from their
        land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "The number of captives taken to Babylon in the seventh year of Nebuchadnezzar\u2019s
        reign[[COMMENT(0)]] was 3,023. "
      comments:
      - number: '52:28 '
        content: "This exile in the seventh year of Nebuchadnezzar\u2019s reign occurred
          in 597 <span class=\"ChapterContent_sc__Hg9da\">b.c.</span>"
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Then in Nebuchadnezzar\u2019s eighteenth year[[COMMENT(0)]] he took
        832 more. "
      comments:
      - number: '52:29 '
        content: "This exile in the eighteenth year of Nebuchadnezzar\u2019s reign
          occurred in 586 <span class=\"ChapterContent_sc__Hg9da\">b.c.</span>"
    - name: "30: Hope for Israel\u2019s Royal Line"
      title: "Hope for Israel\u2019s Royal Line"
      number: 30
      content: "In Nebuchadnezzar\u2019s twenty-third year[[COMMENT(0)]] he sent
        Nebuzaradan, the captain of the guard, who took 745 more\u2014a total of
        4,600 captives in all.  "
      comments:
      - number: '52:30 '
        content: "This exile in the twenty-third year of Nebuchadnezzar\u2019s reign
          occurred in 581 <span class=\"ChapterContent_sc__Hg9da\">b.c.</span>"
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'In the thirty-seventh year of the exile of King Jehoiachin of Judah,
        Evil-merodach ascended to the Babylonian throne. He was kind to[[COMMENT(0)]]
        Jehoiachin and released him from prison on March 31 of that year.[[COMMENT(1)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '52:31a '
        content: Hebrew <b>He raised the head of.</b>
      - number: '52:31b '
        content: Hebrew <b>on the twenty-fifth day of the twelfth month, </b>of the
          ancient Hebrew lunar calendar. This day was March 31, 561 <span class="ChapterContent_sc__Hg9da">b.c.</span>;
          also see note on 52:4a.
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'He spoke kindly to Jehoiachin and gave him a higher place than all
        the other exiled kings in Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "He supplied Jehoiachin with new clothes to replace his prison garb
        and allowed him to dine in the king\u2019s presence for the rest of his life. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: So the Babylonian king gave him a regular food allowance as long as
        he lived. This continued until the day of his death.
      comments: []
